{"type":"text","timestamp":1784624001967,"sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","part":{"id":"prt_f83e110fc001lgDuSl5H6AZqDC","messageID":"msg_f83e0dfed001PnGWcNgq9WoThY","sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","type":"text","text":"The command contract confirms this is a valid pre-bound autonomous invocation: setup is resolved, `max-iterations` suppresses early convergence stops, and the provided lineage override replaces artifact-root resolution. I’m binding the auto YAML and executor contracts next; no target analysis or artifact writes will occur outside the workflow-owned lineage.","time":{"start":1784623993084,"end":1784624001966},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0a88b627636cb19a016a5f3378e6c48191aed00d916846cc66","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784624002108,"sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_S3wadgTNAURsim1avMh8E7Hr","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast</path>\n<type>directory</type>\n<entries>\n.executor-state/\n\n(1 entries)\n</entries>","metadata":{"preview":".executor-state/","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"directory","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast","entries":[".executor-state/"],"offset":1,"totalEntries":1,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast","time":{"start":1784624002093,"end":1784624002102}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a88b627636cb19a016a5f3381e1208191b4ba971082f5c3a6"}},"id":"prt_f83e134250015Xbr76aQRz6exx","sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","messageID":"msg_f83e0dfed001PnGWcNgq9WoThY"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784624002126,"sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"skill","callID":"call_IS6qkSPVFmLlsfxlx46OhugP","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"name":"cli-opencode"},"output":"<skill_content name=\"cli-opencode\">\n# Skill: cli-opencode\n\n<!-- Keywords: opencode, opencode-cli, opencode-run, cross-ai, spec-kit-runtime, plugin-runtime, parallel-sessions, share-url, detached-session, agent-delegation, deepseek, openai, minimax, minimax-coding-plan, minimax-m3, token-plan, xiaomi, xiaomi-token-plan, xiaomi-token-plan-ams, xiaomi-api, xiaomi-direct, mimo, mimo-v2.5-pro, mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed, ultraspeed, glm-5.2, zai-coding-plan, z.ai-coding-plan, glm-coding-plan -->\n\n# OpenCode CLI Orchestrator - Full-Runtime Cross-AI Dispatch\n\n> **CRITICAL — SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED**\n>\n> This skill dispatches to the OpenCode CLI binary (`opencode`). If the agent currently reading this skill is itself running inside OpenCode (TUI / acp / serve / run modes — detection signals listed in §2), the skill MUST refuse to load and return the documented error message instead of generating any `opencode` invocation. The only exception is an explicit \"parallel detached\" request that intentionally spawns a SEPARATE session with its own session id and state directory.\n>\n> A running CLI skill never dispatches itself. The cli-X skills are for **cross-AI delegation only** — never self-invocation.\n\nOrchestrate OpenCode's `opencode run` from external AI assistants (Claude Code, OpenCode, raw shell) AND from inside an existing OpenCode session for parallel detached workers. Three documented use cases keep the cycle risk explicit while giving every dispatch path a copy-paste invocation shape.\n\n**Core Principle**: The calling AI stays the conductor. Delegate to OpenCode for what it does best — full plugin, skill, MCP, and Spec Kit Memory runtime in a one-shot dispatch. Validate and integrate the output.\n\n---\n\n## 1. WHEN TO USE\n\n### Activation Triggers\n\n- **Full plugin / skill / MCP runtime** (use case 1) — calling AI is Claude Code / OpenCode / Copilot / raw shell AND the task needs the project's full Spec Kit Memory database, Code Graph semantic index, structural code graph, or every plugin/skill/MCP tool in a one-shot dispatch. Includes `@deep-research` / `@deep-review` agent loops with externalized state under `.opencode/specs/`.\n- **Parallel detached session** (use case 2) — operator already inside OpenCode (TUI / web / serve / acp) AND wants a SEPARATE session with its own session id and state directory for ablation, worker farm, or parallel research. Prompt explicitly mentions \"parallel detached\", \"ablation suite\", \"worker farm\", \"parallel research\", \"spawn detached\", or \"share URL\".\n- **Cross-AI orchestration handback** (use case 3) — calling AI is non-Anthropic (OpenCode / Copilot), task targets a project-specific subsystem (spec-kit, memory, code-graph, advisor), and the non-Anthropic CLI cannot load the project's plugin/skill/MCP runtime on its own and needs OpenCode as a bridge. When the caller only needs a daemon-backed tool call, prefer the shipped front doors (`spec-memory.cjs`, `code-index.cjs`, `skill-advisor.cjs`) over a full `opencode run` delegation.\n- **Agent dispatch** — task matches a specialized OpenCode agent. Primary agents (directly invokable via `--agent`): `general`, `plan` (built-in), `orchestrate`. Generic subagents fully dispatched via the orchestrate primary: `context`, `review`, `write`, `debug`, `ai-council`. Command-owned loop executors (`deep-research`, `deep-review`, `deep-improvement`, `prompt-improver`) are owned end-to-end by their parent `/deep:*` command; `orchestrate` may perform exactly one bounded hand-off dispatch to a recognized loop request, but never manages the loop itself. See §3 \"OpenCode Agent Delegation\" for the full contract.\n- **Cross-repo dispatch** — session in repo A dispatches into repo B's plugin/skill/MCP runtime via `--dir <path>` or remote OpenCode server via `--attach <url>`.\n\n### When NOT to Use\n\n- **You ARE OpenCode already.** If your runtime is OpenCode (detection signal: `$OPENCODE_CONFIG_DIR` or any `OPENCODE_*` env var set, `opencode` in process ancestry, or `~/.opencode/state/<id>/lock` present), this skill refuses to load. Self-invocation creates a circular dispatch loop and burns tokens for no value. The cli-X family is exclusively for cross-AI delegation. The single legitimate exception is an explicit \"parallel detached\" request that intentionally spawns a SEPARATE session id and state directory (use case 2); without that qualifier, the smart router refuses per ADR-001.\n- Simple, quick tasks where `opencode run` overhead is not worth it.\n- Tasks that only need a raw model dispatch — use a sibling cli-* skill.\n- Tasks requiring interactive TUI or web UI (use `opencode` directly instead of `opencode run`).\n- Context already loaded and understood by the calling AI.\n- Tasks where the OpenCode binary is not installed at the expected path.\n\n---\n\n## 2. SMART ROUTING\n\n\n### Prerequisite Detection\n\n```bash\n# Verify OpenCode CLI is available\ncommand -v opencode || echo \"Not installed. Run: brew install opencode (macOS) or curl -fsSL https://opencode.ai/install | bash\"\n```\n\n### Self-Invocation Guard (ADR-001)\n\nBefore any dispatch, run the layered ADR-001 detection: Layer 1 env-var lookup for any `OPENCODE_*`, Layer 2 process-ancestry probe for an `opencode` parent, Layer 3 a best-effort `~/.opencode/state/<id>/lock` probe. A positive on any layer refuses the dispatch unless the prompt carries explicit parallel-session keywords (use case 2), which permits a SEPARATE session id and state directory instead. Full bash + python detection: [`references/self-invocation-guard.md`](./references/self-invocation-guard.md). Decision tree + refusal text: [`references/integration-patterns.md`](./references/integration-patterns.md) §5.\n\n### Resource Loading Levels\n\n| Level       | When to Load            | Resources                      |\n| ----------- | ----------------------- | ------------------------------ |\n| ALWAYS      | Every skill invocation  | `references/cli-reference.md`, `assets/prompt-quality-card.md` |\n| CONDITIONAL | If intent signals match | Intent-mapped reference docs   |\n| ON_DEMAND   | Only on explicit request| Extended templates and patterns |\n\n### Smart Router\n\nIntent-specific dictionaries (used by the shared helper functions in [`system-spec-kit/references/cli/shared-smart-router.md`](../../system-spec-kit/references/cli/shared-smart-router.md)):\n\n- Pattern 1: Runtime Discovery - `discover_markdown_resources()` recursively scans existing `references/` and `assets/` folders with `base.exists()` safeguards.\n- Pattern 2: Existence-Check Before Load - `load_if_available()` uses `_guard_in_skill()`, `inventory`, and `seen` so raw loads, missing files, duplicate loads, and path escapes are rejected.\n- Pattern 3: Not applicable here - `cli-opencode` has flat resource folders, not keyed `references/<key>/` or `assets/<key>/` subdirectories. Routing selects from `RESOURCE_MAP` by intent signal rather than by runtime resource key.\n- Pattern 4: Multi-Tier Graceful Fallback - low-confidence intent scores return `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK` with a disambiguation checklist; missing intent resources still return always-load baseline docs plus a clear notice.\n\n```python\nINTENT_SIGNALS = {\n    \"EXTERNAL_DISPATCH\":  {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"delegate to opencode\", \"opencode run\", \"from claude code\", \"from opencode\", \"from copilot\", \"external runtime\", \"full plugin runtime\", \"hand this off to opencode\", \"hand off to opencode\", \"send this to opencode\", \"dispatch to opencode\", \"run this through opencode\", \"let opencode handle this\", \"opencode's full runtime\", \"full runtime dispatch\", \"one-shot dispatch\", \"invoke opencode\", \"kick this off in opencode\", \"have opencode take care of this\", \"get opencode to run this\", \"pass this over to opencode\", \"opencode has access to every tool\", \"opencode has the whole toolchain\", \"since opencode has all the plugins\", \"opencode can load every skill\", \"ask opencode to handle this\", \"opencode should handle this\", \"offload this to opencode\", \"outsource this to opencode\", \"forward this to opencode\", \"route this to opencode\", \"push this to opencode\", \"opencode has everything loaded\", \"opencode has the whole toolset\", \"opencode cli\", \"run externally\", \"full toolset\", \"handle this externally\", \"external ai assistant\", \"run in opencode\", \"hand off externally\"]},\n    \"PARALLEL_DETACHED\":  {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"parallel detached\", \"ablation suite\", \"worker farm\", \"parallel research\", \"spawn detached\", \"share url\", \"share-url\", \"detached session\", \"separate session id\", \"own state directory\", \"spin up a new session\", \"background opencode session\", \"run this in the background\", \"fan out workers\", \"concurrent sessions\", \"isolated session\", \"run these in parallel\", \"spin off a few workers\", \"kick off several sessions at once\", \"run copies side by side\", \"fire off multiple runs at the same time\", \"farm this out to multiple workers\", \"run a bunch of these concurrently\", \"distribute the work across sessions\", \"batch this across sessions\", \"start several sessions at once\", \"spin up another instance\", \"new opencode instance\", \"run it as its own session\", \"own separate session\", \"side session\", \"run this independently\", \"additional worker\", \"background job\", \"separate instance\", \"own instance\", \"parallel run\", \"concurrent run\", \"session of its own\", \"spin up a worker\", \"worker pool\", \"run in parallel\"]},\n    \"CROSS_AI_HANDBACK\":  {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"spec kit\", \"spec-kit\", \"spec_kit\", \"code graph\", \"memory_search\", \"session_bootstrap\", \"skill advisor\", \"cross-ai handback\", \"hand back to opencode\", \"bridge back to opencode\", \"opencode as a bridge\", \"non-anthropic cli\", \"project's memory database\", \"structural code index\", \"use the skill advisor\"]},\n    \"AGENT_DISPATCH\":     {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"delegate\", \"agent\", \"deep-research\", \"deep-review\", \"ai-council\", \"review agent\", \"context agent\", \"dispatch an agent\", \"spawn an agent\", \"run a subagent\", \"invoke a subagent\", \"specialized subagent\", \"debug agent\", \"write agent\"]},\n    \"CROSS_REPO\":         {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"cross-repo\", \"different repo\", \"--dir\", \"another repository\", \"remote opencode\", \"different repository\", \"target repo\", \"other codebase\", \"separate repository\", \"remote opencode server\", \"--attach\"]},\n    \"TEMPLATES\":          {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"template\", \"prompt\", \"how to ask\", \"opencode prompt\", \"minimax\", \"MiniMax-M3\", \"tidd-ec\", \"prompt framework\", \"prompt template\", \"how do i phrase this\", \"copy-paste template\", \"prompt quality\", \"prompt craft\", \"costar framework\", \"example prompt\"]},\n    \"PATTERNS\":           {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"pattern\", \"workflow\", \"orchestrate\", \"session continue\", \"resume session\", \"integration pattern\", \"dispatch pattern\", \"continue the session\", \"resume a session\", \"session continuation\"]},\n    # WHY: DESIGN is an intent signal only — a deliberate cross-skill handoff to sk-design,\n    # not a same-skill resource bundle. It intentionally has NO RESOURCE_MAP entry: this skill\n    # hands design work off rather than owning design reference docs. The durable sk-design\n    # loading contract lives in the always-fires Design Standards Loading rule and the dispatch\n    # manifest (see ALWAYS rules 13-14); RESOURCE_MAP stays limited to same-skill markdown paths.\n    \"DESIGN\":             {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"sk-design\", \"interface design\", \"frontend design\", \"visual design\", \"redesign the ui\", \"design foundations\", \"design tokens\", \"motion design\", \"micro-interactions\", \"design audit\", \"ui critique\", \"extract design system\", \"generate design.md\"]},\n}\n\nRESOURCE_MAP = {\n    \"EXTERNAL_DISPATCH\":  [\"references/cli-reference.md\", \"references/integration-patterns.md\"],\n    \"PARALLEL_DETACHED\":  [\"references/integration-patterns.md\", \"assets/prompt-templates.md\"],\n    \"CROSS_AI_HANDBACK\":  [\"references/integration-patterns.md\", \"references/opencode-tools.md\"],\n    \"AGENT_DISPATCH\":     [\"references/agent-delegation.md\", \"assets/prompt-templates.md\"],\n    \"CROSS_REPO\":         [\"references/cli-reference.md\", \"references/opencode-tools.md\"],\n    \"TEMPLATES\":          [\"assets/prompt-templates.md\", \"references/cli-reference.md\"],\n    \"PATTERNS\":           [\"references/integration-patterns.md\", \"references/cli-reference.md\"],\n}\n\nLOADING_LEVELS = {\n    \"ALWAYS\": [\"references/cli-reference.md\", \"assets/prompt-quality-card.md\"],\n    \"ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS\": [\"full reference\", \"all templates\", \"deep dive\", \"complete guide\", \"opencode agent\", \"opencode prompt\", \"share url\", \"ablation\", \"worker farm\", \"self-invocation\", \"memory handback\", \"minimax\", \"MiniMax-M3\", \"tidd-ec\"],\n    \"ON_DEMAND\": [\"references/opencode-tools.md\", \"assets/prompt-templates.md\"],\n}\n\nUNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST = [\n    \"Is the user asking about OpenCode CLI specifically?\",\n    \"Does the task need the project's full plugin / skill / MCP runtime?\",\n    \"Is a parallel detached session what they want?\",\n    \"Is a non-Anthropic CLI handing back to OpenCode for a spec-kit workflow?\",\n]\n```\n\n**Call sequence** (using shared helpers from `shared-smart-router.md`):\n\n1. `discover_markdown_resources()` — recursively enumerate current `.md` files under existing `references/` and `assets/` folders at routing time.\n2. `_guard_in_skill()` + `load_if_available()` — sandbox paths to this skill, reject non-markdown loads, skip missing files, and suppress duplicates.\n3. `score_intents(task)` and `select_intents(scores, ambiguity_delta=1.0)` — preserve provider-specific weighted intent scoring and top-2 ambiguity handling.\n4. ALWAYS-load `LOADING_LEVELS[\"ALWAYS\"]`, then return `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK` with `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST` when max score is 0.\n5. CONDITIONAL-load existing `RESOURCE_MAP[intent]` entries via `load_if_available()`, ON_DEMAND-load keyword matches, and return a notice when no intent-specific knowledge base is available beyond always-load resources.\n\nThe `route_opencode_resources(task)` function body lives in [`shared-smart-router.md`](../../system-spec-kit/references/cli/shared-smart-router.md) — substitute `<PROVIDER>` = `opencode`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. HOW IT WORKS\n\n### Prerequisites\n\n```bash\n# Verify installation (cli-opencode v1.0.0 is pinned to opencode v1.3.17)\nopencode --version | grep -q '^1\\.' || echo \"Not installed or version drift. See references/cli-reference.md §9.\"\n\n# Self-invocation guard\nenv | grep -q '^OPENCODE_' && echo \"ERROR: Already inside OpenCode session\"\n\n# Authentication — providers configured via opencode providers (alias auth)\nopencode providers\n```\n\n**Authentication options**: `opencode providers login <provider>` (and `opencode auth login` for subscription plans). Full per-provider login shapes and the configured-provider list: `references/cli-reference.md` §4.\n\n### Provider Auth Pre-Flight (Smart Fallback)\n\n**MANDATORY before any first dispatch in a session.** The default provider may not be logged in — silently failing with `provider/model not found` or `401 Unauthorized` mid-dispatch wastes a round-trip. Run the pre-flight once per session, cache the result, and re-run only on an auth failure.\n\nThe one-shot pre-flight bash, the per-provider decision trees, the user-facing prompt templates for missing providers, and the error-recovery contract live in [`references/cli-reference.md`](./references/cli-reference.md) §4 — do not duplicate them here. Never substitute a model the user didn't approve; ASK when the default is unavailable.\n\n### Default Invocation (Skill Default)\n\n**Default model + variant + format + dir**: `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro` · `--variant high` · `--format json` · `--dir <repo-root>` (pinned to avoid CWD ambiguity). Direct DeepSeek is the default provider — elevated reasoning at low cost for routine dispatches.\n\nUse `opencode run --model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --variant high --format json --dir <repo-root> \"<prompt>\"`.\n\n> **The `--agent` flag (read this):** Do NOT pass `--agent` on a top-level `opencode run` — current opencode treats named agents like `general` as **subagents** and rejects them at the top level, so `--agent general` fails outright. The default agent runs when `--agent` is omitted, which is correct for almost every dispatch. **To target a specific agent profile, describe the role in the prompt body instead** (e.g. open with \"Act as a code-review agent: …\"); only pass `--agent <name>` after confirming acceptance via `opencode run --help` on the installed version.\n\nHonor explicit user model, port, and handback phrasing verbatim; otherwise use the default invocation above.\n\n### Core Invocation Pattern\n\nCore flags: `--model`, `--agent`, `--variant`, `--format json`, `--dir`, continuation/session/fork flags, `--share` and `--port` for detached sessions, `--file`, `--thinking`, `--pure`, and log flags.\n\n> **Non-interactive invocation stdin**: always append `</dev/null` to any non-interactive `opencode run` invocation — without it, opencode can inherit parent-terminal stdin and hang. See `references/integration-patterns.md` §6.\n\n> **Registered command dispatch (`--command`)**: slash-command text inside a `run` message is NOT expanded — `opencode run \"/memory:search query\"` delivers the slash text as raw prose. Execute a registered command via `opencode run --command <family>/<name> [flags] \"<args>\"` (becomes `$ARGUMENTS`; e.g. `memory/search` for `/memory:search`). Full semantics: `references/cli-reference.md` §4.\n\n### Model Selection\n\nRun `opencode providers list` to confirm credentials and `opencode models <provider>` for live choices. Default: `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --variant high` (direct DeepSeek API). Alternates (all omit `--agent`): MiniMax Token Plan/Direct API `MiniMax-M3`, Xiaomi Token Plan/Direct API `mimo-v2.5-pro` (+ low-latency `-ultraspeed`), Kimi For Coding `k2p7` (256k, subscription), Z.AI GLM Coding Plan `glm-5.2` (1M, subscription), and the OpenAI GPT-5.6 catalog (`gpt-5.6-sol` flagship default; bare/Sol/Terra/Luna x base/Fast/Pro, `--variant` up to `xhigh`). Full model table, per-provider `--variant` mapping, and model-specific operational caveats: `references/cli-reference.md` §5.\n\nShared small-model facts, context defaults, quota pools, and fallback targets live in `../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/assets/model-profiles.json`.\n\n### OpenCode Agent Delegation\n\nThe calling AI is the conductor. OpenCode distinguishes **primary agents** (directly invokable via `--agent <slug>`) from **subagents** (dispatched as Task-tool subagents from a primary).\n\n#### Primary agents — directly invokable via `--agent`\n\nOpenCode defines `general`, `plan`, and `orchestrate` as primary agents. **Never pass `--agent general`** — it is rejected at the top level; the default agent (used when `--agent` is omitted) already covers that case. Pin `--agent plan|orchestrate` only when the task needs that profile AND `opencode run --help` confirms top-level acceptance; otherwise state the role in the prompt body.\n\n#### Subagents — dispatched as Task subagents from a primary\n\nThese live at `.opencode/agents/<slug>.md` with `mode: subagent` and are NOT directly invokable via `opencode run --agent`. Three dispatch surfaces are legal under the single-hop NDP contract:\n\n1. **Generic subagents** (`context`, `review`, `write`, `debug`) — dispatched by `orchestrate` via the Task tool. Route through `--agent orchestrate` and let it dispatch the relevant subagent.\n2. **`ai-council`** — dispatched via `/deep:ai-council` or `orchestrate`'s registry-backed Task-dispatch. Direct `--agent ai-council` is rejected at the top level (`mode: subagent`).\n3. **Command-owned loop executors** (`deep-research`, `deep-review`, `deep-improvement`, `prompt-improver`) — LOOP-OWNED by their parent commands (`/deep:research`, `/deep:review`, `/deep:agent-improvement`, `/prompt`), which own iteration state, convergence detection, and continuity. Never dispatch these directly via raw `--agent <slug>`. `orchestrate` is an authorized **caller/coordinator only** — it may perform exactly one bounded hand-off dispatch to the resolved leaf, but MUST NOT re-implement the loop.\n\nSee [agent-delegation.md](./references/agent-delegation.md) for the complete agent roster and dispatch patterns.\n\n### Unique OpenCode Strengths\n\nFull project runtime loading, detached sessions, JSON event streams, agent routing, cross-repo/server dispatch, session continuation, and plugin-disable debugging.\n\n### Essential Commands\n\nDefault invocation for external runtime handback; `--share --port <N>` only for explicit detached sessions; `--agent orchestrate` for generic subagent routing; `--dir` for cross-repo dispatch.\n\n### Error Handling\n\nInstall missing binaries, refuse ambiguous self-invocation, run provider pre-flight for model/auth errors, check version drift for unknown flags, force `--format json` for empty streams, add `</dev/null` for background loops, confirm `--share`, use `--pure` only for plugin crashes, inspect state logs for stuck sessions.\n\n---\n\n## 4. RULES\n\n### ✅ ALWAYS\n\n1. Verify OpenCode CLI is installed before first invocation; confirm version baseline against v1.3.17 (drift handling per `references/cli-reference.md` §9).\n2. **Run the self-invocation guard before dispatch** (ADR-001): Layer 1 env-var lookup for any `OPENCODE_*`, Layer 2 process-ancestry probe for `opencode` parent, Layer 3 `~/.opencode/state/<id>/lock` probe. Trip on ANY positive — refuse unless prompt has explicit parallel-session keywords.\n3. Pin model + variant + format + dir explicitly — **no `--agent`** (see the Default Invocation note: current opencode rejects a top-level `--agent general`; put any agent-profile request in the prompt body). Default: `--model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --variant high --format json --dir <repo-root>`. Honor user overrides verbatim (e.g. `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro`, `minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3`, `minimax/MiniMax-M3`, `xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro`, `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro`, `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed`, `openai/gpt-5.6-sol-pro`).\n4. Pass `--format json` unless the calling AI explicitly wants formatted output — JSON event stream is what external runtimes parse incrementally.\n5. **Append `</dev/null` to every non-interactive `opencode run` invocation** that redirects stdout and/or stderr to files OR runs inside `while read` loops. opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation; without explicit closed stdin, automation hangs forever at 0% CPU after the `+60s service=snapshot prune=7.days cleanup` log line. Position: AFTER the prompt positional argument, BEFORE the `> stdout 2> stderr` redirects. Foreground `| tail` happens to provide closed stdin (pipe stage upstream is empty) and accidentally bypasses the bug, but `> stdout.log 2> stderr.log` does not. The 9-character `</dev/null` redirect provides immediate EOF on stdin, unblocking the dispatch. **DO NOT auto-kill external operator-owned opencode sessions** when sweeping orphans between dispatches; exclude `opencode run` from pkill (per 2026-05-23 operator directive captured in memory `feedback_proactive_orphan_cleanup.md`). See `references/integration-patterns.md` §6 + memory `feedback_opencode_run_requires_dev_null_stdin.md` + CHANGELOG-2026-05-08-tool-name-regex-fix.md §Fix 4.\n6. **Pass the spec folder to the dispatched session** in the prompt: if the calling AI has an active Gate-3 spec folder, include `Spec folder: <path> (pre-approved, skip Gate 3)`. If none, ASK the user before delegating — the dispatched session cannot answer Gate 3 interactively in non-interactive `run` mode.\n7. **Prompt construction & model-craft (cli-* family precedence).** Compose every dispatch prompt via the 3-tier rule canonical in `../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/assets/cli-prompt-quality-card.md`:\n   1. **Fast path (default).** Build from the local `assets/prompt-quality-card.md`, which delegates the framework table + CLEAR check to the canonical card.\n   2. **Model override (mandatory for a profiled model).** If the target model has a profile at `../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/references/models/<id>.md`, that profile OVERRIDES the cross-model default. The **sk-prompt/prompt-models** hub owns per-model prompt-craft (framework + scaffold + gotchas, mirroring `sk-prompt/prompt-models/assets/model-profiles.json` `recommended_frameworks`); consult it before composing for any small model.\n   3. **Deep path (escalation).** Dispatch `@prompt-improver` via the Task tool (never load full `sk-prompt` inline) when any canonical **Tier 3** trigger applies — the trigger list lives in `../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/assets/cli-prompt-quality-card.md` under \"Tier 3 — Deep path\"; do not re-enumerate it here.\n8. Validate dispatched session output: parse JSON events incrementally (tool calls, partial messages, final summary), run syntax checks if code generated, and cross-reference against project standards via `sk-code` surface detection plus its code-review mode when findings-first review is requested (see ALWAYS rule 12).\n9. Capture stderr (`2>&1`) to catch tool errors and warnings.\n10. Classify the use case (1 / 2 / 3) before dispatching — the smart router refuses dispatches that do not map to one of the three.\n11. **Run the Provider Auth Pre-Flight once per session** (see §3 Provider Auth Pre-Flight). Cache the configured-providers list. If the default `deepseek` is missing, ASK the user — never silently substitute the model. If a later dispatch returns an auth error, invalidate the cache and rerun the pre-flight before retrying.\n12. **Code Standards Loading (surface-aware contract)** — When dispatching for code review or code generation, instruct the dispatched session to: (1) load `sk-code`; (2) let `sk-code` emit a surface tag matching the detected stack from markers and target files; (3) load the selected surface resources and run its verification commands; (4) load `sk-code`'s code-review mode only for formal findings-first review output. Fallback: if the surface cannot be determined confidently, ask for the runtime surface and verification command set. NEVER hardcode obsolete sibling code skills in dispatch prompts.\n13. **Design Standards Loading (surface-aware contract)** — When dispatching for design or UI work, instruct the dispatched session to: (1) load `sk-design` (the hub); (2) let the hub resolve a `workflowMode` through `mode-registry.json` (interface / foundations / motion / audit / md-generator / design-mcp-open-design); (3) load the selected mode packet, set the design register, and run that mode's design verification; (4) if the work feeds Open Design, carry the `design-mcp-open-design` pairing (a nested transport packet of the hub) — the transport never decides taste. Fallback: if the design mode cannot be determined confidently, ask for the surface and design intent. NEVER treat `mcp-figma` or `design-mcp-open-design` as the taste authority, or hardcode obsolete flat design skills in dispatch prompts.\n14. **Pass the design dispatch manifest to the dispatched session** — when dispatching design or UI work, inline a `DESIGN_DISPATCH_MANIFEST v1` block in the prompt (the child cannot resolve skill paths, so the manifest travels in the payload, not by reference): `skDesignLoaded` true, `register` resolved to `Brand` or `Product` (never `unknown`), registry-valid `workflowModes`, `dials`, `loadedFiles`, and `proofDemandBack`. If the manifest cannot be assembled — `sk-design` not loaded, register unresolved, or no registry-valid mode — ASK before launching the child rather than starting a silent design dispatch. The child returns the demanded proof; the parent reconciles it on the return path.\n15. **Destructive-scope-violation prevention (RM-8) for deep-loop dispatches** — The structured permissions-matrix gate (`permissions-gate.ts`; schema and design in `references/permissions-matrix.md`) is built and unit-tested but has ZERO production callers today — no `opencode run` dispatch path invokes it, so a loaded `--permissions-matrix <path>` config or recipe field is NOT currently enforced and does NOT bypass anything. Regardless of whether a matrix config is present, any non-interactive `opencode run` with `--dangerously-skip-permissions` against a populated worktree MUST apply the four-layer mitigation — it is the only active protection today: (L1) rendered prompt contains literal `BANNED OPERATIONS` and `ALLOWED WRITE PATHS`; (L2) `--dir` points at a fresh `git worktree`; (L3) main `git status` clean OR committed, recovery-baseline commit hash recorded; (L4) for multi-phase / phase-parent targets, prefer `cli-copilot` + `gpt-5.6-sol --reasoning-effort high` (verify `gpt-5.6-sol` availability on the Copilot surface — unverified, carried over from a gpt-5.5-era check; if absent, pick an available Copilot model, don't silently fall back to the risky default) over `deepseek-v4-pro`. Background: on 2026-05-04 an `opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro` dispatch under `/deep:review:auto` deleted 44 files across two phase folders because the only safeguard was prose and `--dangerously-skip-permissions` granted unrestricted FS write. Full incident + root cause + checklist: `references/destructive-scope-violations.md`.\n16. **Single-dispatch discipline (operator-gated, session-scoped)** — Default: launch ONE cli-* dispatch at a time across the cli-* family (cli-opencode, cli-claude-code). Wait for the dispatched agent's work to return, verify outputs exist, then SIGKILL only the dispatch THIS skill started: capture its PID at launch (`opencode run ... & OC_PID=$!`) and kill that captured PID directly plus its own orphan children (`kill -9 \"$OC_PID\" 2>/dev/null; pkill -9 -P \"$OC_PID\" 2>/dev/null`), then apply the same PID-scoped `gtimeout` / `positional_scoring_fallback:app` cleanup. (A backgrounded `opencode run &` is NOT a process-group leader unless launched with `setsid`/`set -m`, so a negative-PID group kill would target a nonexistent group and miss the process — kill the captured PID directly.) **Kill only the dispatch you started, by captured PID; never a blanket `pkill -9 -f \"opencode run\"` pattern — see Rule 5** (a blanket match kills operator-owned `opencode run` sessions too). Only launch the next dispatch (this skill OR a sibling) after the prior one is dead and RSS has dropped. **Within a deep-flow session** (deep-review / deep-research): the operator authorizes the whole multi-iteration session at start — iterations chain back-to-back with kill-between as the safety mechanism, NOT a per-iteration operator confirmation prompt. **Exception (cross-skill parallel)**: when the operator explicitly authorizes N parallel dispatches, run N concurrently — but still SIGKILL each by its own captured PID as its work returns.\n17. **Set `AI_SESSION_CHILD=1` in the dispatched session's env** when sessions may be launched through the per-session worktree wrapper (`.opencode/bin/worktree-session.sh`). A dispatched `opencode run` is an orchestrated sub-session, not a new top-level session, so it must SHARE the parent's worktree rather than allocate its own. The wrapper checks `AI_SESSION_CHILD` (plus a `git --git-common-dir` structural backstop) and exec's in place when set. Pattern: `AI_SESSION_CHILD=1 opencode run ... </dev/null`. Harmless when the wrapper is not in use. See `.opencode/bin/README.md` → \"Worktree session isolation\". Prepend `MK_SPEC_GATE_ENFORCE=0` next to it so a dispatched child never inherits an enforced spec-gate from the parent shell (belt-and-suspenders alongside the wrapper's own neutralization and the core's `AI_SESSION_CHILD` deny-narrowing): `MK_SPEC_GATE_ENFORCE=0 AI_SESSION_CHILD=1 opencode run ... </dev/null`.\n\n### ⛔ NEVER\n\n1. Invoke this skill from within OpenCode itself for a self-dispatch — refuse with the documented error message; use a sibling cli-* / fresh shell / parallel-session keywords.\n2. Pass `--share` without operator confirmation (CHK-033) — share URL exposes session contents.\n3. Trust dispatched session output blindly for security-sensitive code, send sensitive data (API keys, passwords, credentials) in prompts, or hammer the API with rapid sequential calls.\n4. Use `--pure` outside of plugin debugging (disabling plugins removes the entire point of cli-opencode dispatch).\n5. Nest `opencode run` inside a dispatched session's tool calls — use OpenCode's native Task tool for sub-agent dispatch.\n\n### ⚠️ ESCALATE IF\n\n1. OpenCode CLI is not installed and user has not acknowledged (provide `brew install opencode` or `curl -fsSL https://opencode.ai/install | bash`).\n2. Operator wants to publish a `--share` URL — get explicit confirmation per CHK-033.\n3. Binary version differs from the v1.3.17 baseline — run `opencode --version` and `opencode run --help`; surface drift and fall back or require approval.\n4. Smart router cannot map the prompt to one of the three use cases — surface the disambiguation checklist from UNKNOWN_FALLBACK.\n5. Self-invocation guard trips AND the prompt is ambiguous — surface the refusal with three remediation options (sibling cli-* / fresh shell / parallel-session keywords).\n\n### Memory Handback Protocol\n\nWhen the calling AI needs to preserve session context from an OpenCode CLI delegation, run the canonical 7-step procedure (extract `MEMORY_HANDBACK` section → build structured JSON → scrub secrets → invoke `generate-context.js` via `--stdin`/`--json`/temp-file → `memory_index_scan`). Full procedure and caveats: [`system-spec-kit/references/cli/memory-handback.md`](../../system-spec-kit/references/cli/memory-handback.md).\n\nFor read-only or hook-style recovery, use the daemon-backed CLI front doors instead of spawning OpenCode: `node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs <tool>`, `node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs <tool>`, or `node .opencode/bin/skill-advisor.cjs <tool>`. Prompt-time paths must probe warm sockets or pass `--warm-only`; exit `75` is retryable daemon/IPC unavailability, not a model failure.\n\nOpenCode-specific Memory Epilogue template: see [assets/prompt-templates.md](./assets/prompt-templates.md) §14.\n\nExample invocation:\n```bash\nprintf '%s' \"$JSON_PAYLOAD\" | node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js --stdin [spec-folder]\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. REFERENCES AND RELATED RESOURCES\n\n### Core References\n\n- [cli-reference.md](./references/cli-reference.md) - Full subcommand/flag reference, provider auth pre-flight, models, version drift\n- [integration-patterns.md](./references/integration-patterns.md) - 3 use cases, decision tree, silent stdin\n- [self-invocation-guard.md](./references/self-invocation-guard.md) - ADR-001 layered bash + python detection contract\n- [opencode-tools.md](./references/opencode-tools.md) - Unique value props vs sibling cli-* skills\n- [agent-delegation.md](./references/agent-delegation.md) - Agent routing matrix, leaf-agent constraints\n- [destructive-scope-violations.md](./references/destructive-scope-violations.md) - RM-8 incident, root cause, four-layer prevention playbook\n\n### Templates and Assets\n\n- [prompt-templates.md](./assets/prompt-templates.md) - Copy-paste templates per use case + agent + handback\n- [prompt-quality-card.md](./assets/prompt-quality-card.md) - Executor-specific model overrides; delegates framework/CLEAR check to canonical card\n\n### Shared (cli-* family)\n- [shared-smart-router.md](../../system-spec-kit/references/cli/shared-smart-router.md) - Helper-function bodies for the smart router.\n- [memory-handback.md](../../system-spec-kit/references/cli/memory-handback.md) - Canonical 7-step Memory Handback procedure.\n\n### External\n- [OpenCode GitHub](https://github.com/sst/opencode) - Official repository\n- [OpenCode Install](https://opencode.ai/install) - Standalone installer entry point\n- [OpenCode Documentation](https://opencode.ai/docs) - Official docs\n\n### Reference Loading Notes\n\n- Load only references needed for current intent.\n- Smart Routing (Section 2) is the single routing authority.\n- `cli-reference.md` and `prompt-quality-card.md` are ALWAYS loaded as baseline.\n- The router discovers reference, asset, and script docs dynamically — task-specific resources from `references/`, templates from `assets/`, and automation from `scripts/` when present.\n\n### Related Skills\n\n`cli-claude-code` and `cli-opencode` for sibling cross-AI dispatch; `system-spec-kit` for handback; `sk-code` plus the selected overlay for generated code; `system-deep-loop` for loop execution (its `research` and `review` modes); and `mcp-code-mode` for MCP-backed tools.\n\n---\n\n## 6. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n\n### Task Completion\n\n- OpenCode CLI invoked with the correct subcommand, flags, model, agent, variant, format, and dir.\n- Self-invocation guard checked before dispatch — refused when appropriate.\n- Use case (1 / 2 / 3) classified explicitly before invocation.\n- JSON event stream captured, parsed incrementally, validated, integrated.\n- No security vulnerabilities introduced from generated code.\n- `--share` URLs opt-in with operator confirmation per CHK-033.\n- Background dispatches in `while read` loops include `</dev/null` redirect.\n- Memory Handback extracted and saved through `generate-context.js` when applicable.\n\n### Skill Quality\n\n- All numbered sections present and correctly ordered.\n- Smart routing covers all intent signals with UNKNOWN_FALLBACK.\n- Reference files provide deep-dive content without duplication.\n- Self-invocation guard pseudocode reproduced in Section 2 mirrors ADR-001.\n\n---\n\n## 7. INTEGRATION POINTS\n\n### Framework Integration\n\nThis skill operates within the behavioral framework defined in [AGENTS.md](../../../../AGENTS.md).\n\nKey integrations:\n- **Gate 2**: Skill routing via the Skill Advisor Hook (or `skill_advisor.py` fallback)\n- **Tool Routing**: Per AGENTS.md Section 6 decision tree\n- **Memory**: Context preserved via Spec Kit Memory MCP (`generate-context.js`)\n- **Validation**: `bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh` for spec-folder workflows\n\n**Tool roles**: Bash dispatches the CLI; Read/Glob/Grep validate output and probe `~/.opencode/state/` for session locks.\n\nBase directory for this skill: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode\nRelative paths in this skill (e.g., scripts/, reference/) are relative to this base directory.\nNote: file list is sampled.\n\n<skill_files>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/assets/permissions-matrix.example-packet-local.json</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/assets/permissions-matrix.example-readonly.json</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/assets/permissions-matrix.schema.json</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/assets/prompt-quality-card.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/assets/prompt-templates.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/assets/permissions-matrix.example-repo-wide.json</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/scripts/lib/dispatch-audit.mjs</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/scripts/lib/README.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/scripts/lib/dispatch-audit.test.mjs</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/scripts/lib/dispatch-rule-checks.test.mjs</file>\n</skill_files>\n</skill_content>","metadata":{"name":"cli-opencode","dir":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode","truncated":false},"title":"Loaded skill: cli-opencode","time":{"start":1784624002083,"end":1784624002120}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a88b627636cb19a016a5f3381e118819181f434b5a243461f"}},"id":"prt_f83e1341d0015PP2fu3XjbfbuE","sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","messageID":"msg_f83e0dfed001PnGWcNgq9WoThY"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784624002204,"sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_2Gw7MbEdTxfVQG9RN87uJKnL","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/state/state-reducer-registry.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/state/state-reducer-registry.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Reducer And Registry Reference\n3: description: Reducer ownership, findings registry schema, validation, fault tolerance, and reconstruction rules.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research reducer registry\"\n6:   - \"research findings registry\"\n7:   - \"reducer ownership contract\"\n8:   - \"research registry fingerprint\"\n9:   - \"reducer fault tolerance\"\n10:   - \"research dashboard derivation\"\n11: importance_tier: normal\n12: contextType: implementation\n13: version: 1.14.0.2\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # Deep Research Reducer And Registry Reference\n17: \n18: The reducer turns append-only iteration state into synchronized strategy, registry, dashboard, and synthesis metadata. It is the source of truth for derived packet state.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n23: \n24: ### Purpose\n25: \n26: Define reducer ownership, findings registry shape, validation behavior, fault tolerance, file protection, dashboard derivation, and legacy aliases.\n27: \n28: ### When to Use\n29: \n30: Load this reference when rebuilding derived state, validating registry/dashboard outputs, or deciding whether a file is agent-owned or reducer-owned.\n31: \n32: ### Core Principle\n33: \n34: The reducer owns derived state. Manual edits to reducer-managed outputs are temporary and may be overwritten.\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ## 2. REDUCER CONTRACT\n39: \n40: The workflow reducer:\n41: \n42: - reads `deep-research-state.jsonl`, per-iteration deltas, strategy, and iteration markdown;\n43: - reads `inbox.jsonl` as immutable question input;\n44: - reads the prior registry as canonical question state when present;\n45: - validates required iteration artifacts;\n46: - updates machine-owned strategy sections;\n47: - regenerates the findings registry;\n48: - regenerates the dashboard;\n49: - records convergence and blocked-stop summaries.\n50: \n51: It must fail closed before writing derived files when JSONL corruption is detected in strict mode.\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: ## 3. FINDINGS REGISTRY\n56: \n57: The canonical registry stores open/resolved questions, findings, ruled-out directions, convergence state, and blocked-stop history.\n58: \n59: ```json\n60: {\n61:   \"openQuestions\": [],\n62:   \"resolvedQuestions\": [],\n63:   \"keyFindings\": [],\n64:   \"ruledOutDirections\": [],\n65:   \"coverageBySources\": {},\n66:   \"convergenceScore\": 0.42,\n67:   \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n68:   \"graphConvergenceScore\": null,\n69:   \"graphDecision\": null,\n70:   \"graphBlockers\": [],\n71:   \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n72: }\n73: ```\n74: \n75: Question ownership:\n76: \n77: - `inbox.jsonl` is append-only input for external questions.\n78: - The registry is the canonical owner of promoted question text, provenance, and operator decisions.\n79: - The strategy `key-questions` block is a generated projection and is rewritten from registry state on every reduce step.\n80: \n81: When an inbox row targets an existing registry question by promoted question id or inbox id but carries different text, the reducer records a conflict instead of overwriting markdown. Conflict records use `operatorDecision` values of `accepted`, `rejected`, `superseded`, or `needs_decision`; the default unresolved decision is `needs_decision`. The emitted `question_conflict` JSONL event includes both `inboxValue` and `registryValue`.\n82: \n83: The reducer writes the registry to `findings-registry.json`; this is the canonical live name. `deep-research-findings-registry.json` is a legacy read-fallback path only -- the reducer checks it when `findings-registry.json` is absent but never writes to it. New docs should reference `findings-registry.json` and mention the legacy name only when explaining read-compatibility.\n84: \n85: ---\n86: \n87: ## 4. VALIDATION RULES\n88: \n89: Blocking validation:\n90: \n91: - config, state log, and strategy exist before a resume;\n92: - every dispatched iteration produces a non-empty iteration markdown file;\n93: - every dispatched iteration appends a JSONL delta record with required fields;\n94: - JSONL records parse in strict mode;\n95: - reducer-owned outputs refresh after iteration evaluation;\n96: - convergence STOP candidates record gate evidence.\n97: \n98: Post-dispatch failure codes include:\n99: \n100: | Code | Meaning |\n101: |------|---------|\n102: | `iteration_file_missing` | Expected iteration markdown file was not created |\n103: | `iteration_file_empty` | Iteration markdown exists but is empty |\n104: | `jsonl_not_appended` | JSONL state did not receive the iteration record |\n105: | `jsonl_missing_fields` | Required JSONL fields are absent |\n106: | `jsonl_parse_error` | JSONL line is malformed |\n107: \n108: Three consecutive failures route to stuck recovery or escalation.\n109: \n110: ---\n111: \n112: ## 5. FAULT TOLERANCE\n113: \n114: Fault-tolerant reads may skip malformed JSONL lines only in lenient recovery mode. Strict mode stops before derived writes.\n115: \n116: Safe recovery order:\n117: \n118: 1. Preserve the corrupted state file.\n119: 2. Read valid JSONL records.\n120: 3. Reconstruct missing iteration summaries from `iterations/iteration-NNN.md`.\n121: 4. Append explicit reconstructed records.\n122: 5. Regenerate registry and dashboard.\n123: 6. Record the recovery in JSONL.\n124: \n125: Example reconstructed record:\n126: \n127: ```json\n128: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":3,\"status\":\"reconstructed\",\"focus\":\"extracted focus\",\"findingsCount\":0,\"newInfoRatio\":0.0}\n129: ```\n130: \n131: ---\n132: \n133: ## 6. FILE PROTECTION MAP\n134: \n135: The config may include:\n136: \n137: ```json\n138: {\n139:   \"fileProtection\": {\n140:     \"deep-research-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n141:     \"deep-research-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n142:     \"deep-research-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n143:     \"deep-research-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n144:     \"findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n145:     \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\",\n146:     \"research/research.md\": \"mutable\"\n147:   }\n148: }\n149: ```\n150: \n151: Protection is a workflow contract. It documents ownership and supports validation; it is not a substitute for command-level checks.\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: ## 7. DASHBOARD DERIVATION\n156: \n157: Dashboard values are derived from raw state:\n158: \n159: | Dashboard Field | Source |\n160: |-----------------|--------|\n161: | iteration count | JSONL iteration records |\n162: | current status | latest lifecycle or synthesis event |\n163: | convergence trend | `convergenceSignals` |\n164: | blocked stops | registry `blockedStopHistory` |\n165: | graph convergence | registry graph fields |\n166: | next focus | strategy |\n167: \n168: `synthesis_complete` events are authoritative for terminal status when present.\n169: \n170: ---\n171: \n172: ## 8. LEGACY ALIASES\n173: \n174: The workflow may dual-read older names during migration windows, but new writes use canonical `deep-research-*` artifacts. Migration reads should append a migration event that records `legacyPath`, `canonicalPath`, and timestamp.\n\n(End of file - total 174 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Reducer And Registry Reference\ndescription: Reducer ownership, findings registry schema, validation, fault tolerance, and reconstruction rules.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research reducer registry\"\n  - \"research findings registry\"\n  - \"reducer ownership contract\"\n  - \"research registry fingerprint\"\n  - \"reducer fault tolerance\"\n  - \"research dashboard derivation\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.2\n---\n\n# Deep Research Reducer And Registry Reference\n\nThe reducer turns append-only iteration state into synchronized strategy, registry, dashboard, and synthesis metadata. It is the source of truth for derived packet state.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/state/state-reducer-registry.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Reducer And Registry Reference\ndescription: Reducer ownership, findings registry schema, validation, fault tolerance, and reconstruction rules.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research reducer registry\"\n  - \"research findings registry\"\n  - \"reducer ownership contract\"\n  - \"research registry fingerprint\"\n  - \"reducer fault tolerance\"\n  - \"research dashboard derivation\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.2\n---\n\n# Deep Research Reducer And Registry Reference\n\nThe reducer turns append-only iteration state into synchronized strategy, registry, dashboard, and synthesis metadata. It is the source of truth for derived packet state.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nDefine reducer ownership, findings registry shape, validation behavior, fault tolerance, file protection, dashboard derivation, and legacy aliases.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this reference when rebuilding derived state, validating registry/dashboard outputs, or deciding whether a file is agent-owned or reducer-owned.\n\n### Core Principle\n\nThe reducer owns derived state. Manual edits to reducer-managed outputs are temporary and may be overwritten.\n\n---\n\n## 2. REDUCER CONTRACT\n\nThe workflow reducer:\n\n- reads `deep-research-state.jsonl`, per-iteration deltas, strategy, and iteration markdown;\n- reads `inbox.jsonl` as immutable question input;\n- reads the prior registry as canonical question state when present;\n- validates required iteration artifacts;\n- updates machine-owned strategy sections;\n- regenerates the findings registry;\n- regenerates the dashboard;\n- records convergence and blocked-stop summaries.\n\nIt must fail closed before writing derived files when JSONL corruption is detected in strict mode.\n\n---\n\n## 3. FINDINGS REGISTRY\n\nThe canonical registry stores open/resolved questions, findings, ruled-out directions, convergence state, and blocked-stop history.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"openQuestions\": [],\n  \"resolvedQuestions\": [],\n  \"keyFindings\": [],\n  \"ruledOutDirections\": [],\n  \"coverageBySources\": {},\n  \"convergenceScore\": 0.42,\n  \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n  \"graphConvergenceScore\": null,\n  \"graphDecision\": null,\n  \"graphBlockers\": [],\n  \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nQuestion ownership:\n\n- `inbox.jsonl` is append-only input for external questions.\n- The registry is the canonical owner of promoted question text, provenance, and operator decisions.\n- The strategy `key-questions` block is a generated projection and is rewritten from registry state on every reduce step.\n\nWhen an inbox row targets an existing registry question by promoted question id or inbox id but carries different text, the reducer records a conflict instead of overwriting markdown. Conflict records use `operatorDecision` values of `accepted`, `rejected`, `superseded`, or `needs_decision`; the default unresolved decision is `needs_decision`. The emitted `question_conflict` JSONL event includes both `inboxValue` and `registryValue`.\n\nThe reducer writes the registry to `findings-registry.json`; this is the canonical live name. `deep-research-findings-registry.json` is a legacy read-fallback path only -- the reducer checks it when `findings-registry.json` is absent but never writes to it. New docs should reference `findings-registry.json` and mention the legacy name only when explaining read-compatibility.\n\n---\n\n## 4. VALIDATION RULES\n\nBlocking validation:\n\n- config, state log, and strategy exist before a resume;\n- every dispatched iteration produces a non-empty iteration markdown file;\n- every dispatched iteration appends a JSONL delta record with required fields;\n- JSONL records parse in strict mode;\n- reducer-owned outputs refresh after iteration evaluation;\n- convergence STOP candidates record gate evidence.\n\nPost-dispatch failure codes include:\n\n| Code | Meaning |\n|------|---------|\n| `iteration_file_missing` | Expected iteration markdown file was not created |\n| `iteration_file_empty` | Iteration markdown exists but is empty |\n| `jsonl_not_appended` | JSONL state did not receive the iteration record |\n| `jsonl_missing_fields` | Required JSONL fields are absent |\n| `jsonl_parse_error` | JSONL line is malformed |\n\nThree consecutive failures route to stuck recovery or escalation.\n\n---\n\n## 5. FAULT TOLERANCE\n\nFault-tolerant reads may skip malformed JSONL lines only in lenient recovery mode. Strict mode stops before derived writes.\n\nSafe recovery order:\n\n1. Preserve the corrupted state file.\n2. Read valid JSONL records.\n3. Reconstruct missing iteration summaries from `iterations/iteration-NNN.md`.\n4. Append explicit reconstructed records.\n5. Regenerate registry and dashboard.\n6. Record the recovery in JSONL.\n\nExample reconstructed record:\n\n```json\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":3,\"status\":\"reconstructed\",\"focus\":\"extracted focus\",\"findingsCount\":0,\"newInfoRatio\":0.0}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. FILE PROTECTION MAP\n\nThe config may include:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"fileProtection\": {\n    \"deep-research-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n    \"deep-research-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n    \"deep-research-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n    \"deep-research-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\",\n    \"research/research.md\": \"mutable\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nProtection is a workflow contract. It documents ownership and supports validation; it is not a substitute for command-level checks.\n\n---\n\n## 7. DASHBOARD DERIVATION\n\nDashboard values are derived from raw state:\n\n| Dashboard Field | Source |\n|-----------------|--------|\n| iteration count | JSONL iteration records |\n| current status | latest lifecycle or synthesis event |\n| convergence trend | `convergenceSignals` |\n| blocked stops | registry `blockedStopHistory` |\n| graph convergence | registry graph fields |\n| next focus | strategy |\n\n`synthesis_complete` events are authoritative for terminal status when present.\n\n---\n\n## 8. LEGACY ALIASES\n\nThe workflow may dual-read older names during migration windows, but new writes use canonical `deep-research-*` artifacts. Migration reads should append a migration event that records `legacyPath`, `canonicalPath`, and timestamp.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":174,"totalLines":174,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/state/state-reducer-registry.md","time":{"start":1784624002064,"end":1784624002130}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a88b627636cb19a016a5f3381e108819194781fecc6840a27"}},"id":"prt_f83e1340a001ZoBgtXNQ9DEA9N","sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","messageID":"msg_f83e0dfed001PnGWcNgq9WoThY"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784624002204,"sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_DD3MnPtBKLs5GqdVbscd4nQX","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/state/state-jsonl.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/state/state-jsonl.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research JSONL State Reference\n3: description: Config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, and blocked-stop records for deep-research state logs.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research state jsonl\"\n6:   - \"research config record\"\n7:   - \"research iteration records\"\n8:   - \"research negative knowledge\"\n9:   - \"research graph events\"\n10:   - \"research event records\"\n11: importance_tier: normal\n12: contextType: implementation\n13: version: 1.14.0.3\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # Deep Research JSONL State Reference\n17: \n18: `deep-research-state.jsonl` is append-only. Each line is one JSON object. The first line is normally the config record, followed by iteration and event records.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n23: \n24: ### Purpose\n25: \n26: Define the append-only JSONL records used by deep-research config, iteration, lifecycle, graph, pause, stuck-recovery, and blocked-stop state.\n27: \n28: ### When to Use\n29: \n30: Load this reference when validating state logs, adding event records, reconstructing a packet, or mapping legacy stop labels to current values.\n31: \n32: ### Core Principle\n33: \n34: Raw JSONL is append-only evidence. Reducer-owned files derive from it, but they do not replace it.\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ## 2. CONFIG RECORD\n39: \n40: The config record captures the initialized loop contract.\n41: \n42: ```json\n43: {\n44:   \"type\": \"config\",\n45:   \"topic\": \"API response time optimization\",\n46:   \"maxIterations\": 10,\n47:   \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n48:   \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n49:   \"specFolder\": \"028-auto-deep-research\",\n50:   \"createdAt\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n51: }\n52: ```\n53: \n54: The full config file also stores executor, lineage, reducer, capability matrix, pause sentinel, archive, and file-protection settings.\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: ## 3. ITERATION RECORDS\n59: \n60: ```json\n61: {\n62:   \"type\": \"iteration\",\n63:   \"run\": 1,\n64:   \"status\": \"complete\",\n65:   \"focus\": \"Initial broad survey\",\n66:   \"findingsCount\": 5,\n67:   \"newInfoRatio\": 1.0,\n68:   \"noveltyJustification\": \"First pass; all findings are new to this packet\",\n69:   \"keyQuestions\": [\"What causes latency?\"],\n70:   \"answeredQuestions\": [\"What causes latency?\"],\n71:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:05:00Z\",\n72:   \"durationMs\": 45000\n73: }\n74: ```\n75: \n76: | Field | Required | Notes |\n77: |-------|----------|-------|\n78: | `type` | Yes | `iteration` |\n79: | `run` | Yes | 1-indexed iteration number |\n80: | `status` | Yes | See status values below |\n81: | `focus` | Yes | Single focus investigated |\n82: | `findingsCount` | Yes | Number of findings reported |\n83: | `newInfoRatio` | Yes | Novelty score used by convergence |\n84: | `noveltyJustification` | Recommended | One-sentence explanation of the ratio |\n85: | `keyQuestions` | Recommended | Questions considered during this iteration |\n86: | `answeredQuestions` | Recommended | Questions answered by evidence |\n87: | `ruledOut` | Optional | Negative knowledge entries |\n88: | `graphEvents` | Optional | Coverage graph mutations |\n89: \n90: Status values:\n91: \n92: | Status | Meaning |\n93: |--------|---------|\n94: | `complete` | Normal evidence-gathering iteration |\n95: | `timeout` | Time/tool budget exceeded |\n96: | `error` | Tool, parse, or unexpected failure |\n97: | `stuck` | No new information and no clear next direction |\n98: | `insight` | Low ratio but important conceptual breakthrough |\n99: | `thought` | Analytical-only iteration; excluded from stuck and signal math |\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ## 4. CONVERGENCE SIGNAL FIELDS\n104: \n105: When the composite algorithm runs, the iteration may include signal values:\n106: \n107: ```json\n108: {\n109:   \"type\": \"iteration\",\n110:   \"run\": 5,\n111:   \"convergenceSignals\": {\n112:     \"rollingAvg\": 0.12,\n113:     \"madScore\": 0.08,\n114:     \"entropyCoverage\": 0.71,\n115:     \"compositeStop\": 0.42\n116:   }\n117: }\n118: ```\n119: \n120: Signal rules live in `../convergence/convergence-signals.md`.\n121: \n122: ---\n123: \n124: ## 5. NEGATIVE KNOWLEDGE\n125: \n126: Use `ruledOut` to preserve eliminated approaches.\n127: \n128: ```json\n129: {\n130:   \"type\": \"iteration\",\n131:   \"run\": 3,\n132:   \"status\": \"complete\",\n133:   \"ruledOut\": [\n134:     {\n135:       \"approach\": \"HTTP/3 multiplexing\",\n136:       \"reason\": \"No server-side support in target environment\",\n137:       \"evidence\": \"file:docs/protocols.md:42\"\n138:     }\n139:   ]\n140: }\n141: ```\n142: \n143: Ruled-out directions should also appear in strategy and synthesis outputs.\n144: \n145: ---\n146: \n147: ## 6. GRAPH EVENTS\n148: \n149: `graphEvents` records coverage graph mutations from an iteration.\n150: \n151: ```json\n152: {\n153:   \"type\": \"iteration\",\n154:   \"run\": 4,\n155:   \"graphEvents\": [\n156:     {\"type\": \"question\", \"id\": \"q-reconnect\", \"label\": \"How should reconnect work?\"},\n157:     {\"type\": \"finding\", \"id\": \"f-backoff\", \"label\": \"Exponential backoff is required\"},\n158:     {\"type\": \"edge\", \"from\": \"f-backoff\", \"to\": \"q-reconnect\", \"relation\": \"ANSWERS\"}\n159:   ]\n160: }\n161: ```\n162: \n163: Valid node types are `question`, `finding`, `claim`, and `source`; `edge` records connect nodes. IDs must be unique within a single `(specFolder, loopType, sessionId)` namespace. Reusing the same logical ID across independent sessions is allowed because the coverage graph uses a composite key.\n164: \n165: ---\n166: \n167: ## 7. EVENT RECORDS\n168: \n169: Lifecycle event:\n170: \n171: ```json\n172: {\n173:   \"type\": \"event\",\n174:   \"event\": \"resumed\",\n175:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n176:   \"sessionId\": \"dr-2026-05-24T00-00-00Z\",\n177:   \"parentSessionId\": \"dr-2026-05-24T00-00-00Z\",\n178:   \"lineageMode\": \"resume\",\n179:   \"continuedFromRun\": 4,\n180:   \"generation\": 1,\n181:   \"archivedPath\": null,\n182:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n183: }\n184: ```\n185: \n186: Blocked stop event:\n187: \n188: ```json\n189: {\n190:   \"type\": \"event\",\n191:   \"event\": \"blocked_stop\",\n192:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n193:   \"run\": 7,\n194:   \"stopReason\": \"blockedStop\",\n195:   \"blockedBy\": [\"keyQuestionCoverage\", \"sourceDiversity\"],\n196:   \"recoveryStrategy\": \"focus_pivot\",\n197:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n198: }\n199: ```\n200: \n201: Pause event:\n202: \n203: ```json\n204: {\n205:   \"type\": \"event\",\n206:   \"event\": \"userPaused\",\n207:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n208:   \"run\": 7,\n209:   \"stopReason\": \"userPaused\",\n210:   \"sentinelPath\": \"research/.deep-research-pause\",\n211:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n212: }\n213: ```\n214: \n215: Stuck recovery event:\n216: \n217: ```json\n218: {\n219:   \"type\": \"event\",\n220:   \"event\": \"stuckRecovery\",\n221:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n222:   \"run\": 7,\n223:   \"stopReason\": \"stuckRecovery\",\n224:   \"fromFocus\": \"Connection pooling\",\n225:   \"toFocus\": \"Transport alternatives\",\n226:   \"strategy\": \"try_opposites\",\n227:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n228: }\n229: ```\n230: \n231: Idea observation event:\n232: \n233: ```json\n234: {\n235:   \"type\": \"event\",\n236:   \"event\": \"idea_observed\",\n237:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n238:   \"run\": 7,\n239:   \"ideaId\": \"idea-cache-stampede\",\n240:   \"idea\": \"Investigate cache stampede mitigation as a follow-up focus\",\n241:   \"category\": \"ideas\",\n242:   \"source\": \"iteration-007.md\",\n243:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n244: }\n245: ```\n246: \n247: Leaf agents may append `idea_observed` for promising tangents. They must not append `idea_promoted`; promotion is reducer-owned.\n248: \n249: Idea promotion event:\n250: \n251: ```json\n252: {\n253:   \"type\": \"event\",\n254:   \"event\": \"idea_promoted\",\n255:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n256:   \"run\": 8,\n257:   \"ideaId\": \"idea-cache-stampede\",\n258:   \"idea\": \"Investigate cache stampede mitigation as a follow-up focus\",\n259:   \"category\": \"ideas\",\n260:   \"observationCount\": 2,\n261:   \"minIdeaObservations\": 2,\n262:   \"firstObservedRun\": 6,\n263:   \"lastObservedRun\": 7,\n264:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:02:00Z\"\n265: }\n266: ```\n267: \n268: The reducer emits `idea_promoted` once per idea after replay shows `observationCount >= minIdeaObservations`. `minIdeaObservations` defaults to `2` and is clamped to the inclusive range `1..10`.\n269: \n270: Rejected idea event:\n271: \n272: ```json\n273: {\n274:   \"type\": \"event\",\n275:   \"event\": \"idea_rejected\",\n276:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n277:   \"run\": 7,\n278:   \"ideaId\": \"idea-cache-stampede\",\n279:   \"idea\": \"Investigate cache stampede mitigation as a follow-up focus\",\n280:   \"category\": \"ideas\",\n281:   \"reason\": \"Already rejected by environment evidence\",\n282:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n283: }\n284: ```\n285: \n286: `idea_rejected` durably suppresses the matching promoted idea and also enters the reducer-owned rejected-pattern cache. Use `category: \"general\"` only when the rejection should suppress matching text across next-focus, recovery, and ideas candidates.\n287: \n288: Rejected idea removal event:\n289: \n290: ```json\n291: {\n292:   \"type\": \"event\",\n293:   \"event\": \"ideaRejectedRemoved\",\n294:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n295:   \"pattern\": \"Retry HTTP/3 as the primary latency fix\",\n296:   \"category\": \"next-focus\",\n297:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n298: }\n299: ```\n300: \n301: Rejected idea reset event:\n302: \n303: ```json\n304: {\n305:   \"type\": \"event\",\n306:   \"event\": \"ideaRejectedReset\",\n307:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n308:   \"reason\": \"Operator wants previously rejected ideas eligible again\",\n309:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n310: }\n311: ```\n312: \n313: The reducer derives a bounded active rejected-pattern cache from these events. `idea_rejected` adds or refreshes one pattern, `ideaRejectedRemoved` removes a single matching pattern or id, and `ideaRejectedReset` clears the active cache. Legacy `ideaRejected`, `ideaRejectedRemoved`, and `ideaRejectedReset` rows remain replayable for existing state logs. The active cache is capped at 100 entries; when more are added, the oldest active entry is evicted and the reducer emits a warning.\n314: \n315: Candidate checks compare normalized exact text first, then apply fuzzy matching only when the candidate category is compatible with the rejected category. Omit `category` for a general rejection that can suppress candidates across next-focus, recovery, or ideas surfaces.\n316: \n317: Graph convergence event shape lives in `../convergence/convergence-graph.md`.\n318: \n319: ---\n320: \n321: ## 8. NORMALIZATION\n322: \n323: Emission-time normalization maps legacy labels into canonical `stopReason` values before persistence. The mapping lives in `../convergence/convergence.md`.\n324: \n325: Malformed lines are handled by the reducer according to its strict/lenient mode. Fault tolerance and reconstruction are documented in `state-reducer-registry.md`.\n\n(End of file - total 325 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research JSONL State Reference\ndescription: Config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, and blocked-stop records for deep-research state logs.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research state jsonl\"\n  - \"research config record\"\n  - \"research iteration records\"\n  - \"research negative knowledge\"\n  - \"research graph events\"\n  - \"research event records\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.3\n---\n\n# Deep Research JSONL State Reference\n\n`deep-research-state.jsonl` is append-only. Each line is one JSON object. The first line is normally the config record, followed by iteration and event records.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/state/state-jsonl.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research JSONL State Reference\ndescription: Config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, and blocked-stop records for deep-research state logs.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research state jsonl\"\n  - \"research config record\"\n  - \"research iteration records\"\n  - \"research negative knowledge\"\n  - \"research graph events\"\n  - \"research event records\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.3\n---\n\n# Deep Research JSONL State Reference\n\n`deep-research-state.jsonl` is append-only. Each line is one JSON object. The first line is normally the config record, followed by iteration and event records.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nDefine the append-only JSONL records used by deep-research config, iteration, lifecycle, graph, pause, stuck-recovery, and blocked-stop state.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this reference when validating state logs, adding event records, reconstructing a packet, or mapping legacy stop labels to current values.\n\n### Core Principle\n\nRaw JSONL is append-only evidence. Reducer-owned files derive from it, but they do not replace it.\n\n---\n\n## 2. CONFIG RECORD\n\nThe config record captures the initialized loop contract.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"config\",\n  \"topic\": \"API response time optimization\",\n  \"maxIterations\": 10,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n  \"specFolder\": \"028-auto-deep-research\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nThe full config file also stores executor, lineage, reducer, capability matrix, pause sentinel, archive, and file-protection settings.\n\n---\n\n## 3. ITERATION RECORDS\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"iteration\",\n  \"run\": 1,\n  \"status\": \"complete\",\n  \"focus\": \"Initial broad survey\",\n  \"findingsCount\": 5,\n  \"newInfoRatio\": 1.0,\n  \"noveltyJustification\": \"First pass; all findings are new to this packet\",\n  \"keyQuestions\": [\"What causes latency?\"],\n  \"answeredQuestions\": [\"What causes latency?\"],\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:05:00Z\",\n  \"durationMs\": 45000\n}\n```\n\n| Field | Required | Notes |\n|-------|----------|-------|\n| `type` | Yes | `iteration` |\n| `run` | Yes | 1-indexed iteration number |\n| `status` | Yes | See status values below |\n| `focus` | Yes | Single focus investigated |\n| `findingsCount` | Yes | Number of findings reported |\n| `newInfoRatio` | Yes | Novelty score used by convergence |\n| `noveltyJustification` | Recommended | One-sentence explanation of the ratio |\n| `keyQuestions` | Recommended | Questions considered during this iteration |\n| `answeredQuestions` | Recommended | Questions answered by evidence |\n| `ruledOut` | Optional | Negative knowledge entries |\n| `graphEvents` | Optional | Coverage graph mutations |\n\nStatus values:\n\n| Status | Meaning |\n|--------|---------|\n| `complete` | Normal evidence-gathering iteration |\n| `timeout` | Time/tool budget exceeded |\n| `error` | Tool, parse, or unexpected failure |\n| `stuck` | No new information and no clear next direction |\n| `insight` | Low ratio but important conceptual breakthrough |\n| `thought` | Analytical-only iteration; excluded from stuck and signal math |\n\n---\n\n## 4. CONVERGENCE SIGNAL FIELDS\n\nWhen the composite algorithm runs, the iteration may include signal values:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"iteration\",\n  \"run\": 5,\n  \"convergenceSignals\": {\n    \"rollingAvg\": 0.12,\n    \"madScore\": 0.08,\n    \"entropyCoverage\": 0.71,\n    \"compositeStop\": 0.42\n  }\n}\n```\n\nSignal rules live in `../convergence/convergence-signals.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. NEGATIVE KNOWLEDGE\n\nUse `ruledOut` to preserve eliminated approaches.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"iteration\",\n  \"run\": 3,\n  \"status\": \"complete\",\n  \"ruledOut\": [\n    {\n      \"approach\": \"HTTP/3 multiplexing\",\n      \"reason\": \"No server-side support in target environment\",\n      \"evidence\": \"file:docs/protocols.md:42\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nRuled-out directions should also appear in strategy and synthesis outputs.\n\n---\n\n## 6. GRAPH EVENTS\n\n`graphEvents` records coverage graph mutations from an iteration.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"iteration\",\n  \"run\": 4,\n  \"graphEvents\": [\n    {\"type\": \"question\", \"id\": \"q-reconnect\", \"label\": \"How should reconnect work?\"},\n    {\"type\": \"finding\", \"id\": \"f-backoff\", \"label\": \"Exponential backoff is required\"},\n    {\"type\": \"edge\", \"from\": \"f-backoff\", \"to\": \"q-reconnect\", \"relation\": \"ANSWERS\"}\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nValid node types are `question`, `finding`, `claim`, and `source`; `edge` records connect nodes. IDs must be unique within a single `(specFolder, loopType, sessionId)` namespace. Reusing the same logical ID across independent sessions is allowed because the coverage graph uses a composite key.\n\n---\n\n## 7. EVENT RECORDS\n\nLifecycle event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"resumed\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"dr-2026-05-24T00-00-00Z\",\n  \"parentSessionId\": \"dr-2026-05-24T00-00-00Z\",\n  \"lineageMode\": \"resume\",\n  \"continuedFromRun\": 4,\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"archivedPath\": null,\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nBlocked stop event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"blocked_stop\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 7,\n  \"stopReason\": \"blockedStop\",\n  \"blockedBy\": [\"keyQuestionCoverage\", \"sourceDiversity\"],\n  \"recoveryStrategy\": \"focus_pivot\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nPause event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"userPaused\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 7,\n  \"stopReason\": \"userPaused\",\n  \"sentinelPath\": \"research/.deep-research-pause\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nStuck recovery event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"stuckRecovery\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 7,\n  \"stopReason\": \"stuckRecovery\",\n  \"fromFocus\": \"Connection pooling\",\n  \"toFocus\": \"Transport alternatives\",\n  \"strategy\": \"try_opposites\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nIdea observation event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"idea_observed\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 7,\n  \"ideaId\": \"idea-cache-stampede\",\n  \"idea\": \"Investigate cache stampede mitigation as a follow-up focus\",\n  \"category\": \"ideas\",\n  \"source\": \"iteration-007.md\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nLeaf agents may append `idea_observed` for promising tangents. They must not append `idea_promoted`; promotion is reducer-owned.\n\nIdea promotion event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"idea_promoted\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 8,\n  \"ideaId\": \"idea-cache-stampede\",\n  \"idea\": \"Investigate cache stampede mitigation as a follow-up focus\",\n  \"category\": \"ideas\",\n  \"observationCount\": 2,\n  \"minIdeaObservations\": 2,\n  \"firstObservedRun\": 6,\n  \"lastObservedRun\": 7,\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:02:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nThe reducer emits `idea_promoted` once per idea after replay shows `observationCount >= minIdeaObservations`. `minIdeaObservations` defaults to `2` and is clamped to the inclusive range `1..10`.\n\nRejected idea event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"idea_rejected\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 7,\n  \"ideaId\": \"idea-cache-stampede\",\n  \"idea\": \"Investigate cache stampede mitigation as a follow-up focus\",\n  \"category\": \"ideas\",\n  \"reason\": \"Already rejected by environment evidence\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\n`idea_rejected` durably suppresses the matching promoted idea and also enters the reducer-owned rejected-pattern cache. Use `category: \"general\"` only when the rejection should suppress matching text across next-focus, recovery, and ideas candidates.\n\nRejected idea removal event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"ideaRejectedRemoved\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"pattern\": \"Retry HTTP/3 as the primary latency fix\",\n  \"category\": \"next-focus\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nRejected idea reset event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"ideaRejectedReset\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"reason\": \"Operator wants previously rejected ideas eligible again\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nThe reducer derives a bounded active rejected-pattern cache from these events. `idea_rejected` adds or refreshes one pattern, `ideaRejectedRemoved` removes a single matching pattern or id, and `ideaRejectedReset` clears the active cache. Legacy `ideaRejected`, `ideaRejectedRemoved`, and `ideaRejectedReset` rows remain replayable for existing state logs. The active cache is capped at 100 entries; when more are added, the oldest active entry is evicted and the reducer emits a warning.\n\nCandidate checks compare normalized exact text first, then apply fuzzy matching only when the candidate category is compatible with the rejected category. Omit `category` for a general rejection that can suppress candidates across next-focus, recovery, or ideas surfaces.\n\nGraph convergence event shape lives in `../convergence/convergence-graph.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 8. NORMALIZATION\n\nEmission-time normalization maps legacy labels into canonical `stopReason` values before persistence. The mapping lives in `../convergence/convergence.md`.\n\nMalformed lines are handled by the reducer according to its strict/lenient mode. Fault tolerance and reconstruction are documented in `state-reducer-registry.md`.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":325,"totalLines":325,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/state/state-jsonl.md","time":{"start":1784624002048,"end":1784624002183}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a88b627636cb19a016a5f3381e0f481919381db81077ec2cb"}},"id":"prt_f83e133fc001CZILjkoZHr0OeN","sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","messageID":"msg_f83e0dfed001PnGWcNgq9WoThY"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784624002204,"sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_h6cioDHTMYxN76KipkN29ybI","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/state/state-outputs.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/state/state-outputs.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Output Files Reference\n3: description: Markdown output structures for strategy, iterations, dashboard, synthesis, and resource-map artifacts.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research output files\"\n6:   - \"research iteration files\"\n7:   - \"research synthesis document\"\n8:   - \"research resource map\"\n9:   - \"research strategy file\"\n10:   - \"spec anchoring output\"\n11: importance_tier: normal\n12: contextType: implementation\n13: version: 1.14.0.3\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # Deep Research Output Files Reference\n17: \n18: This reference covers human-readable packet outputs. JSONL records live in `state-jsonl.md`; reducer ownership lives in `state-reducer-registry.md`.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n23: \n24: ### Purpose\n25: \n26: Define the human-readable deep-research packet outputs: strategy, iteration markdown, synthesis, dashboard, resource map, and bounded spec anchoring.\n27: \n28: ### When to Use\n29: \n30: Load this reference when writing or validating markdown outputs rather than JSONL records.\n31: \n32: ### Core Principle\n33: \n34: Human-readable outputs must stay synchronized with raw state and respect reducer ownership.\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ## 2. STRATEGY FILE\n39: \n40: `deep-research-strategy.md` is the persistent research plan. The reducer owns machine-managed sections.\n41: \n42: Required sections:\n43: \n44: - Research Topic\n45: - Known Context\n46: - Key Questions\n47: - Answered Questions\n48: - What Worked\n49: - What Failed\n50: - Exhausted Approaches\n51: - Ruled-Out Directions\n52: - Next Focus\n53: \n54: Update protocol:\n55: \n56: - read strategy before each iteration;\n57: - choose one focus from `Next Focus`;\n58: - append what worked, failed, and was ruled out;\n59: - update answered/open questions through reducer-owned sections;\n60: - when a STOP candidate is blocked, override `Next Focus` with the blocker recovery focus.\n61: \n62: ---\n63: \n64: ## 3. ITERATION FILES\n65: \n66: Iteration files are write-once markdown narratives.\n67: \n68: ```text\n69: research/iterations/iteration-001.md\n70: research/iterations/iteration-002.md\n71: research/iterations/iteration-003.md\n72: ```\n73: \n74: Required shape:\n75: \n76: | Markdown Element | Required Content |\n77: |------------------|------------------|\n78: | H1 title | `Iteration N: Focus Area` |\n79: | `Focus` section | What this iteration investigated |\n80: | `Findings` section | Evidence-backed findings with source citations |\n81: | `Sources Consulted` section | Files, URLs, memory hits, or commands used |\n82: | `Assessment` section | `newInfoRatio`, novelty justification, and confidence notes |\n83: | `Reflection` section | What worked, failed, or was ruled out |\n84: | `Recommended Next Focus` section | One concrete next focus |\n85: \n86: Every finding must cite a source such as `[SOURCE: file:path:line]` or `[SOURCE: https://example.test]`.\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: ## 4. RESEARCH SYNTHESIS\n91: \n92: `research.md` is the workflow-owned synthesis output at `{artifact_dir}/research.md`.\n93: \n94: Rules:\n95: \n96: - progressive synthesis may update the file during the loop;\n97: - final synthesis consolidates duplicate findings and unresolved gaps;\n98: - prior findings are not silently overwritten;\n99: - generated or machine-owned sections must be marked explicitly when the workflow uses them;\n100: - when `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References.\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ## 5. DASHBOARD\n105: \n106: `deep-research-dashboard.md` is auto-generated from JSONL, strategy, and registry state.\n107: \n108: Expected sections:\n109: \n110: | Section | Source |\n111: |---------|--------|\n112: | Iteration Table | JSONL iteration records |\n113: | Question Status | Strategy + registry |\n114: | Convergence Trend | `convergenceSignals` + reducer |\n115: | Dead Ends | JSONL `ruledOut` + strategy |\n116: | Blocked Stops | Registry blocked-stop history |\n117: | Graph Convergence | Graph convergence registry fields |\n118: | Next Focus | Strategy |\n119: \n120: Generation rules:\n121: \n122: - regenerate after each iteration evaluation;\n123: - compute derived values from raw state;\n124: - overwrite the full dashboard rather than appending;\n125: - if state is missing, write a minimal \"No iteration data available\" dashboard;\n126: - agent writes are discarded on next refresh.\n127: \n128: ---\n129: \n130: ## 6. RESOURCE MAP\n131: \n132: When `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init:\n133: \n134: - persist `resource_map_present: true` in config;\n135: - summarize section counts and themes into strategy `Known Context`;\n136: - treat listed files as known inventory, not net-new discoveries;\n137: - cite the map in final synthesis references;\n138: - emit `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from converged deltas unless disabled.\n139: \n140: When absent:\n141: \n142: - persist `resource_map_present: false`;\n143: - write `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate` into `Known Context`;\n144: - continue normally.\n145: \n146: ---\n147: \n148: ## 7. SPEC ANCHORING OUTPUT\n149: \n150: `references/protocol/spec-check-protocol.md` defines bounded `spec.md` writes:\n151: \n152: - acquire `research/.deep-research.lock`;\n153: - classify `folder_state`;\n154: - seed or append bounded context during init when allowed;\n155: - replace exactly one generated findings fence during synthesis.\n156: \n157: This output path is protocol-owned, not iteration-agent owned.\n\n(End of file - total 157 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Output Files Reference\ndescription: Markdown output structures for strategy, iterations, dashboard, synthesis, and resource-map artifacts.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research output files\"\n  - \"research iteration files\"\n  - \"research synthesis document\"\n  - \"research resource map\"\n  - \"research strategy file\"\n  - \"spec anchoring output\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.3\n---\n\n# Deep Research Output Files Reference\n\nThis reference covers human-readable packet outputs. JSONL records live in `state-jsonl.md`; reducer ownership lives in `state-reducer-registry.md`.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/state/state-outputs.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Output Files Reference\ndescription: Markdown output structures for strategy, iterations, dashboard, synthesis, and resource-map artifacts.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research output files\"\n  - \"research iteration files\"\n  - \"research synthesis document\"\n  - \"research resource map\"\n  - \"research strategy file\"\n  - \"spec anchoring output\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.3\n---\n\n# Deep Research Output Files Reference\n\nThis reference covers human-readable packet outputs. JSONL records live in `state-jsonl.md`; reducer ownership lives in `state-reducer-registry.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nDefine the human-readable deep-research packet outputs: strategy, iteration markdown, synthesis, dashboard, resource map, and bounded spec anchoring.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this reference when writing or validating markdown outputs rather than JSONL records.\n\n### Core Principle\n\nHuman-readable outputs must stay synchronized with raw state and respect reducer ownership.\n\n---\n\n## 2. STRATEGY FILE\n\n`deep-research-strategy.md` is the persistent research plan. The reducer owns machine-managed sections.\n\nRequired sections:\n\n- Research Topic\n- Known Context\n- Key Questions\n- Answered Questions\n- What Worked\n- What Failed\n- Exhausted Approaches\n- Ruled-Out Directions\n- Next Focus\n\nUpdate protocol:\n\n- read strategy before each iteration;\n- choose one focus from `Next Focus`;\n- append what worked, failed, and was ruled out;\n- update answered/open questions through reducer-owned sections;\n- when a STOP candidate is blocked, override `Next Focus` with the blocker recovery focus.\n\n---\n\n## 3. ITERATION FILES\n\nIteration files are write-once markdown narratives.\n\n```text\nresearch/iterations/iteration-001.md\nresearch/iterations/iteration-002.md\nresearch/iterations/iteration-003.md\n```\n\nRequired shape:\n\n| Markdown Element | Required Content |\n|------------------|------------------|\n| H1 title | `Iteration N: Focus Area` |\n| `Focus` section | What this iteration investigated |\n| `Findings` section | Evidence-backed findings with source citations |\n| `Sources Consulted` section | Files, URLs, memory hits, or commands used |\n| `Assessment` section | `newInfoRatio`, novelty justification, and confidence notes |\n| `Reflection` section | What worked, failed, or was ruled out |\n| `Recommended Next Focus` section | One concrete next focus |\n\nEvery finding must cite a source such as `[SOURCE: file:path:line]` or `[SOURCE: https://example.test]`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. RESEARCH SYNTHESIS\n\n`research.md` is the workflow-owned synthesis output at `{artifact_dir}/research.md`.\n\nRules:\n\n- progressive synthesis may update the file during the loop;\n- final synthesis consolidates duplicate findings and unresolved gaps;\n- prior findings are not silently overwritten;\n- generated or machine-owned sections must be marked explicitly when the workflow uses them;\n- when `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References.\n\n---\n\n## 5. DASHBOARD\n\n`deep-research-dashboard.md` is auto-generated from JSONL, strategy, and registry state.\n\nExpected sections:\n\n| Section | Source |\n|---------|--------|\n| Iteration Table | JSONL iteration records |\n| Question Status | Strategy + registry |\n| Convergence Trend | `convergenceSignals` + reducer |\n| Dead Ends | JSONL `ruledOut` + strategy |\n| Blocked Stops | Registry blocked-stop history |\n| Graph Convergence | Graph convergence registry fields |\n| Next Focus | Strategy |\n\nGeneration rules:\n\n- regenerate after each iteration evaluation;\n- compute derived values from raw state;\n- overwrite the full dashboard rather than appending;\n- if state is missing, write a minimal \"No iteration data available\" dashboard;\n- agent writes are discarded on next refresh.\n\n---\n\n## 6. RESOURCE MAP\n\nWhen `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init:\n\n- persist `resource_map_present: true` in config;\n- summarize section counts and themes into strategy `Known Context`;\n- treat listed files as known inventory, not net-new discoveries;\n- cite the map in final synthesis references;\n- emit `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from converged deltas unless disabled.\n\nWhen absent:\n\n- persist `resource_map_present: false`;\n- write `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate` into `Known Context`;\n- continue normally.\n\n---\n\n## 7. SPEC ANCHORING OUTPUT\n\n`references/protocol/spec-check-protocol.md` defines bounded `spec.md` writes:\n\n- acquire `research/.deep-research.lock`;\n- classify `folder_state`;\n- seed or append bounded context during init when allowed;\n- replace exactly one generated findings fence during synthesis.\n\nThis output path is protocol-owned, not iteration-agent owned.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":157,"totalLines":157,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/state/state-outputs.md","time":{"start":1784624002057,"end":1784624002189}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a88b627636cb19a016a5f3381e1008191b3ac503b5d8801eb"}},"id":"prt_f83e13402001UzbEpX5cQB96ix","sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","messageID":"msg_f83e0dfed001PnGWcNgq9WoThY"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784624002205,"sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_5JG7EyZNqgP1FP4JDsVNwwQ9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-presentation.txt"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-presentation.txt</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Start Research Loop Presentation Contract\n2: \n3: Presentation source of truth for `/deep:research`. The command router owns only mode selection, setup binding, and asset loading. Workflow YAML owns execution. This file owns visible prompts, dashboard/checkpoint layout, final result displays, examples, and next-step wording.\n4: \n5: ## 1. Startup Presentation\n6: \n7: This workflow gathers all setup inputs in one prompt. Confirm mode still includes multiple approval gates after setup; only the setup round-trip is consolidated here.\n8: \n9: For `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt MUST be the first visible response. No implementation or file-modifying tool calls before asking. Lightweight read-only discovery to suggest a spec folder or load prior context is allowed, then ask ALL questions immediately and wait.\n10: \n11: For `:auto`, do not emit the consolidated prompt by default. Resolve setup with the three-tier branch below, then load the auto YAML only after all required values are bound.\n12: \n13: ### `:auto` Setup Resolution\n14: \n15: Setup contract: see `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/auto-mode-contract.md`.\n16: \n17: Under `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS` (from the `:auto` suffix), follow the three-tier flow:\n18: \n19: 1. **Tier 1 — Resolve confidently** (contract §1): parse `$ARGUMENTS` flags + `PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:` block (§2) + the Default Resolution Table below (§3). When every required field is resolved, persist to `{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json` (shape: `researchTopic`, `specFolder`, `maxIterations`, `convergenceThreshold`, `antiConvergence.convergenceMode`, reserved `antiConvergence.divergent: {}`, `executionMode: \"auto\"`, `resource_map.emit`, `config.executor.*`), bind runtime YAML placeholders, set `STATUS: PASSED`, load `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml`. End §0.\n20: \n21: 2. **Tier 2 — Targeted ask** (contract §1): when 1-2 required fields are genuinely ambiguous AND no default exists, emit ONE narrow question per ambiguous field. Command-specific Tier-2-eligible fields (per the Default Resolution Table below): `spec_folder`. **Ordering rule**: none needed. Missing `research_topic` is absence, not ambiguity — go to Tier 3.\n22: \n23: 3. **Tier 3 — Fail fast** (contract §4): emit the named-missing-inputs error format with `/deep:research:auto` as the command name. Exit non-zero. Do not load YAML.\n24: \n25: `:confirm` path stays unchanged — see the consolidated setup prompt section below.\n26: \n27: ### PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS Schema (for `:auto` non-interactive dispatch)\n28: \n29: The dispatched prompt body may contain one structured marker block. Parse it before applying defaults. Grammar: see `auto-mode-contract.md` §2.\n30: \n31: ```yaml\n32: PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n33:   research_topic: WebSocket reconnection strategies  # string\n34:   spec_folder: <spec-folder>  # existing | new | update-related | phase-folder | explicit path\n35:   execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS  # from :auto suffix\n36:   maxIterations: 10  # positive integer\n37:   convergenceThreshold: 0.05  # decimal 0..1\n38:   convergence_mode: default  # default | off | sliding-window | divergent\n39:   executor: native  # native | cli-opencode | cli-claude-code\n40:   executor_model: \"\"  # optional executor-specific model id (cli-opencode e.g. xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro, minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M2.7-highspeed)\n41:   executor_config_dir: \"\"  # optional, cli-claude-code only; maps to CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR\n42:   executor_reasoning: \"\"  # optional reasoning effort\n43:   executor_service_tier: \"\"  # optional service tier\n44:   executor_timeout: 900  # optional positive integer seconds\n45:   resource_map_emit: true  # boolean\n46: ```\n47: \n48: Rules: see `auto-mode-contract.md` §2 (unspecified fields fall back to default; marker fields take precedence over `$ARGUMENTS` flags; unknown fields warn; malformed lines parse-error).\n49: \n50: ### Default Resolution Table\n51: \n52: | Field                   | Required | Resolves Via                                                                                                                                                                                           | Default                            | Tier-2 Candidate                                        |\n53: | -------------------------| ----------| --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------| ------------------------------------| ---------------------------------------------------------|\n54: | `research_topic`        | Y        | `$ARGUMENTS` positional topic, or marker `research_topic`                                                                                                                                              | none                               | N                                                       |\n55: | `spec_folder`           | Y        | flag `--spec-folder`, marker `spec_folder`, `scope-extract` → a spec-folder path named in the topic/`$ARGUMENTS` that resolves to an existing folder (auto-bound + stripped, per `auto_mode_contract` §1 source 3), or targeted choice among suggested existing/new/update-related/phase folder | none | Y, ONLY when topic is present, names no resolvable spec folder, and the folder choice is ambiguous |\n56: | `execution_mode`        | Y        | attached suffix `:auto` or marker `execution_mode`                                                                                                                                                     | `AUTONOMOUS` under `:auto`         | N                                                       |\n57: | `maxIterations`         | Y        | flag `--max-iterations`, marker `maxIterations`, or default                                                                                                                                            | `10`                               | N                                                       |\n58: | `convergenceThreshold`  | Y        | flag `--convergence`, marker `convergenceThreshold`, or default                                                                                                                                        | `0.05`                             | N                                                       |\n59: | `convergence_mode`      | Y        | flag `--convergence-mode=default|off|sliding-window|divergent`, marker `convergence_mode`, or default                                                                                                  | `default`                          | N                                                       |\n60: | `executor`              | N        | flag `--executor`, marker `executor`, config file, or default                                                                                                                                          | `native`                           | N                                                       |\n61: | `executor_model`        | N        | flag `--model`, marker `executor_model`, or executor-specific validation                                                                                                                               | none                               | N                                                       |\n62: | `executor_config_dir`   | N        | flag `--config-dir`, marker `executor_config_dir`, or executor-specific default                                                                                                                        | none                               | N                                                       |\n63: | `executor_reasoning`    | N        | flag `--reasoning-effort`, marker `executor_reasoning`, or executor default                                                                                                                            | none                               | N                                                       |\n64: | `executor_service_tier` | N        | flag `--service-tier`, marker `executor_service_tier`, or executor default                                                                                                                             | none                               | N                                                       |\n65: | `executor_timeout`      | N        | flag `--executor-timeout`, marker `executor_timeout`, or default                                                                                                                                       | `900`                              | N                                                       |\n66: | `resource_map_emit`     | N        | flag `--no-resource-map`, marker `resource_map_emit`, or default                                                                                                                                       | `true`                             | N                                                       |\n67: | `fanout_executors`      | N        | repeatable `--executor=<type>` flags or `--executors=<json>`; each `--executor` group accepts `--model`, `--config-dir`, `--reasoning-effort`, `--service-tier`, `--executor-timeout`, `--iters`, `--label`, `--count` | none (single-executor when absent) | N                                                       |\n68: | `fanout_concurrency`    | N        | flag `--concurrency=N`                                                                                                                                                                                 | `2`                                | N                                                       |\n69: \n70: **Fan-out default policy:** 0–1 `--executor` flags and no `--executors` → `config.executor` (single-executor, default, unchanged). 2+ `--executor` flags, `--executors`, or any `--count > 1` → `config.fanout`. Native fan-out (count N for `native` executor) runs N sequential `@deep-research` agent dispatches with isolated dirs. CLI fan-out runs N headless subprocesses concurrently in the capped pool.\n71: \n72: ### Consolidated Prompt Template\n73: \n74: **STATUS: ☐ BLOCKED**\n75: \n76: ```\n77: EXECUTE THIS SINGLE CONSOLIDATED PROMPT:\n78: \n79: 1. CHECK for mode suffix:\n80:    |-- \":auto\"         -> execution_mode = \"AUTONOMOUS\"\n81:    |-- \":confirm\"      -> execution_mode = \"INTERACTIVE\"\n82:    +-- No suffix       -> execution_mode = \"ASK\"\n83: \n84: 2. CHECK $ARGUMENTS for topic:\n85:    |-- Has content (ignoring suffixes and flags):\n86:    |     -> research_topic = $ARGUMENTS, omit Q0\n87:    +-- Empty -> include Q0\n88: \n89: 3. PARSE optional flags from $ARGUMENTS:\n90:    |-- --max-iterations=N -> maxIterations = N\n91:    |-- --convergence=N -> convergenceThreshold = N\n92:    |-- --convergence-mode=default|off|sliding-window|divergent -> antiConvergence.convergenceMode = value\n93:    |-- --spec-folder=PATH -> spec_path = PATH, omit Q1\n94:    |-- --executor=<type> -> config.executor.type (`native` | `cli-opencode` | `cli-claude-code`)\n95:    |-- --model=<id> -> config.executor.model (for example `gpt-5.4`)\n96:    |-- --config-dir=<path> -> config.executor.configDir (cli-claude-code only; fan-out sets CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR)\n97:    |-- --reasoning-effort=<level> -> config.executor.reasoningEffort (`none` | `minimal` | `low` | `medium` | `high` | `xhigh` | `max`)\n98:    |-- --service-tier=<tier> -> config.executor.serviceTier (`priority` | `standard` | `fast`)\n99:    |-- --executor-timeout=<seconds> -> config.executor.timeoutSeconds (positive integer, default `900`)\n100:    |-- --no-resource-map -> config.resource_map.emit = false\n101:    |-- --executor=<type> [--model=X] [--config-dir=PATH] [--reasoning-effort=Y] [--service-tier=Z] [--executor-timeout=N] [--iters=N] [--label=X] [--count=N]\n102:    |     (repeatable; each occurrence adds one entry to config.fanout.executors)\n103:    |-- --executors=<json> -> config.fanout.executors = parse(json) escape hatch for complex configs\n104:    |-- --concurrency=N -> config.fanout.concurrency (default 2)\n105:    |\n106:    |   Fan-out default policy:\n107:    |   - 0 or 1 --executor (no --executors, no count>1): write config.executor (single, unchanged)\n108:    |   - 2+ --executor flags, --executors, or any count>1: write config.fanout\n109:    |\n110:    +-- Defaults: maxIterations=10, convergenceThreshold=0.05, antiConvergence.convergenceMode=`default`, antiConvergence.divergent=`{}`, config.executor.type=`native`, config.executor.timeoutSeconds=900, config.resource_map.emit=`true`\n111: \n112:    Executor precedence for setup resolution:\n113:    - CLI flag > config file > schema defaults\n114:    - The generated `deep-research-config.json` stores executor settings under `config.executor.*`\n115: \n116:    Parsing to config mapping:\n117:    - `--executor` -> `config.executor.type`\n118:    - `--model` -> `config.executor.model`\n119:    - `--config-dir` -> `config.executor.configDir`\n120:    - `--reasoning-effort` -> `config.executor.reasoningEffort`\n121:    - `--service-tier` -> `config.executor.serviceTier`\n122:    - `--executor-timeout` -> `config.executor.timeoutSeconds`\n123:    - `--convergence-mode` -> `antiConvergence.convergenceMode`\n124: \n125:    Validation hook:\n126:    - `parseExecutorConfig` from `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts` runs at config-write time\n127:    - Invalid combinations fail fast with clear errors, including `cli-opencode` without `--model` and reserved-but-unwired executor kinds\n128: \n129: 4. Search for related spec folders across alias roots:\n130:    $ find specs .opencode/specs -mindepth 2 -maxdepth 2 -type d 2>/dev/null | sort | tail -10\n131: \n132: 5. Search for prior work (background):\n133:    - memory_context({ input: research_topic OR \"deep-research\", mode: \"focused\", includeContent: true })\n134:    - Store: prior_work_found = [yes/no]\n135: \n136: 6. ASK with SINGLE prompt (include only applicable questions):\n137:    - Include Q-Exec only when `--executor` is NOT present and the topic text does NOT already mention executor hints such as `cli-opencode`, `cli-claude-code`, or `gpt-5.4`\n138:    - If Q-Exec is omitted and no executor is otherwise resolved, default to `native`\n139: \n140:    Q0. Research Topic (if not in command): What topic to research deeply?\n141: \n142:    Q1. Spec Folder (required):\n143:      A) Use existing [suggest if found]\n144:      B) Create new under `specs/[track]/[###]-[slug]/` (accept `.opencode/specs/` alias roots when already in use)\n145:      C) Update related [if match found]\n146:      D) Phase folder (e.g., `specs/NN-track/NNN-name/001-phase/` or matching `.opencode/specs/` alias)\n147: \n148:    Q2. Execution Mode (if no suffix):\n149:      A) Autonomous -- all iterations without approval\n150:      B) Interactive -- pause at each iteration for review\n151: \n152:    Q3. Max Iterations (if not set via flag):\n153:      Default is 10. Change? [Enter number or press enter for default]\n154: \n155:    Q-Exec. Executor (optional, press enter for default):\n156:      A) Native (default) — dispatch via @deep-research agent with Opus.\n157:      B) cli-opencode — `opencode run --model X --format json --dangerously-skip-permissions --pure --dir {repo_root} [--variant Y] \"PROMPT\" </dev/null` (no `--agent`: current opencode rejects top-level `--agent general` — default agent runs; required for MiniMax/Xiaomi token-plan models). `reasoningEffort` maps to `--variant`. No service-tier.\n158:      C) cli-claude-code — `claude -p \"PROMPT\" --model X --permission-mode acceptEdits` with optional --effort and optional `--config-dir=PATH` for CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR. No service-tier.\n159: \n160:    Reply format examples:\n161:    - `\"A, A\"`\n162:    - `\"WebSocket research, A, B, 15\"`\n163:    - `\"WebSocket reconnection strategies, B, A, 10, 0.05, B, gpt-5.4, high, fast\"`\n164:    - `\"agent execution guardrails research, B, A, 15, 0.05, C, gpt-5.4, _, _\"`\n165: \n166: 7. WAIT for user response (DO NOT PROCEED)\n167: \n168: 8. Parse response and store ALL results:\n169:    - research_topic = [from Q0 or $ARGUMENTS]\n170:    - spec_choice = [A/B/C/D from Q1]\n171:    - spec_path = [derived path]\n172:    - execution_mode = [AUTONOMOUS/INTERACTIVE]\n173:    - maxIterations = [from Q3 or flag or default 10]\n174:    - convergenceThreshold = [from flag or default 0.05]\n175:    - convergence_mode = [from flag, marker, or default `default`; one of `default`, `off`, `sliding-window`, `divergent`]\n176:     - executor config = [CLI flags, compact reply, config file, or default `native`; map compact reply fields to `config.executor.type/model/configDir/reasoningEffort/serviceTier`, and accept an optional volunteered convergence value before executor fields]\n177: \n178: 9. SET STATUS: PASSED\n179: \n180: STOP HERE - Wait for user answers before continuing.\n181: \n182: DO NOT proceed until user explicitly answers\n183: NEVER auto-create spec folders without confirmation\n184: NEVER split questions into multiple prompts\n185: ```\n186: \n187: **Phase Output:**\n188: - `research_topic` | `spec_choice` | `spec_path`\n189: - `execution_mode` | `maxIterations` | `convergenceThreshold` | `convergence_mode`\n190: \n191: ## 2. Dashboard / Checkpoint Layout\n192: \n193: ### Deep Research\n194: \n195: Conduct autonomous iterative deep research with convergence detection. Each iteration dispatches a fresh LEAF agent (`@deep-research`) that reads externalized state, performs focused investigation, and writes findings to files.\n196: \n197: For code review and quality auditing, see `/deep:review`.\n198: \n199: ### Convergence Threshold Semantics\n200: \n201: **Default:** 0.05 on newInfoRatio (fully-new=1.0, partially-new=0.5, +0.10 simplicity bonus, capped 1.0)\n202: \n203: **Semantic:** `convergenceThreshold` compares newly discovered information against accumulated research knowledge with negative-knowledge emphasis. Lower = more iterations / higher signal threshold.\n204: \n205: **NOT INTERCHANGEABLE with siblings:**\n206: - `deep-review` uses 0.10 default on weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio\n207: - `deep-ai-council` (proposed) uses 0.20 default on adjudicator-verdict stability\n208: \n209: Carrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. See 116 research at `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/z_archive/006-deep-skill-evolution/007-deep-stack-cross-cutting/001-unique-value-differentiation/research/research.md` §2 F56/F78, §5 Recommendation, and §6 Parity Invariants.\n210: \n211: ```yaml\n212: role: Deep Research Loop Manager\n213: purpose: Run iterative research cycles until convergence or max iterations\n214: action: Execute YAML workflow managing init, loop, synthesis, and save phases\n215: operating_mode:\n216:   workflow: iterative_loop\n217:   compliance: MANDATORY\n218:   execution: autonomous_or_interactive\n219:   validation: convergence_detection\n220: ```\n221: \n222: ### Purpose\n223: \n224: Run an iterative loop for deep research: Initialize state under `{artifact_dir}` (resolved via `resolveArtifactRoot()` — root specs use `{spec_folder}/research/`; child phases and sub-phases use `{spec_folder}/research/{packet}-pt-{NN}/`), dispatch `@deep-research` agent per iteration, evaluate convergence, synthesize findings into `{artifact_dir}/research.md`, and emit `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` at convergence unless `--no-resource-map` disables it. Use when deep investigation requiring multiple rounds of discovery.\n225: \n226: ### Contract\n227: \n228: **Inputs:** `$ARGUMENTS` -- Research topic with optional flags and mode suffix\n229: **Outputs:** Spec folder with `{artifact_dir}/` packet (`{spec_folder}/research/` for root specs or `{spec_folder}/research/{packet}-pt-{NN}/` for nested phases), `research.md`, optional `resource-map.md`, state files, and `STATUS=<OK|FAIL|CANCELLED>`\n230: \n231: ### Workflow Overview\n232: \n233: | Phase | Name | Purpose | Outputs |\n234: |-------|------|---------|---------|\n235: | Init | Initialize | Create config, strategy (with research charter), state files | State files in `research/` |\n236: | Loop | Iterate | Dispatch @deep-research agent, evaluate convergence + quality guards, generate dashboard | iteration-NNN.md files, deep-research-dashboard.md |\n237: | Synth | Synthesize | Emit `research/resource-map.md` and compile final research/research.md | research/resource-map.md, research/research.md (17 sections) |\n238: | Save | Preserve | Refresh continuity update in canonical spec docs | canonical spec doc updated via `generate-context.js` |\n239: \n240: ### Execution Modes\n241: \n242: | Mode | Invocation | Behavior |\n243: |------|-----------|----------|\n244: | `:auto` | `/deep:research:auto \"topic\"` | All iterations without approval |\n245: | `:confirm` | `/deep:research:confirm \"topic\"` | Multi-gate review at setup, iteration, and synthesis |\n246: | (default) | `/deep:research \"topic\"` | Ask user to choose mode during setup |\n247: \n248: ### Memory Integration Before Starting\n249: \n250: - `memory_context({ input: topic, intent: \"understand\" })` -- Load prior research\n251: - Inject results into strategy.md \"Known Context\" section\n252: \n253: ### Code Context Bootstrap\n254: \n255: - Use Code Graph (`code_graph_query`) to find relevant code examples before starting research\n256: - Query: 2-5 word concept descriptions related to the research topic\n257: - Inject discovered code patterns into strategy.md \"Known Context\" section alongside memory findings\n258: \n259: ## 3. Results Display\n260: \n261: ### Output Formats\n262: \n263: **Success:**\n264: ```\n265: Deep research complete.\n266: Iterations: [N] | Stop reason: [converged|max_iterations|all_answered]\n267: Artifacts: research/research.md, research/resource-map.md (unless `--no-resource-map`), [N] iteration files, continuity update in canonical spec docs refreshed\n268: Ready for: /speckit:plan [feature-description]\n269: STATUS=OK PATH=[spec-folder-path]\n270: ```\n271: \n272: **Failure:**\n273: ```\n274: Error: [error description]  Phase: [phase name]\n275: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"[message]\"\n276: ```\n277: \n278: ### Memory Integration After Completing\n279: \n280: - `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json [spec-folder]`\n281: - Verify that the canonical save routed continuity into the expected packet doc (decision-record.md / implementation-summary.md / handover.md)\n282: \n283: ### Anchor Tags (Automatic)\n284: \n285: `ANCHOR:deep-research-[topic]`, `ANCHOR:findings`, `ANCHOR:convergence-report`\n286: \n287: ### Error Handling\n288: \n289: | Error | Action |\n290: |-------|--------|\n291: | Agent dispatch timeout | Retry once with reduced scope, then mark timeout |\n292: | State file missing | Reconstruct from iteration files |\n293: | 3+ consecutive failures | Halt loop, enter synthesis with partial findings |\n294: | Memory save failure | Save to `scratch/` as backup |\n295: \n296: ## 4. Next-Step Suggestions\n297: \n298: ### Skill Reference\n299: \n300: Full protocol documentation: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md`\n301: \n302: Key references:\n303: - Loop protocol: `system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/loop-protocol.md`\n304: - Spec check protocol: `system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/spec-check-protocol.md`\n305: - State formats: `system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/state/state-format.md`\n306: - Convergence: `system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md`\n307: - Quick reference: `system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/guides/quick-reference.md`\n308: \n309: For code review, see `deep-review` skill (`.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/SKILL.md`).\n310: \n311: ### Examples\n312: \n313: ```\n314: # Single-executor (default — unchanged)\n315: /deep:research:auto \"WebSocket reconnection strategies across browsers\"\n316: /deep:research:confirm \"distributed caching patterns for microservices\"\n317: /deep:research:auto \"API rate limiting approaches\" --max-iterations 5 --convergence 0.10\n318: \n319: # Fan-out: two CLI lineages in parallel (cli-opencode + cli-claude-code)\n320: /deep:research:auto \"caching patterns\" \\\n321:   --executor=cli-opencode --model=o4-mini --label= \\\n322:   --executor=cli-claude-code --model=claude-opus-4-8 --label=claude \\\n323:   --concurrency=2\n324: \n325: # Fan-out: native (sequential agent dispatches) + CLI lineages mixed\n326: /deep:research:auto \"distributed systems consensus\" \\\n327:   --executor=native --count=1 --label=native \\\n328:   --executor=cli-opencode --model=o4-mini --count=2 \\\n329:   --concurrency=3\n330: \n331: # Fan-out via JSON escape hatch\n332: /deep:research:auto \"WebRTC internals\" \\\n333:   --executors='[{\"kind\":\"cli-opencode\",\"model\":\"o4-mini\",\"label\":\"\",\"count\":3},{\"kind\":\"cli-claude-code\",\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-8\",\"label\":\"claude\",\"count\":2}]' \\\n334:   --concurrency=4\n335: ```\n336: \n337: > **Note on native fan-out:** `--executor=native --count=N` dispatches N sequential `@deep-research` sub-agents with isolated artifact dirs. Not pooled. Best for count 1–3. For higher parallelism, use CLI executor kinds.\n338: \n339: ### Next Steps\n340: \n341: > **Note:** Deep-research now anchors bounded findings back into `spec.md` through the generated findings fence while keeping `research/research.md` canonical.\n342: \n343: | Condition | Suggested Command | Reason |\n344: |-----------|-------------------|--------|\n345: | Research complete, ready to plan | `/speckit:plan [feature]` | Use findings for spec/plan |\n346: | Need more investigation | `/deep:research [new-topic]` | Another deep research session |\n347: | Need code/spec audit | `/deep:review [target]` | Iterative code review |\n348: | Want to refresh search support | `/memory:save [spec-folder]` | Refresh the indexed canonical spec document while canonical continuity stays in spec docs |\n349: \n350: ### Key Differences (vs. single-pass research)\n351: \n352: - Iterative (multi-pass) vs. single-pass research\n353: - Dispatches `@deep-research` LEAF agent per iteration (fresh context each time)\n354: - Externalized state via JSONL + strategy files\n355: - Automatic convergence detection with quality guards (3 binary checks before STOP)\n356: - Persistent dashboard auto-generated each iteration for progress tracking\n357: - Negative knowledge (ruled-out directions) as first-class research output\n358: - Research charter (non-goals, stop conditions) validated at init\n359: - Does NOT proceed to implementation\n360: \n361: ### Command Chain\n362: \n363: **Research path:** `/deep:research` → `/speckit:plan` → `/speckit:implement`\n364: **Review:** `/deep:review` → (if issues) `/speckit:plan` → `/speckit:implement`\n365: \n366: ### Offline Optimization\n367: \n368: Convergence thresholds and recovery settings used by this command are a governed maintenance surface managed by the offline loop optimizer (042.004). The optimizer tunes deterministic numeric thresholds offline against real run traces and emits advisory-only candidate patches.\n369: \n370: **Key constraints:**\n371: - Optimization is offline only -- it does not run during live research sessions\n372: - Promotion is advisory-only until replay fixtures and behavioral suites exist\n373: - Prompt optimization is deferred future work (Phase 4b) and will use generated prompt packs, never direct agent markdown mutation\n374: \n375: **References:**\n376: - Optimizer configuration: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json`\n377: - Tunable thresholds: `convergenceThreshold`, `stuckThreshold`, `maxIterations`\n378: - Convergence reference: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md`\n\n(End of file - total 378 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Start Research Loop Presentation Contract\n\nPresentation source of truth for `/deep:research`. The command router owns only mode selection, setup binding, and asset loading. Workflow YAML owns execution. This file owns visible prompts, dashboard/checkpoint layout, final result displays, examples, and next-step wording.\n\n## 1. Startup Presentation\n\nThis workflow gathers all setup inputs in one prompt. Confirm mode still includes multiple approval gates after setup; only the setup round-trip is consolidated here.\n\nFor `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt MUST be the first visible response. No implementation or file-modifying tool calls before asking. Lightweight read-only discovery to suggest a spec folder or load prior context is allowed, then ask ALL questions immediately and wait.\n\nFor `:auto`, do not emit the consolidated prompt by default. Resolve setup with the three-tier branch below, then load the auto YAML only after all required values are bound.\n\n### `:auto` Setup Resolution\n\nSetup contract: see `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/auto-mode-contract.md`.\n\nUnder `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS` (from the `:auto` suffix), follow the three-tier flow:\n\n1. **Tier 1 — Resolve confidently** (contract §1): parse `$ARGUMENTS` flags + `PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:` block (§2) + the Default Resolution Table below (§3). When every required field is resolved, persist to `{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json` (shape: `researchTopic`, `specFolder`, `maxIterations`, `convergenceThreshold`, `antiConvergence.convergenceMode`, reserved `antiConvergence.divergent: {}`, `executionMode: \"auto\"`, `resource_map.emit`, `config.executor.*`), bind runtime YAML placeholders, set `STATUS: PASSED`, load `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml`. End §0.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-presentation.txt","text":"# Deep Start Research Loop Presentation Contract\n\nPresentation source of truth for `/deep:research`. The command router owns only mode selection, setup binding, and asset loading. Workflow YAML owns execution. This file owns visible prompts, dashboard/checkpoint layout, final result displays, examples, and next-step wording.\n\n## 1. Startup Presentation\n\nThis workflow gathers all setup inputs in one prompt. Confirm mode still includes multiple approval gates after setup; only the setup round-trip is consolidated here.\n\nFor `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt MUST be the first visible response. No implementation or file-modifying tool calls before asking. Lightweight read-only discovery to suggest a spec folder or load prior context is allowed, then ask ALL questions immediately and wait.\n\nFor `:auto`, do not emit the consolidated prompt by default. Resolve setup with the three-tier branch below, then load the auto YAML only after all required values are bound.\n\n### `:auto` Setup Resolution\n\nSetup contract: see `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/auto-mode-contract.md`.\n\nUnder `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS` (from the `:auto` suffix), follow the three-tier flow:\n\n1. **Tier 1 — Resolve confidently** (contract §1): parse `$ARGUMENTS` flags + `PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:` block (§2) + the Default Resolution Table below (§3). When every required field is resolved, persist to `{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json` (shape: `researchTopic`, `specFolder`, `maxIterations`, `convergenceThreshold`, `antiConvergence.convergenceMode`, reserved `antiConvergence.divergent: {}`, `executionMode: \"auto\"`, `resource_map.emit`, `config.executor.*`), bind runtime YAML placeholders, set `STATUS: PASSED`, load `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml`. End §0.\n\n2. **Tier 2 — Targeted ask** (contract §1): when 1-2 required fields are genuinely ambiguous AND no default exists, emit ONE narrow question per ambiguous field. Command-specific Tier-2-eligible fields (per the Default Resolution Table below): `spec_folder`. **Ordering rule**: none needed. Missing `research_topic` is absence, not ambiguity — go to Tier 3.\n\n3. **Tier 3 — Fail fast** (contract §4): emit the named-missing-inputs error format with `/deep:research:auto` as the command name. Exit non-zero. Do not load YAML.\n\n`:confirm` path stays unchanged — see the consolidated setup prompt section below.\n\n### PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS Schema (for `:auto` non-interactive dispatch)\n\nThe dispatched prompt body may contain one structured marker block. Parse it before applying defaults. Grammar: see `auto-mode-contract.md` §2.\n\n```yaml\nPRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n  research_topic: WebSocket reconnection strategies  # string\n  spec_folder: <spec-folder>  # existing | new | update-related | phase-folder | explicit path\n  execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS  # from :auto suffix\n  maxIterations: 10  # positive integer\n  convergenceThreshold: 0.05  # decimal 0..1\n  convergence_mode: default  # default | off | sliding-window | divergent\n  executor: native  # native | cli-opencode | cli-claude-code\n  executor_model: \"\"  # optional executor-specific model id (cli-opencode e.g. xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro, minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M2.7-highspeed)\n  executor_config_dir: \"\"  # optional, cli-claude-code only; maps to CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR\n  executor_reasoning: \"\"  # optional reasoning effort\n  executor_service_tier: \"\"  # optional service tier\n  executor_timeout: 900  # optional positive integer seconds\n  resource_map_emit: true  # boolean\n```\n\nRules: see `auto-mode-contract.md` §2 (unspecified fields fall back to default; marker fields take precedence over `$ARGUMENTS` flags; unknown fields warn; malformed lines parse-error).\n\n### Default Resolution Table\n\n| Field                   | Required | Resolves Via                                                                                                                                                                                           | Default                            | Tier-2 Candidate                                        |\n| -------------------------| ----------| --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------| ------------------------------------| ---------------------------------------------------------|\n| `research_topic`        | Y        | `$ARGUMENTS` positional topic, or marker `research_topic`                                                                                                                                              | none                               | N                                                       |\n| `spec_folder`           | Y        | flag `--spec-folder`, marker `spec_folder`, `scope-extract` → a spec-folder path named in the topic/`$ARGUMENTS` that resolves to an existing folder (auto-bound + stripped, per `auto_mode_contract` §1 source 3), or targeted choice among suggested existing/new/update-related/phase folder | none | Y, ONLY when topic is present, names no resolvable spec folder, and the folder choice is ambiguous |\n| `execution_mode`        | Y        | attached suffix `:auto` or marker `execution_mode`                                                                                                                                                     | `AUTONOMOUS` under `:auto`         | N                                                       |\n| `maxIterations`         | Y        | flag `--max-iterations`, marker `maxIterations`, or default                                                                                                                                            | `10`                               | N                                                       |\n| `convergenceThreshold`  | Y        | flag `--convergence`, marker `convergenceThreshold`, or default                                                                                                                                        | `0.05`                             | N                                                       |\n| `convergence_mode`      | Y        | flag `--convergence-mode=default|off|sliding-window|divergent`, marker `convergence_mode`, or default                                                                                                  | `default`                          | N                                                       |\n| `executor`              | N        | flag `--executor`, marker `executor`, config file, or default                                                                                                                                          | `native`                           | N                                                       |\n| `executor_model`        | N        | flag `--model`, marker `executor_model`, or executor-specific validation                                                                                                                               | none                               | N                                                       |\n| `executor_config_dir`   | N        | flag `--config-dir`, marker `executor_config_dir`, or executor-specific default                                                                                                                        | none                               | N                                                       |\n| `executor_reasoning`    | N        | flag `--reasoning-effort`, marker `executor_reasoning`, or executor default                                                                                                                            | none                               | N                                                       |\n| `executor_service_tier` | N        | flag `--service-tier`, marker `executor_service_tier`, or executor default                                                                                                                             | none                               | N                                                       |\n| `executor_timeout`      | N        | flag `--executor-timeout`, marker `executor_timeout`, or default                                                                                                                                       | `900`                              | N                                                       |\n| `resource_map_emit`     | N        | flag `--no-resource-map`, marker `resource_map_emit`, or default                                                                                                                                       | `true`                             | N                                                       |\n| `fanout_executors`      | N        | repeatable `--executor=<type>` flags or `--executors=<json>`; each `--executor` group accepts `--model`, `--config-dir`, `--reasoning-effort`, `--service-tier`, `--executor-timeout`, `--iters`, `--label`, `--count` | none (single-executor when absent) | N                                                       |\n| `fanout_concurrency`    | N        | flag `--concurrency=N`                                                                                                                                                                                 | `2`                                | N                                                       |\n\n**Fan-out default policy:** 0–1 `--executor` flags and no `--executors` → `config.executor` (single-executor, default, unchanged). 2+ `--executor` flags, `--executors`, or any `--count > 1` → `config.fanout`. Native fan-out (count N for `native` executor) runs N sequential `@deep-research` agent dispatches with isolated dirs. CLI fan-out runs N headless subprocesses concurrently in the capped pool.\n\n### Consolidated Prompt Template\n\n**STATUS: ☐ BLOCKED**\n\n```\nEXECUTE THIS SINGLE CONSOLIDATED PROMPT:\n\n1. CHECK for mode suffix:\n   |-- \":auto\"         -> execution_mode = \"AUTONOMOUS\"\n   |-- \":confirm\"      -> execution_mode = \"INTERACTIVE\"\n   +-- No suffix       -> execution_mode = \"ASK\"\n\n2. CHECK $ARGUMENTS for topic:\n   |-- Has content (ignoring suffixes and flags):\n   |     -> research_topic = $ARGUMENTS, omit Q0\n   +-- Empty -> include Q0\n\n3. PARSE optional flags from $ARGUMENTS:\n   |-- --max-iterations=N -> maxIterations = N\n   |-- --convergence=N -> convergenceThreshold = N\n   |-- --convergence-mode=default|off|sliding-window|divergent -> antiConvergence.convergenceMode = value\n   |-- --spec-folder=PATH -> spec_path = PATH, omit Q1\n   |-- --executor=<type> -> config.executor.type (`native` | `cli-opencode` | `cli-claude-code`)\n   |-- --model=<id> -> config.executor.model (for example `gpt-5.4`)\n   |-- --config-dir=<path> -> config.executor.configDir (cli-claude-code only; fan-out sets CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR)\n   |-- --reasoning-effort=<level> -> config.executor.reasoningEffort (`none` | `minimal` | `low` | `medium` | `high` | `xhigh` | `max`)\n   |-- --service-tier=<tier> -> config.executor.serviceTier (`priority` | `standard` | `fast`)\n   |-- --executor-timeout=<seconds> -> config.executor.timeoutSeconds (positive integer, default `900`)\n   |-- --no-resource-map -> config.resource_map.emit = false\n   |-- --executor=<type> [--model=X] [--config-dir=PATH] [--reasoning-effort=Y] [--service-tier=Z] [--executor-timeout=N] [--iters=N] [--label=X] [--count=N]\n   |     (repeatable; each occurrence adds one entry to config.fanout.executors)\n   |-- --executors=<json> -> config.fanout.executors = parse(json) escape hatch for complex configs\n   |-- --concurrency=N -> config.fanout.concurrency (default 2)\n   |\n   |   Fan-out default policy:\n   |   - 0 or 1 --executor (no --executors, no count>1): write config.executor (single, unchanged)\n   |   - 2+ --executor flags, --executors, or any count>1: write config.fanout\n   |\n   +-- Defaults: maxIterations=10, convergenceThreshold=0.05, antiConvergence.convergenceMode=`default`, antiConvergence.divergent=`{}`, config.executor.type=`native`, config.executor.timeoutSeconds=900, config.resource_map.emit=`true`\n\n   Executor precedence for setup resolution:\n   - CLI flag > config file > schema defaults\n   - The generated `deep-research-config.json` stores executor settings under `config.executor.*`\n\n   Parsing to config mapping:\n   - `--executor` -> `config.executor.type`\n   - `--model` -> `config.executor.model`\n   - `--config-dir` -> `config.executor.configDir`\n   - `--reasoning-effort` -> `config.executor.reasoningEffort`\n   - `--service-tier` -> `config.executor.serviceTier`\n   - `--executor-timeout` -> `config.executor.timeoutSeconds`\n   - `--convergence-mode` -> `antiConvergence.convergenceMode`\n\n   Validation hook:\n   - `parseExecutorConfig` from `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts` runs at config-write time\n   - Invalid combinations fail fast with clear errors, including `cli-opencode` without `--model` and reserved-but-unwired executor kinds\n\n4. Search for related spec folders across alias roots:\n   $ find specs .opencode/specs -mindepth 2 -maxdepth 2 -type d 2>/dev/null | sort | tail -10\n\n5. Search for prior work (background):\n   - memory_context({ input: research_topic OR \"deep-research\", mode: \"focused\", includeContent: true })\n   - Store: prior_work_found = [yes/no]\n\n6. ASK with SINGLE prompt (include only applicable questions):\n   - Include Q-Exec only when `--executor` is NOT present and the topic text does NOT already mention executor hints such as `cli-opencode`, `cli-claude-code`, or `gpt-5.4`\n   - If Q-Exec is omitted and no executor is otherwise resolved, default to `native`\n\n   Q0. Research Topic (if not in command): What topic to research deeply?\n\n   Q1. Spec Folder (required):\n     A) Use existing [suggest if found]\n     B) Create new under `specs/[track]/[###]-[slug]/` (accept `.opencode/specs/` alias roots when already in use)\n     C) Update related [if match found]\n     D) Phase folder (e.g., `specs/NN-track/NNN-name/001-phase/` or matching `.opencode/specs/` alias)\n\n   Q2. Execution Mode (if no suffix):\n     A) Autonomous -- all iterations without approval\n     B) Interactive -- pause at each iteration for review\n\n   Q3. Max Iterations (if not set via flag):\n     Default is 10. Change? [Enter number or press enter for default]\n\n   Q-Exec. Executor (optional, press enter for default):\n     A) Native (default) — dispatch via @deep-research agent with Opus.\n     B) cli-opencode — `opencode run --model X --format json --dangerously-skip-permissions --pure --dir {repo_root} [--variant Y] \"PROMPT\" </dev/null` (no `--agent`: current opencode rejects top-level `--agent general` — default agent runs; required for MiniMax/Xiaomi token-plan models). `reasoningEffort` maps to `--variant`. No service-tier.\n     C) cli-claude-code — `claude -p \"PROMPT\" --model X --permission-mode acceptEdits` with optional --effort and optional `--config-dir=PATH` for CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR. No service-tier.\n\n   Reply format examples:\n   - `\"A, A\"`\n   - `\"WebSocket research, A, B, 15\"`\n   - `\"WebSocket reconnection strategies, B, A, 10, 0.05, B, gpt-5.4, high, fast\"`\n   - `\"agent execution guardrails research, B, A, 15, 0.05, C, gpt-5.4, _, _\"`\n\n7. WAIT for user response (DO NOT PROCEED)\n\n8. Parse response and store ALL results:\n   - research_topic = [from Q0 or $ARGUMENTS]\n   - spec_choice = [A/B/C/D from Q1]\n   - spec_path = [derived path]\n   - execution_mode = [AUTONOMOUS/INTERACTIVE]\n   - maxIterations = [from Q3 or flag or default 10]\n   - convergenceThreshold = [from flag or default 0.05]\n   - convergence_mode = [from flag, marker, or default `default`; one of `default`, `off`, `sliding-window`, `divergent`]\n    - executor config = [CLI flags, compact reply, config file, or default `native`; map compact reply fields to `config.executor.type/model/configDir/reasoningEffort/serviceTier`, and accept an optional volunteered convergence value before executor fields]\n\n9. SET STATUS: PASSED\n\nSTOP HERE - Wait for user answers before continuing.\n\nDO NOT proceed until user explicitly answers\nNEVER auto-create spec folders without confirmation\nNEVER split questions into multiple prompts\n```\n\n**Phase Output:**\n- `research_topic` | `spec_choice` | `spec_path`\n- `execution_mode` | `maxIterations` | `convergenceThreshold` | `convergence_mode`\n\n## 2. Dashboard / Checkpoint Layout\n\n### Deep Research\n\nConduct autonomous iterative deep research with convergence detection. Each iteration dispatches a fresh LEAF agent (`@deep-research`) that reads externalized state, performs focused investigation, and writes findings to files.\n\nFor code review and quality auditing, see `/deep:review`.\n\n### Convergence Threshold Semantics\n\n**Default:** 0.05 on newInfoRatio (fully-new=1.0, partially-new=0.5, +0.10 simplicity bonus, capped 1.0)\n\n**Semantic:** `convergenceThreshold` compares newly discovered information against accumulated research knowledge with negative-knowledge emphasis. Lower = more iterations / higher signal threshold.\n\n**NOT INTERCHANGEABLE with siblings:**\n- `deep-review` uses 0.10 default on weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio\n- `deep-ai-council` (proposed) uses 0.20 default on adjudicator-verdict stability\n\nCarrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. See 116 research at `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/z_archive/006-deep-skill-evolution/007-deep-stack-cross-cutting/001-unique-value-differentiation/research/research.md` §2 F56/F78, §5 Recommendation, and §6 Parity Invariants.\n\n```yaml\nrole: Deep Research Loop Manager\npurpose: Run iterative research cycles until convergence or max iterations\naction: Execute YAML workflow managing init, loop, synthesis, and save phases\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: iterative_loop\n  compliance: MANDATORY\n  execution: autonomous_or_interactive\n  validation: convergence_detection\n```\n\n### Purpose\n\nRun an iterative loop for deep research: Initialize state under `{artifact_dir}` (resolved via `resolveArtifactRoot()` — root specs use `{spec_folder}/research/`; child phases and sub-phases use `{spec_folder}/research/{packet}-pt-{NN}/`), dispatch `@deep-research` agent per iteration, evaluate convergence, synthesize findings into `{artifact_dir}/research.md`, and emit `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` at convergence unless `--no-resource-map` disables it. Use when deep investigation requiring multiple rounds of discovery.\n\n### Contract\n\n**Inputs:** `$ARGUMENTS` -- Research topic with optional flags and mode suffix\n**Outputs:** Spec folder with `{artifact_dir}/` packet (`{spec_folder}/research/` for root specs or `{spec_folder}/research/{packet}-pt-{NN}/` for nested phases), `research.md`, optional `resource-map.md`, state files, and `STATUS=<OK|FAIL|CANCELLED>`\n\n### Workflow Overview\n\n| Phase | Name | Purpose | Outputs |\n|-------|------|---------|---------|\n| Init | Initialize | Create config, strategy (with research charter), state files | State files in `research/` |\n| Loop | Iterate | Dispatch @deep-research agent, evaluate convergence + quality guards, generate dashboard | iteration-NNN.md files, deep-research-dashboard.md |\n| Synth | Synthesize | Emit `research/resource-map.md` and compile final research/research.md | research/resource-map.md, research/research.md (17 sections) |\n| Save | Preserve | Refresh continuity update in canonical spec docs | canonical spec doc updated via `generate-context.js` |\n\n### Execution Modes\n\n| Mode | Invocation | Behavior |\n|------|-----------|----------|\n| `:auto` | `/deep:research:auto \"topic\"` | All iterations without approval |\n| `:confirm` | `/deep:research:confirm \"topic\"` | Multi-gate review at setup, iteration, and synthesis |\n| (default) | `/deep:research \"topic\"` | Ask user to choose mode during setup |\n\n### Memory Integration Before Starting\n\n- `memory_context({ input: topic, intent: \"understand\" })` -- Load prior research\n- Inject results into strategy.md \"Known Context\" section\n\n### Code Context Bootstrap\n\n- Use Code Graph (`code_graph_query`) to find relevant code examples before starting research\n- Query: 2-5 word concept descriptions related to the research topic\n- Inject discovered code patterns into strategy.md \"Known Context\" section alongside memory findings\n\n## 3. Results Display\n\n### Output Formats\n\n**Success:**\n```\nDeep research complete.\nIterations: [N] | Stop reason: [converged|max_iterations|all_answered]\nArtifacts: research/research.md, research/resource-map.md (unless `--no-resource-map`), [N] iteration files, continuity update in canonical spec docs refreshed\nReady for: /speckit:plan [feature-description]\nSTATUS=OK PATH=[spec-folder-path]\n```\n\n**Failure:**\n```\nError: [error description]  Phase: [phase name]\nSTATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"[message]\"\n```\n\n### Memory Integration After Completing\n\n- `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json [spec-folder]`\n- Verify that the canonical save routed continuity into the expected packet doc (decision-record.md / implementation-summary.md / handover.md)\n\n### Anchor Tags (Automatic)\n\n`ANCHOR:deep-research-[topic]`, `ANCHOR:findings`, `ANCHOR:convergence-report`\n\n### Error Handling\n\n| Error | Action |\n|-------|--------|\n| Agent dispatch timeout | Retry once with reduced scope, then mark timeout |\n| State file missing | Reconstruct from iteration files |\n| 3+ consecutive failures | Halt loop, enter synthesis with partial findings |\n| Memory save failure | Save to `scratch/` as backup |\n\n## 4. Next-Step Suggestions\n\n### Skill Reference\n\nFull protocol documentation: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md`\n\nKey references:\n- Loop protocol: `system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/loop-protocol.md`\n- Spec check protocol: `system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/spec-check-protocol.md`\n- State formats: `system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/state/state-format.md`\n- Convergence: `system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md`\n- Quick reference: `system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/guides/quick-reference.md`\n\nFor code review, see `deep-review` skill (`.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/SKILL.md`).\n\n### Examples\n\n```\n# Single-executor (default — unchanged)\n/deep:research:auto \"WebSocket reconnection strategies across browsers\"\n/deep:research:confirm \"distributed caching patterns for microservices\"\n/deep:research:auto \"API rate limiting approaches\" --max-iterations 5 --convergence 0.10\n\n# Fan-out: two CLI lineages in parallel (cli-opencode + cli-claude-code)\n/deep:research:auto \"caching patterns\" \\\n  --executor=cli-opencode --model=o4-mini --label= \\\n  --executor=cli-claude-code --model=claude-opus-4-8 --label=claude \\\n  --concurrency=2\n\n# Fan-out: native (sequential agent dispatches) + CLI lineages mixed\n/deep:research:auto \"distributed systems consensus\" \\\n  --executor=native --count=1 --label=native \\\n  --executor=cli-opencode --model=o4-mini --count=2 \\\n  --concurrency=3\n\n# Fan-out via JSON escape hatch\n/deep:research:auto \"WebRTC internals\" \\\n  --executors='[{\"kind\":\"cli-opencode\",\"model\":\"o4-mini\",\"label\":\"\",\"count\":3},{\"kind\":\"cli-claude-code\",\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-8\",\"label\":\"claude\",\"count\":2}]' \\\n  --concurrency=4\n```\n\n> **Note on native fan-out:** `--executor=native --count=N` dispatches N sequential `@deep-research` sub-agents with isolated artifact dirs. Not pooled. Best for count 1–3. For higher parallelism, use CLI executor kinds.\n\n### Next Steps\n\n> **Note:** Deep-research now anchors bounded findings back into `spec.md` through the generated findings fence while keeping `research/research.md` canonical.\n\n| Condition | Suggested Command | Reason |\n|-----------|-------------------|--------|\n| Research complete, ready to plan | `/speckit:plan [feature]` | Use findings for spec/plan |\n| Need more investigation | `/deep:research [new-topic]` | Another deep research session |\n| Need code/spec audit | `/deep:review [target]` | Iterative code review |\n| Want to refresh search support | `/memory:save [spec-folder]` | Refresh the indexed canonical spec document while canonical continuity stays in spec docs |\n\n### Key Differences (vs. single-pass research)\n\n- Iterative (multi-pass) vs. single-pass research\n- Dispatches `@deep-research` LEAF agent per iteration (fresh context each time)\n- Externalized state via JSONL + strategy files\n- Automatic convergence detection with quality guards (3 binary checks before STOP)\n- Persistent dashboard auto-generated each iteration for progress tracking\n- Negative knowledge (ruled-out directions) as first-class research output\n- Research charter (non-goals, stop conditions) validated at init\n- Does NOT proceed to implementation\n\n### Command Chain\n\n**Research path:** `/deep:research` → `/speckit:plan` → `/speckit:implement`\n**Review:** `/deep:review` → (if issues) `/speckit:plan` → `/speckit:implement`\n\n### Offline Optimization\n\nConvergence thresholds and recovery settings used by this command are a governed maintenance surface managed by the offline loop optimizer (042.004). The optimizer tunes deterministic numeric thresholds offline against real run traces and emits advisory-only candidate patches.\n\n**Key constraints:**\n- Optimization is offline only -- it does not run during live research sessions\n- Promotion is advisory-only until replay fixtures and behavioral suites exist\n- Prompt optimization is deferred future work (Phase 4b) and will use generated prompt packs, never direct agent markdown mutation\n\n**References:**\n- Optimizer configuration: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json`\n- Tunable thresholds: `convergenceThreshold`, `stuckThreshold`, `maxIterations`\n- Convergence reference: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md`","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":378,"totalLines":378,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-presentation.txt","time":{"start":1784624002040,"end":1784624002193}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a88b627636cb19a016a5f3381e0e481919cd13e2f7aad2028"}},"id":"prt_f83e133f2001gRFl4RrSa30cr3","sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","messageID":"msg_f83e0dfed001PnGWcNgq9WoThY"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784624002205,"sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_l944VdwDM8230rkSofA4j1Nh","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Convergence Detection Reference\n3: description: Live stop contract and navigation hub for deep-research convergence.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research convergence detection\"\n6:   - \"research stop contract\"\n7:   - \"research stopreason values\"\n8:   - \"research legal stop gates\"\n9:   - \"research convergence decision order\"\n10: importance_tier: important\n11: contextType: implementation\n12: version: 1.14.0.21\n13: ---\n14: \n15: # Convergence Detection Reference\n16: \n17: Live stop-contract hub for deep-research convergence and routed convergence references.\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n22: \n23: ### Purpose\n24: \n25: Keep the executable deep-research stop contract short enough to load during routing while pointing detailed signal, recovery, and graph behavior to focused references.\n26: \n27: ### When to Use\n28: \n29: Load this hub when deciding whether a deep-research loop should continue, recover, or stop.\n30: \n31: ### Key Sources\n32: \n33: - Command syntax: `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md`\n34: - Workflow algorithm: `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml` and `_confirm.yaml`\n35: - Signal details: `references/convergence/convergence-signals.md`\n36: - Recovery details: `references/convergence/convergence-recovery.md`\n37: - Graph stop gates: `references/convergence/convergence-graph.md`\n38: \n39: For iterative code review convergence, use `deep-review`. Review-mode algorithms and state are not part of the deep-research live contract.\n40: \n41: ### Live Decision Model\n42: \n43: Convergence decides whether the loop should continue, recover from a stuck state, or stop. A STOP candidate is not legal until the legal-stop gate bundle passes. Novelty math can nominate STOP; gates authorize it.\n44: \n45: The live deep-research algorithm evaluates:\n46: \n47: | Stage | Outcome |\n48: |-------|---------|\n49: | Hard stop and completion candidate | Stop unconditionally on max iterations; nominate STOP when all key questions are answered |\n50: | Stuck detection | Enter recovery after configured consecutive no-progress iterations |\n51: | Composite convergence | Nominate STOP when weighted signal score is above `0.60` |\n52: | Legal-stop gates | Allow or block the STOP candidate |\n53: | Graph gates | Add STOP-blocking graph checks when `graphEvents` exist |\n54: \n55: ### Convergence Modes\n56: \n57: The shared convergence runtime accepts four values. The workflow keeps hard terminal boundaries outside mode-specific convergence handling.\n58: \n59: | Mode | Live Behavior |\n60: |------|---------------|\n61: | `default` | Uses the normal full-history convergence signals and sends a legal STOP to synthesis. This is the fallback when no mode is supplied. |\n62: | `off` | Skips convergence-driven STOP candidates. Max iterations, pause or cancellation, manual stop, recovery halt, and unrecoverable error behavior remain active. |\n63: | `sliding-window` | Uses a bounded graph-novelty window, defaulting to 5 snapshots, while preserving the ordinary legal-stop and synthesis path. |\n64: | `divergent` | Computes convergence normally, but translates an eligible legal STOP into a three-seat direction-selection pivot and continues from the selected focus. |\n65: \n66: #### Divergent Pivot Contract\n67: \n68: Research pivots are eligible only when the workflow decision is `STOP` and the exact internal reason is `composite_converged` or `all_questions_answered`. The legal-stop and quality gates run before this branch. `maxIterationsReached`, `blockedStop`, `stuckRecovery`, `minIterationsNotReached`, `error`, `manualStop`, and `userPaused` are explicitly excluded. Max iterations, pause or cancellation, manual stop, and unrecoverable error therefore never dispatch a pivot Council.\n69: \n70: Each eligible pivot runs one native, in-process Council round with exactly three distinct seats: analytical, critical, and pragmatic. It does not use an external CLI. The transaction requires all three seat returns to be parse-valid and at least two seats to materially endorse the same candidate without a high-severity blocker. Research candidates come from persisted adjacent questions, contradiction or verification gaps, missing source classes, alternate evidence methods, and independent checks of recent findings. A completed pivot restores the selected candidate's focus and returns to the research loop; a failed pivot fails closed to synthesis.\n71: \n72: Every pivot dispatches three seats, so a run that pivots has proportionally higher model cost and duration than the same run under `default`, `off`, or `sliding-window`. Pivot evidence is isolated under `<artifactRoot>/divergent/pivots/<pivotId>/council/**`, including config, append-only state, three seat artifacts, deliberation, and report. This path is distinct from ordinary planning Council artifacts under a spec packet's `ai-council/**` tree.\n73: \n74: ---\n75: \n76: ## 2. STOP CONTRACT\n77: \n78: ### stopReason Values\n79: \n80: | Value | When It Is Used |\n81: |-------|-----------------|\n82: | `converged` | Legal-stop gates passed and the loop may exit normally |\n83: | `maxIterationsReached` | The loop hit the configured iteration cap |\n84: | `userPaused` | A pause sentinel or equivalent user pause request halted execution |\n85: | `blockedStop` | A STOP candidate was blocked by legal-stop or graph gates |\n86: | `stuckRecovery` | Stuck detection triggered or failed recovery |\n87: | `error` | The loop hit an unrecoverable workflow or state error |\n88: \n89: ### Legacy Stop Labels\n90: \n91: Legacy labels are normalized before persistence:\n92: \n93: | Legacy label or phrase | New `stopReason` |\n94: |------------------------|------------------|\n95: | `composite_converged` | `converged` |\n96: | `novelty below threshold` | `converged` |\n97: | `all_questions_answered` | `converged` |\n98: | `max_iterations_reached` | `maxIterationsReached` |\n99: | `paused` | `userPaused` |\n100: | `stuck_detected` | `stuckRecovery` |\n101: | `stuck_unrecoverable` | `stuckRecovery` |\n102: \n103: ---\n104: \n105: ## 3. LIVE ALGORITHM\n106: \n107: ### Decision Order\n108: \n109: ```text\n110: 1. If iteration count >= maxIterations, STOP with maxIterationsReached.\n111: 2. If all key questions have evidence-backed answers, nominate STOP.\n112: 3. If stuckCount >= stuckThreshold, enter stuck recovery.\n113: 4. Compute composite convergence signals.\n114: 5. If weighted stop score > 0.60, nominate STOP.\n115: 6. Evaluate legal-stop gates for every STOP candidate except hard max-iteration stop.\n116: 7. If graphEvents exist, evaluate graph-aware STOP blockers.\n117: 8. If gates pass, pivot for an eligible divergent reason or STOP normally; otherwise emit blockedStop and CONTINUE with recovery focus.\n118: ```\n119: \n120: ### Composite Signal Weights\n121: \n122: | Signal | Weight | Min Iterations | Measures |\n123: |--------|--------|----------------|----------|\n124: | Rolling Average | `0.30` | 3 evidence iterations | Recent information yield |\n125: | MAD Noise Floor | `0.35` | 4 evidence iterations | Signal vs noise in `newInfoRatio` |\n126: | Question Entropy | `0.35` | 1 key question | Evidence-backed question coverage |\n127: \n128: The weighted stop score is normalized over active signals. STOP is nominated only when the normalized score is greater than `0.60`. See `convergence-signals.md` for exact signal rules and reporting.\n129: \n130: ---\n131: \n132: ## 4. LEGAL STOP GATES\n133: \n134: Every non-terminal STOP candidate must pass the gate bundle before the workflow exits.\n135: \n136: | Gate | Rule | Failure |\n137: |------|------|---------|\n138: | Convergence Gate | Low novelty holds for the required consecutive evidence iterations | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n139: | Coverage Gate | Every key question has an evidence-backed answer | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n140: | Quality Gate | Source diversity, focus alignment, and no single weak-source dominance pass | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n141: | Graph Gate | When graph data exists, graph coverage has no STOP blockers | Emit `graph_convergence`/`blocked_stop`, continue |\n142: \n143: The reducer surfaces legal-stop evidence through the findings registry and dashboard. The JSONL event shapes live in `../state/state-jsonl.md`.\n144: \n145: ---\n146: \n147: ## 5. ROUTED REFERENCES\n148: \n149: | Resource | Use When |\n150: |----------|----------|\n151: | `convergence-signals.md` | Need scoring, `newInfoRatio`, `stuckCount`, MAD, entropy, report fields, or threshold tuning |\n152: | `convergence-recovery.md` | Need stuck recovery, recovery strategy selection, tiered errors, or escalation behavior |\n153: | `convergence-graph.md` | Need graph-aware STOP gates, graph convergence events, or coverage graph fallback behavior |\n154: | `convergence-reference-only.md` | Need future/reference-only models such as segment filtering, semantic convergence, or optimizer metadata |\n155: | `../state/state-jsonl.md` | Need JSONL event shapes persisted by the convergence workflow |\n156: | `../state/state-reducer-registry.md` | Need reducer-owned registry/dashboard fields derived from convergence |\n157: \n158: ---\n159: \n160: ## 6. NON-GOALS\n161: \n162: - Do not copy `deep-review` convergence into this skill. Use the `deep-review` references for severity-weighted review convergence.\n163: - Do not treat reference-only semantic or segment models as executable contracts.\n164: - Do not change the YAML workflow by editing this document. This document describes and routes the live contract; workflow changes require command/YAML work.\n\n(End of file - total 164 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Convergence Detection Reference\ndescription: Live stop contract and navigation hub for deep-research convergence.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research convergence detection\"\n  - \"research stop contract\"\n  - \"research stopreason values\"\n  - \"research legal stop gates\"\n  - \"research convergence decision order\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.21\n---\n\n# Convergence Detection Reference\n\nLive stop-contract hub for deep-research convergence and routed convergence references.\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md","text":"---\ntitle: Convergence Detection Reference\ndescription: Live stop contract and navigation hub for deep-research convergence.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research convergence detection\"\n  - \"research stop contract\"\n  - \"research stopreason values\"\n  - \"research legal stop gates\"\n  - \"research convergence decision order\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.21\n---\n\n# Convergence Detection Reference\n\nLive stop-contract hub for deep-research convergence and routed convergence references.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nKeep the executable deep-research stop contract short enough to load during routing while pointing detailed signal, recovery, and graph behavior to focused references.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this hub when deciding whether a deep-research loop should continue, recover, or stop.\n\n### Key Sources\n\n- Command syntax: `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md`\n- Workflow algorithm: `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml` and `_confirm.yaml`\n- Signal details: `references/convergence/convergence-signals.md`\n- Recovery details: `references/convergence/convergence-recovery.md`\n- Graph stop gates: `references/convergence/convergence-graph.md`\n\nFor iterative code review convergence, use `deep-review`. Review-mode algorithms and state are not part of the deep-research live contract.\n\n### Live Decision Model\n\nConvergence decides whether the loop should continue, recover from a stuck state, or stop. A STOP candidate is not legal until the legal-stop gate bundle passes. Novelty math can nominate STOP; gates authorize it.\n\nThe live deep-research algorithm evaluates:\n\n| Stage | Outcome |\n|-------|---------|\n| Hard stop and completion candidate | Stop unconditionally on max iterations; nominate STOP when all key questions are answered |\n| Stuck detection | Enter recovery after configured consecutive no-progress iterations |\n| Composite convergence | Nominate STOP when weighted signal score is above `0.60` |\n| Legal-stop gates | Allow or block the STOP candidate |\n| Graph gates | Add STOP-blocking graph checks when `graphEvents` exist |\n\n### Convergence Modes\n\nThe shared convergence runtime accepts four values. The workflow keeps hard terminal boundaries outside mode-specific convergence handling.\n\n| Mode | Live Behavior |\n|------|---------------|\n| `default` | Uses the normal full-history convergence signals and sends a legal STOP to synthesis. This is the fallback when no mode is supplied. |\n| `off` | Skips convergence-driven STOP candidates. Max iterations, pause or cancellation, manual stop, recovery halt, and unrecoverable error behavior remain active. |\n| `sliding-window` | Uses a bounded graph-novelty window, defaulting to 5 snapshots, while preserving the ordinary legal-stop and synthesis path. |\n| `divergent` | Computes convergence normally, but translates an eligible legal STOP into a three-seat direction-selection pivot and continues from the selected focus. |\n\n#### Divergent Pivot Contract\n\nResearch pivots are eligible only when the workflow decision is `STOP` and the exact internal reason is `composite_converged` or `all_questions_answered`. The legal-stop and quality gates run before this branch. `maxIterationsReached`, `blockedStop`, `stuckRecovery`, `minIterationsNotReached`, `error`, `manualStop`, and `userPaused` are explicitly excluded. Max iterations, pause or cancellation, manual stop, and unrecoverable error therefore never dispatch a pivot Council.\n\nEach eligible pivot runs one native, in-process Council round with exactly three distinct seats: analytical, critical, and pragmatic. It does not use an external CLI. The transaction requires all three seat returns to be parse-valid and at least two seats to materially endorse the same candidate without a high-severity blocker. Research candidates come from persisted adjacent questions, contradiction or verification gaps, missing source classes, alternate evidence methods, and independent checks of recent findings. A completed pivot restores the selected candidate's focus and returns to the research loop; a failed pivot fails closed to synthesis.\n\nEvery pivot dispatches three seats, so a run that pivots has proportionally higher model cost and duration than the same run under `default`, `off`, or `sliding-window`. Pivot evidence is isolated under `<artifactRoot>/divergent/pivots/<pivotId>/council/**`, including config, append-only state, three seat artifacts, deliberation, and report. This path is distinct from ordinary planning Council artifacts under a spec packet's `ai-council/**` tree.\n\n---\n\n## 2. STOP CONTRACT\n\n### stopReason Values\n\n| Value | When It Is Used |\n|-------|-----------------|\n| `converged` | Legal-stop gates passed and the loop may exit normally |\n| `maxIterationsReached` | The loop hit the configured iteration cap |\n| `userPaused` | A pause sentinel or equivalent user pause request halted execution |\n| `blockedStop` | A STOP candidate was blocked by legal-stop or graph gates |\n| `stuckRecovery` | Stuck detection triggered or failed recovery |\n| `error` | The loop hit an unrecoverable workflow or state error |\n\n### Legacy Stop Labels\n\nLegacy labels are normalized before persistence:\n\n| Legacy label or phrase | New `stopReason` |\n|------------------------|------------------|\n| `composite_converged` | `converged` |\n| `novelty below threshold` | `converged` |\n| `all_questions_answered` | `converged` |\n| `max_iterations_reached` | `maxIterationsReached` |\n| `paused` | `userPaused` |\n| `stuck_detected` | `stuckRecovery` |\n| `stuck_unrecoverable` | `stuckRecovery` |\n\n---\n\n## 3. LIVE ALGORITHM\n\n### Decision Order\n\n```text\n1. If iteration count >= maxIterations, STOP with maxIterationsReached.\n2. If all key questions have evidence-backed answers, nominate STOP.\n3. If stuckCount >= stuckThreshold, enter stuck recovery.\n4. Compute composite convergence signals.\n5. If weighted stop score > 0.60, nominate STOP.\n6. Evaluate legal-stop gates for every STOP candidate except hard max-iteration stop.\n7. If graphEvents exist, evaluate graph-aware STOP blockers.\n8. If gates pass, pivot for an eligible divergent reason or STOP normally; otherwise emit blockedStop and CONTINUE with recovery focus.\n```\n\n### Composite Signal Weights\n\n| Signal | Weight | Min Iterations | Measures |\n|--------|--------|----------------|----------|\n| Rolling Average | `0.30` | 3 evidence iterations | Recent information yield |\n| MAD Noise Floor | `0.35` | 4 evidence iterations | Signal vs noise in `newInfoRatio` |\n| Question Entropy | `0.35` | 1 key question | Evidence-backed question coverage |\n\nThe weighted stop score is normalized over active signals. STOP is nominated only when the normalized score is greater than `0.60`. See `convergence-signals.md` for exact signal rules and reporting.\n\n---\n\n## 4. LEGAL STOP GATES\n\nEvery non-terminal STOP candidate must pass the gate bundle before the workflow exits.\n\n| Gate | Rule | Failure |\n|------|------|---------|\n| Convergence Gate | Low novelty holds for the required consecutive evidence iterations | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n| Coverage Gate | Every key question has an evidence-backed answer | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n| Quality Gate | Source diversity, focus alignment, and no single weak-source dominance pass | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n| Graph Gate | When graph data exists, graph coverage has no STOP blockers | Emit `graph_convergence`/`blocked_stop`, continue |\n\nThe reducer surfaces legal-stop evidence through the findings registry and dashboard. The JSONL event shapes live in `../state/state-jsonl.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. ROUTED REFERENCES\n\n| Resource | Use When |\n|----------|----------|\n| `convergence-signals.md` | Need scoring, `newInfoRatio`, `stuckCount`, MAD, entropy, report fields, or threshold tuning |\n| `convergence-recovery.md` | Need stuck recovery, recovery strategy selection, tiered errors, or escalation behavior |\n| `convergence-graph.md` | Need graph-aware STOP gates, graph convergence events, or coverage graph fallback behavior |\n| `convergence-reference-only.md` | Need future/reference-only models such as segment filtering, semantic convergence, or optimizer metadata |\n| `../state/state-jsonl.md` | Need JSONL event shapes persisted by the convergence workflow |\n| `../state/state-reducer-registry.md` | Need reducer-owned registry/dashboard fields derived from convergence |\n\n---\n\n## 6. NON-GOALS\n\n- Do not copy `deep-review` convergence into this skill. Use the `deep-review` references for severity-weighted review convergence.\n- Do not treat reference-only semantic or segment models as executable contracts.\n- Do not change the YAML workflow by editing this document. This document describes and routes the live contract; workflow changes require command/YAML work.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":164,"totalLines":164,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md","time":{"start":1784624002072,"end":1784624002202}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a88b627636cb19a016a5f3381e1108191b19d36ca3f2307d0"}},"id":"prt_f83e13412001UjSaFajt0DWJJW","sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","messageID":"msg_f83e0dfed001PnGWcNgq9WoThY"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784624002226,"sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_nxxLeIEwExoitgq24OdVTk01","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2: # DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n3: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n4: # YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n5: # - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n6: #   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n7: #   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n8: # - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n9: #   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n10: #   free-form narrative prose.\n11: # - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n12: #   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n13: #\n14: # GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n15: # - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n16: #   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n17: #   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n18: #   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n19: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n20: role: Deep Research Loop Manager\n21: purpose: Iterative deep research with convergence detection\n22: action: Run deep-research loop from initialization through synthesis\n23: operating_mode:\n24:   workflow: iterative_loop\n25:   workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n26:   workflow_execution: autonomous\n27:   approvals: none\n28:   tracking: progressive_research_state\n29:   validation: convergence_detection\n30: \n31: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n32: # OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n33: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n34: operating_principles:\n35:   core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n36:   approach: \"Dispatch focused agent, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n37:   mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files\"\n38: \n39: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n40: # USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n41: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n42: user_inputs:\n43:   research_topic: \"[RESEARCH_TOPIC] - Topic to investigate deeply. REQUIRED.\"\n44:   spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path. REQUIRED.\"\n45:   max_iterations: \"[MAX_ITERATIONS] - Maximum loop iterations. Default: 10.\"\n46:   convergence_threshold: \"[CONVERGENCE_THRESHOLD] - Stop threshold. Default: 0.05.\"\n47:   convergence_mode: \"[default|off|sliding-window|divergent] - Convergence policy modifier. Default: default.\"\n48: \n49: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n50: # CONTEXT LOADING\n51: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n52: context_loading:\n53:   trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n54:   purpose: \"Load prior research context for the topic and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n55:   mcp_integration:\n56:     tool: memory_context\n57:     note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n58:     parameters: { input: \"{research_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n59:   when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n60:   behavior:\n61:     if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n62:     if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n63: \n64: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n65: # SKILL REFERENCE\n66: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n67: skill_reference:\n68:   skill: system-deep-loop\n69:   skill_md: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md\n70:   references:\n71:     loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/loop-protocol.md\n72:     spec_check_protocol: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/spec-check-protocol.md\n73:     state_format: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/state/state-format.md\n74:     convergence: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md\n75:   templates:\n76:     config: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-config.json\n77:     strategy: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-strategy.md\n78: \n79: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n80: # AGENT CONFIGURATION\n81: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n82: agent_config:\n83:   agent: deep-research\n84:   agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-research.md\"\n85:   # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n86:   model: opus\n87:   leaf_only: true\n88:   tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, WebFetch]\n89:   mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n90:   tool_call_budget: { target: 8, max: 12 }\n91: \n92: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n93: # STATE FILE PATHS\n94: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n95: state_paths:\n96:   # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n97:   # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep root-local\n98:   # research/ and child phases keep local research/ packet directories.\n99:   packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n100:   config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json\"\n101:   state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n102:   status_ledger: \"{artifact_dir}/orchestration-status.log\"\n103:   strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-strategy.md\"\n104:   registry: \"{artifact_dir}/findings-registry.json\"\n105:   dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-dashboard.md\"\n106:   pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-pause\"\n107:   run_now_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-run-now\"\n108:   lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research.lock\"\n109:   prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n110:   iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n111:   iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n112:   # Per-iteration structured delta stream (one file per iteration) — complement to the\n113:   # canonical state_log append. The delta file MUST contain at least one record whose\n114:   # `type === \"iteration\"` so the reducer can rehydrate iteration state after a partial\n115:   # run. Variants like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer; the\n116:   # post_dispatch_validate step enforces the canonical type below.\n117:   delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n118:   delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n119:   research_output: \"{artifact_dir}/research.md\"\n120:   resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n121:   archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n122:   synthesis_snapshot_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/synthesis-v{generation}.md\"\n123: \n124: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n125: # WORKFLOW\n126: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n127: workflow:\n128: \n129:   step_resolve_artifact_root:\n130:     description: \"Resolve artifact directory — use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n131:     note: \"Root specs keep research artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/research/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/research/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/research_archive/{packet}/.\"\n132:     branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n133:     if_present:\n134:       bind:\n135:         artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n136:         artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n137:         artifact_subfolder: null\n138:         artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n139:     if_absent:\n140:       command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('./.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'research')));\\\"\"\n141:       outputs:\n142:         - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local research owner directory\"\n143:         - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n144:         - artifact_dir: \"Resolved research packet directory for this target\"\n145:         - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local research archive directory for this target\"\n146: \n147:   step_fanout_spawn:\n148:     description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n149:     skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n150:     instructions: |\n151:       Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n152:       isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n153:       fanout-run.cjs owns native and CLI lineage execution; native is run through the\n154:       deep/research command surface with config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir so the LEAF\n155:       deep-research agent is used only for individual iterations, never as a full-loop\n156:       sub-agent or pasted phase-running prompt.\n157:       After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n158:       phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n159:       phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n160:     sub_steps:\n161:       step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n162:         description: \"Spawn all native and CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n163:         skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors\"\n164:         command: |\n165:           node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n166:             --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n167:             --loop-type research \\\n168:             --research-topic \"{research_topic}\" \\\n169:             --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n170:             --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir} \\\n171:             --convergence-threshold {convergence_threshold}\n172:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n173:         wait_for_completion: true\n174: \n175:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n176:   # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n177:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n178:   phase_init:\n179:     purpose: Create all state files for the research session\n180:     steps:\n181: \n182:       step_preflight_contract:\n183:         action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n184:         verify:\n185:           - required_values_present: [research_topic, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold, convergence_mode]\n186:           - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n187:           - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n188:           - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n189:         on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n190: \n191:       step_create_directories:\n192:         action: \"Create spec folder and research packet directories if they don't exist\"\n193:         command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n194: \n195:       step_detect_resource_map:\n196:         action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist the flag and seed Known Context\"\n197:         inspect:\n198:           - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n199:         classify:\n200:           present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n201:           absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n202:         outputs:\n203:           - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n204:           - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: summarize the map by section with entry counts across READMEs, Documents, Commands, Agents, Skills, Specs, Scripts, Tests, Config, and Meta, plus a one-line theme summary for each section. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n205: \n206:       step_resolve_canonical_names:\n207:         action: \"Resolve canonical research packet artifact names before classification\"\n208:         inspect_legacy:\n209:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/config.json\"\n210:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/state.jsonl\"\n211:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/strategy.md\"\n212:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dashboard.md\"\n213:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/.pause\"\n214:         migration_policy: \"dual-read / single-write for 4 weeks\"\n215:         on_legacy_read:\n216:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"migration\",\"legacyPath\":\"{legacy_path}\",\"canonicalPath\":\"{canonical_path}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n217: \n218:       step_acquire_lock:\n219:         action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n220:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n221:         on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-research run already holds this packet.\"\n222:         note: \"Uses the promoted runtime/ loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n223:         # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n224:         # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n225:         on_halt:\n226:           action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n227:           applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\", \"step_preinit_spec_branch.conflict-detected\"]\n228:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n229:         on_cancel:\n230:           action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n231:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n232:         on_workflow_exit:\n233:           action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n234:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n235: \n236:       step_classify_session:\n237:         action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n238:         inspect:\n239:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n240:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n241:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n242:         classify:\n243:           fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n244:           resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on topic/spec folder; missing wait-checkpoint fields are read as nextRunAt:null and remainingDelayMs:null\"\n245:           completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n246:           invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n247:         outputs:\n248:           - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n249:         on_resume:\n250:           # T-YML-DPR-01 / R50-001: Resume is a WRITE-PATH. Produces `iteration-NNN.md` + JSONL appends.\n251:           # Paired with T-DOC-03 Gate 3 trigger addition (resume, save context, save memory, /memory:save).\n252:           gate3_classification: write-path\n253:           gate3_rationale: \"resume produces iteration-NNN.md writes and JSONL state-log appends\"\n254:           log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n255:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n256:           skip_to: phase_loop\n257:         on_restart:\n258:           action: \"Archive the current research packet under the root-level research_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n259:           command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n260:           set:\n261:             lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n262:             parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n263:             generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n264:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n265:           skip_to: step_create_config\n266:         note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-research/references/protocol/loop-protocol.md §Lifecycle Branch Contract for the one-session contract.\"\n267:         on_completed_session:\n268:           log: \"Prior session already completed. Do not route directly to synthesis; archive the completed research/ tree or start a fresh packet instead.\"\n269:           halt: true\n270:           message: \"Completed deep-research packet detected. Archive or replace the existing research/ tree before starting a new session.\"\n271:         on_invalid_state:\n272:           halt: true\n273:           message: \"Existing deep-research state is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid research packet before continuing.\"\n274:         on_fresh:\n275:           action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n276: \n277:       step_resolve_session_id:\n278:         action: \"Resolve init session id from caller when supplied, else preserve the auto-generated fallback\"\n279:         branch_on: \"session_id\"\n280:         if_present:\n281:           bind:\n282:             session_id_init: \"{session_id}\"\n283:         if_absent:\n284:           bind:\n285:             session_id_init: \"{AUTO_SESSION_ID}\"\n286: \n287:       step_create_config:\n288:         action: \"Create deep-research-config.json from template\"\n289:         template: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-config.json\n290:         populate:\n291:           topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n292:           maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n293:           minIterations: 3\n294:           # Semantic: newInfoRatio with negative-knowledge emphasis. See SKILL.md §\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n295:           convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n296:           antiConvergence.convergenceMode: \"{convergence_mode}\"\n297:           antiConvergence.divergent: {}\n298:           stuckThreshold: 3\n299:           minIdeaObservations: 2\n300:           maxDurationMinutes: 120\n301:           specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n302:           resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n303:           # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-research.md:73 (default true; false when flag is set).\n304:           # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n305:           resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n306:           createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n307:           status: \"initialized\"\n308:           executionMode: \"auto\"\n309:           lineage.sessionId: \"{session_id_init}\"\n310:           lineage.parentSessionId: null\n311:           lineage.lineageMode: \"new\"\n312:           lineage.generation: 1\n313:           lineage.continuedFromRun: null\n314:           nextRunAt: null\n315:           remainingDelayMs: null\n316:         output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n317: \n318:       step_create_state_log:\n319:         action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record\"\n320:         # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n321:         content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"{research_topic}\",\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"minIterations\":3,\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"antiConvergence\":{\"convergenceMode\":\"{convergence_mode}\",\"divergent\":{}},\"minIdeaObservations\":2,\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\",\"nextRunAt\":null,\"remainingDelayMs\":null}'\n322:         output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n323: \n324:       step_create_strategy:\n325:         action: \"Create strategy file from template with initial questions\"\n326:         template: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-strategy.md\n327:         populate:\n328:           topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n329:           key_questions: \"Derive 3-5 key questions from the research topic\"\n330:           known_context: \"None\"\n331:           known_context_summary: \"None\"\n332:           max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n333:           convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n334:         output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n335: \n336:       step_create_registry:\n337:         action: \"Initialize reducer-owned findings registry\"\n338:         content: '{\"openQuestions\":[],\"resolvedQuestions\":[],\"keyFindings\":[],\"ruledOutDirections\":[],\"metrics\":{\"iterationsCompleted\":0,\"openQuestions\":0,\"resolvedQuestions\":0,\"keyFindings\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0,\"coverageBySources\":{}}}'\n339:         output: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n340: \n341:       step_enrich_strategy_context:\n342:         action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n343:         condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n344:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n345:         note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n346: \n347:       step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n348:         action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n349:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n350:         note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n351: \n352:       step_detect_spec_present:\n353:         action: \"Classify late-INIT spec.md state after the durable research packet exists\"\n354:         inspect:\n355:           - \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n356:           - \"{state_paths.lock_file}\"\n357:         classify:\n358:           no-spec: \"spec.md is absent before any pre-init mutation\"\n359:           spec-present: \"spec.md exists and approved host anchors are available for bounded mutation\"\n360:           spec-just-created-by-this-run: \"spec.md already carries this run's DR seed markers and should not be reseeded\"\n361:           conflict-detected: \"missing host anchor, duplicate markers, or generated-block ambiguity makes mutation unsafe\"\n362:         outputs:\n363:           - folder_state: \"no-spec | spec-present | spec-just-created-by-this-run | conflict-detected\"\n364:           - normalized_topic: \"Trim, lowercase, and collapse whitespace in research_topic before dedupe checks\"\n365:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_check_result\",\"folder_state\":\"{folder_state}\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"lockPath\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n366: \n367:       step_preinit_spec_branch:\n368:         action: \"Run the bounded pre-init spec branch required by spec_check_protocol\"\n369:         protocol_reference: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/spec-check-protocol.md\"\n370:         branches:\n371:           no-spec:\n372:             create: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n373:             seed_markers:\n374:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n375:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n376:             requirements_host: \"Seed Requirements from the research ask without broadening scope\"\n377:             scope_host: \"Seed Scope from the research ask without inventing implementation details\"\n378:             set:\n379:               folder_state: \"spec-just-created-by-this-run\"\n380:               validate_spec_doc: true\n381:             append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_seed_created\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-just-created-by-this-run\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Requirements\",\"Scope\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Seeded Level 1 spec.md from research topic with DR seed markers.\",\"seed_markers\":[\"DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS\",\"DR-SEED:SCOPE\"],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n382:           spec-present:\n383:             edit: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n384:             set:\n385:               validate_spec_doc: true\n386:             idempotency_check:\n387:               host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n388:               normalized_match: \"Normalize the existing anchor text by lowercasing, stripping punctuation, collapsing whitespace, and trimming before comparing with {normalized_topic}.\"\n389:               if_match:\n390:                 skip_append: true\n391:                 append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_deduped\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Skipped duplicate pre-init topic append because normalized topic already exists in Open Questions.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n392:               if_no_match:\n393:                 append_only:\n394:                   - host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n395:                     content: \"Add the normalized research topic only if it is not already present.\"\n396:                   - host_anchor: \"Research Context\"\n397:                     content: \"Add a bounded note that deep-research is active for this topic and that research/research.md remains canonical.\"\n398:                 append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_added\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\",\"Research Context\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Appended bounded pre-init research context for the normalized topic.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n399:           spec-just-created-by-this-run:\n400:             verify_markers:\n401:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n402:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n403:             set:\n404:               validate_spec_doc: false\n405:             note: \"Treat already-seeded spec.md as a no-op guard and continue.\"\n406:           conflict-detected:\n407:             append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation_conflict\",\"folder_state\":\"conflict-detected\",\"reason\":\"Pre-init spec.md mutation is ambiguous or unsafe.\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n408:             halt: true\n409: \n410:       step_validate_preinit_spec_doc:\n411:         action: \"Run targeted strict validation after any deep-research pre-init spec.md mutation\"\n412:         condition: \"validate_spec_doc\"\n413:         command: \"SPECKIT_RULES=FRONTMATTER_VALID,LEVEL_DECLARED,TEMPLATE_SOURCE,TEMPLATE_HEADERS,PLACEHOLDER_FILLED,SECTIONS_PRESENT,ANCHORS_VALID,SPEC_DOC_INTEGRITY,TOC_POLICY bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh {spec_folder} --strict\"\n414:         note: \"This enforces the authored-spec markdown structural contract without applying full-packet required-file or completeness checks to workflow-owned research artifacts. It uses the Node validation orchestrator, whose strict path was measured at about 108ms for a fresh Level 3 packet on the local harness.\"\n415: \n416:       step_telemetry_heartbeat_started:\n417:         action: \"Emit a single-loop started row in the orchestration status ledger\"\n418:         skip_when: \"config.fanout is present\"\n419:         canonical_lifecycle_event: \"iteration_start\"\n420:         command: |\n421:           node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n422:           import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n423: \n424:           import { appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts';\n425:           import observabilityEvents from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/observability-events.cjs';\n426: \n427:           const { appendObservabilityEvent } = observabilityEvents;\n428:           const config = JSON.parse(readFileSync('{state_paths.config}', 'utf8'));\n429:           const timestamp = '{ISO_8601_NOW}';\n430:           const sessionId = String(config.lineage?.sessionId ?? '{AUTO_SESSION_ID}');\n431:           const generation = Number(config.lineage?.generation ?? 1);\n432:           const observabilityPath = '{state_paths.packet_dir}/observability-events.jsonl';\n433:           const row = {\n434:             event: 'started',\n435:             label: 'single',\n436:             at: timestamp,\n437:             duration_ms: 0,\n438:             loop_type: 'research',\n439:             sessionId,\n440:             generation,\n441:             gauges: { iterations: 0, elapsed_ms: 0, score: 0 },\n442:           };\n443: \n444:           const appended = appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic('{state_paths.status_ledger}', row, {\n445:             diffData: { event: row.event, label: row.label, sessionId, generation, gauges: { iterations: 0, score: 0 } },\n446:             diffField: 'state_hash',\n447:           });\n448:           if (appended) {\n449:             try {\n450:               appendObservabilityEvent(observabilityPath, row, {\n451:                 producer: 'deep-research-auto',\n452:                 stream: 'single-loop-telemetry',\n453:                 subject: { label: row.label, sessionId, generation },\n454:                 event: row.event,\n455:                 status: 'running',\n456:               });\n457:             } catch {}\n458:           }\n459:           EOF\n460:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n461:         outputs:\n462:           - status_ledger_started: \"A fan-out-shaped status row with label single and event started\"\n463: \n464:       step_init_complete:\n465:         log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, and strategy files created.\"\n466:         set: { current_iteration: 1, current_segment: 1, stuck_count: 0 }\n467: \n468:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n469:   # PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n470:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n471:   phase_loop:\n472:     purpose: Dispatch agent iterations until convergence\n473:     repeat: true\n474:     max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n475:     steps:\n476: \n477:       step_read_state:\n478:         action: \"Read current state from JSONL and strategy\"\n479:         read:\n480:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n481:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n482:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n483:         extract:\n484:           - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n485:           - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n486:           - current_segment: \"Latest segment_start event segment, else 1\"\n487:           - last_newInfoRatio: \"Extract newInfoRatio from last iteration record\"\n488:           - last_focus: \"Extract focus from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n489:           - ratio_prev: \"Extract newInfoRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n490:           - ratio_latest: \"Extract newInfoRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n491:           - next_focus: \"Extract 'Next Focus' section from strategy.md\"\n492:           - remaining_questions: \"Count unchecked items in 'Key Questions'\"\n493:           - remaining_questions_list: \"List unchecked key questions from strategy.md\"\n494:           - carried_forward_open_questions: \"Extract 'Carried-Forward Open Questions' section from strategy.md, else '[None yet]'\"\n495:           - answered_count: \"Count answered questions from strategy.md\"\n496:           - total_questions: \"Count total questions tracked in strategy.md\"\n497:           - resource_map_present: \"Extract boolean from deep-research-config.json, default false\"\n498:           - resource_map_prompt_line: \"If resource_map_present is true, return 'Resource map: prior-inventoried files are listed in {spec_folder}/resource-map.md; treat them as the exclusion set when hunting for net-new files; flag only missed-from-map candidates as gaps.' Else return 'Resource map: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.'\"\n499:           - memory_context_prompt_line: \"If a refreshed memory context summary exists from the previous iteration, return 'Memory context refresh: {summary}'. Else use prior_context_summary from startup when available; otherwise return 'Memory context refresh: none loaded yet.'\"\n500:           - least_explored: \"First unanswered question not covered by the most recent iteration focus, else first unanswered question\"\n501:           - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: focus (ratio)'\"\n502:           - latest_status: \"Extract status from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n503:           - nextRunAt: \"Extract nullable nextRunAt from deep-research-config.json, default null\"\n504:           - remainingDelayMs: \"Extract nullable remainingDelayMs from deep-research-config.json, default null\"\n505:           - min_iterations_present: \"Boolean true when deep-research-config.json has a numeric minIterations field\"\n506:           - min_iterations_missing_warning: \"Boolean true when minIterations is missing; use no floor and log a warning so older configs keep prior stop behavior\"\n507:           - min_iterations_raw: \"Extract numeric minIterations from deep-research-config.json when present, default 0\"\n508:           - effective_min_iterations: \"Clamp min_iterations_raw to the inclusive range 0..max_iterations; if min_iterations_raw exceeds max_iterations, use max_iterations\"\n509:           - min_iterations_clamped: \"Boolean true when min_iterations_raw > max_iterations\"\n510:           - min_iterations_guard_already_passed: \"Boolean true when state_log already contains event == 'min_iterations_guard_pass'\"\n511:           - convergence_mode: \"Extract antiConvergence.convergenceMode when it is one of 'default', 'off', 'sliding-window', or 'divergent'; default to 'default'\"\n512:           - convergence_mode_warning: \"Boolean true when antiConvergence.convergenceMode is present with an unsupported value; use 'default'\"\n513:           - rejected_patterns_count: \"Read registry.rejectedPatterns length when registry exists, else 0\"\n514:           - rejected_candidate_matches: \"Read registry.suppressedCandidates when registry exists, else []\"\n515:           - rejected_pattern_fuzzy_threshold: \"Read config.rejectedPatternFuzzyThreshold when present, else 0.85\"\n516:           - min_idea_observations: \"Read config.minIdeaObservations when present, default 2; clamp to 1..10\"\n517:           - observed_ideas_count: \"Read registry.observedIdeas length when registry exists, else 0\"\n518:           - promoted_ideas_count: \"Read registry.promotedIdeas length when registry exists, else 0\"\n519:           - promoted_ideas_list: \"Read registry.promotedIdeas idea text in rank order when registry exists, else []\"\n520:           - suppressed_ideas_count: \"Read registry.suppressedIdeas length when registry exists, else 0\"\n521:           - pivot_lineage: \"Summarize registry.divergence.completed and registry.divergence.overrides with pivot ids, source iterations, and selected focus; else 'none yet'\"\n522:           - saturated_directions: \"List registry.divergence.saturatedDirections; else 'none yet'\"\n523: \n524:       step_run_now_check:\n525:         action: \"Detect and consume a one-shot run-now sentinel before pause/convergence/dispatch\"\n526:         command: |\n527:           node <<'EOF'\n528:           const { appendFileSync, existsSync, renameSync, unlinkSync } = require('node:fs');\n529: \n530:           const stateLogPath = \"{state_paths.state_log}\";\n531:           const sentinelPath = \"{state_paths.run_now_sentinel}\";\n532:           const pausePath = \"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\";\n533:           const timestamp = \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\";\n534:           const sessionId = \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\";\n535:           const generation = Number(\"{config.lineage.generation}\");\n536:           const run = Number(\"{current_iteration}\");\n537: \n538:           function append(event) {\n539:             appendFileSync(\n540:               stateLogPath,\n541:               `${JSON.stringify({\n542:                 type: \"event\",\n543:                 mode: \"research\",\n544:                 run,\n545:                 timestamp,\n546:                 sessionId,\n547:                 generation,\n548:                 ...event,\n549:               })}\\n`,\n550:               \"utf8\",\n551:             );\n552:           }\n553: \n554:           if (existsSync(sentinelPath)) {\n555:             append({ event: \"run_now_requested\", sentinelPath });\n556:             if (existsSync(pausePath)) {\n557:               append({\n558:                 event: \"run_now_rejected\",\n559:                 reason: \"loop_paused\",\n560:                 sentinelPath,\n561:                 pauseSentinelPath: pausePath,\n562:               });\n563:             } else {\n564:               const claimPath = `${sentinelPath}.consuming.${process.pid}.${Date.now()}`;\n565:               try {\n566:                 renameSync(sentinelPath, claimPath);\n567:                 unlinkSync(claimPath);\n568:                 append({\n569:                   event: \"run_now_accepted\",\n570:                   sentinelPath,\n571:                   dispatchEvent: \"iteration_start\",\n572:                 });\n573:               } catch (error) {\n574:                 if (!error || error.code !== \"ENOENT\") {\n575:                   throw error;\n576:                 }\n577:               }\n578:             }\n579:           }\n580:           EOF\n581:         outputs:\n582:           - run_now_requested: \"Emitted when {state_paths.run_now_sentinel} exists at the loop boundary\"\n583:           - run_now_accepted: \"Emitted after the sentinel is atomically renamed and deleted before dispatch\"\n584:           - run_now_rejected: \"Emitted with reason loop_paused when pause takes precedence; sentinel remains present\"\n585: \n586:       step_check_pause_sentinel:\n587:         action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n588:         check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n589:         if_exists:\n590:           log_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n591:           message: \"Research paused. Delete research/.deep-research-pause to resume.\"\n592:           halt: true\n593:         if_not_exists:\n594:           proceed: true\n595: \n596:       step_validate_convergence_config:\n597:         action: \"Validate convergence floor settings when loading config\"\n598:         if_min_iterations_missing:\n599:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"config_warning\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"field\":\"minIterations\",\"fallback\":0,\"message\":\"minIterations missing; using no convergence floor for backward compatibility.\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n600:           log: \"minIterations missing; using no convergence floor for backward compatibility.\"\n601:         if_min_iterations_clamped:\n602:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"config_warning\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"field\":\"minIterations\",\"configured\":{min_iterations_raw},\"effective\":{effective_min_iterations},\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"message\":\"minIterations exceeds maxIterations; clamping to the hard cap.\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n603:           log: \"minIterations exceeds maxIterations; clamping to the hard cap.\"\n604:         if_convergence_mode_invalid:\n605:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"config_warning\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"field\":\"convergenceMode\",\"fallback\":\"default\",\"message\":\"Unsupported convergenceMode; using default convergence behavior.\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n606:           log: \"Unsupported convergenceMode; using default convergence behavior.\"\n607: \n608:       step_graph_convergence:\n609:         action: \"Evaluate coverage-graph convergence before the inline 3-signal vote and persist the graph decision snapshot\"\n610:         bash: 'node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"research\" --session-id \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\" --convergence-mode \"{convergence_mode}\"'\n611:         note: \"Run before the inline vote. STOP from the inline 3-signal vote is allowed only when the graph decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\"\n612:         outputs:\n613:           - graph_decision: \"Tool decision value (CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED), else null when unavailable\"\n614:           - graph_decision_json: \"JSON-encoded graph decision string, else null\"\n615:           - graph_signals_json: \"Tool signals object, else {}\"\n616:           - graph_blockers_json: \"Tool blockers array, else []\"\n617:           - graph_trace_json: \"Tool trace payload, else []\"\n618:           - graph_convergence_score: \"signals.blendedScore when present, else the best available graph score, else 0\"\n619:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"graph_convergence\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"decision\":{graph_decision_json},\"signals\":{graph_signals_json},\"blockers\":{graph_blockers_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n620: \n621:       step_check_convergence:\n622:         action: \"Evaluate stop conditions and combine the inline 3-signal vote with graph convergence\"\n623:         algorithm: |\n624:           1. if iteration_count >= max_iterations: STOP (maxIterationsReached). This terminal cap bypasses quality-guard overrides; record failed guards/blockers as synthesis evidence instead of continuing.\n625:           2. if stuck_count >= config.stuckThreshold: STUCK_RECOVERY\n626:           3. if convergence_mode == \"off\": skip convergence stop candidates and continue unless a terminal cap, pause sentinel, or recovery halt has already fired.\n627:           4. if remaining_questions == 0: STOP (all_questions_answered)\n628:           5. GRAPH-ASSISTED COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE:\n629:                step_graph_convergence already recorded graph_decision, graph_signals_json, graph_blockers_json, and graph_convergence_score for this run.\n630:                The existing inline 3-signal vote still computes the inline STOP candidate and is not replaced.\n631:                signals = []\n632:                Filter: exclude iterations where status == thought from signal inputs (use only evidence iterations)\n633:                a) Rolling average (w=0.30, needs 3+ iterations):\n634:                   avg = mean(last 3 newInfoRatios)\n635:                   stop if avg < convergence_threshold\n636:                b) MAD noise floor (w=0.35, needs 4+ iterations):\n637:                   noiseFloor = MAD(all ratios) * 1.4826\n638:                   stop if latest ratio <= noiseFloor\n639:                c) Question entropy (w=0.35):\n640:                   coverage = answered / total questions\n641:                   stop if coverage >= 0.85\n642:                Redistribute weights for unavailable signals.\n643:                if weighted_stop_score > 0.60: inline_stop_candidate = true\n644:                Combined stop rule: STOP only if the inline 3-signal vote says STOP AND graph_decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\n645:                if inline_stop_candidate and graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\":\n646:                  decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n647:                  reason = \"blockedStop\"\n648:                  stop_blocked = true\n649:                  blocked_by_json = JSON array derived from graph_blockers_json\n650:                  blocked_by_csv = comma-separated blocker names derived from graph_blockers_json\n651:                  gate_convergence_pass = false\n652:                  gate_convergence_score = graph_convergence_score\n653:                  gate_key_question_coverage_pass = no blocker named questionCoverage\n654:                  gate_evidence_density_pass = no blocker named sourceDiversity or evidenceDepth\n655:                  gate_evidence_density_sources = graph_signals_json.sourceDiversity or 0\n656:                  gate_hotspot_saturation_pass = true\n657:                  recovery_strategy = first blocker reason/message, else \"Collect deeper graph evidence before stopping.\"\n658:                else if inline_stop_candidate and (graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\" or graph_decision is absent):\n659:                  decision = \"STOP\"\n660:                  reason = \"composite_converged\"\n661:                  stop_blocked = false\n662:           6. else: CONTINUE\n663:           7. if decision == \"STOP\" and reason != \"maxIterationsReached\" and effective_min_iterations > 1 and iteration_count < effective_min_iterations:\n664:                decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n665:                reason = \"minIterationsNotReached\"\n666:                min_iterations_guard_blocked = true\n667:                min_iterations_guard_pass = false\n668:           8. if effective_min_iterations > 1 and iteration_count >= effective_min_iterations and min_iterations_guard_already_passed == false:\n669:                min_iterations_guard_pass = true\n670:           9. if decision == \"STOP\" and reason != \"maxIterationsReached\":\n671:                guardResult = checkQualityGuards(state, strategy)\n672:                if not guardResult.passed:\n673:                  log: \"Quality guard failed: {guardResult.violations}. Overriding STOP to CONTINUE.\"\n674:                  decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n675:           See convergence.md for full pseudocode and signal definitions.\n676:           Segment-aware convergence is experimental/reference-only; live workflow uses the current session as a single segment.\n677:         outputs:\n678:           - decision: \"STOP | BLOCKED | STUCK_RECOVERY | CONTINUE\"\n679:           - reason: \"Human-readable stop reason\"\n680:           - stop_blocked: \"Boolean marker set when graph convergence vetoes an inline STOP candidate\"\n681:           - blocked_by_json: \"JSON array of graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n682:           - blocked_by_csv: \"Comma-separated graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n683:           - gate_convergence_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for the graph-assisted convergence gate\"\n684:           - gate_convergence_score: \"Numeric score recorded from graph convergence\"\n685:           - gate_key_question_coverage_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker coverage signals\"\n686:           - gate_evidence_density_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker evidence-depth signals\"\n687:           - gate_evidence_density_sources: \"Source-diversity count or equivalent evidence-depth proxy\"\n688:           - gate_hotspot_saturation_pass: \"Research placeholder gate; true unless an explicit blocker sets otherwise\"\n689:           - recovery_strategy: \"One-line hint describing the next research action when decision == BLOCKED or STUCK_RECOVERY\"\n690:           - min_iterations_guard_pass: \"Boolean true when the configured convergence floor has cleared for the first time\"\n691:           - min_iterations_guard_blocked: \"Boolean true when the configured convergence floor overrides a STOP candidate to CONTINUE\"\n692: \n693:       step_emit_min_iterations_guard_pass:\n694:         action: \"Persist a first-class event when the convergence floor clears\"\n695:         if_pass:\n696:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"min_iterations_guard_pass\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"iterationCount\":{iteration_count},\"minIterations\":{effective_min_iterations},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n697:           log: \"Minimum iteration floor cleared for convergence stopping.\"\n698: \n699:       step_emit_blocked_stop:\n700:         action: \"Persist a first-class blocked_stop event when the legal-stop decision tree returns blocked\"\n701:         if_blocked:\n702:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergence\":{\"pass\":{gate_convergence_pass},\"score\":{gate_convergence_score}},\"keyQuestionCoverage\":{\"pass\":{gate_key_question_coverage_pass},\"answered\":{answered_count},\"total\":{total_questions}},\"evidenceDensity\":{\"pass\":{gate_evidence_density_pass},\"sources\":{gate_evidence_density_sources}},\"hotspotSaturation\":{\"pass\":{gate_hotspot_saturation_pass}}},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n703:           log: \"Graph convergence blocked STOP. Failed blockers: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n704:           set:\n705:             decision: \"CONTINUE\"\n706:             reason: \"blockedStop\"\n707:             stop_blocked: false\n708: \n709:       step_handle_convergence:\n710:         action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n711:         if_stop:\n712:           branch_on: \"convergence_mode == 'divergent' AND reason is in ['composite_converged', 'all_questions_answered']\"\n713:           if_divergent_eligible:\n714:             eligibility_contract:\n715:               required_decision: \"STOP\"\n716:               eligible_reasons: [composite_converged, all_questions_answered]\n717:               excluded_reasons: [maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, minIterationsNotReached, error, manualStop, userPaused]\n718:               fail_closed: \"Any missing or ambiguous reason uses if_existing_terminal_path without preparing a pivot.\"\n719:             steps:\n720:               step_prepare_divergent_pivot:\n721:                 action: \"Generate state-grounded research candidates and prepare or resume the pivot transaction\"\n722:                 command: |\n723:                   node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n724:                   import {\n725:                     buildResearchPivotPreparationInput,\n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 1-725. Use offset=726 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n# - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n#   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n#   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n# - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n#   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n#   free-form narrative prose.\n# - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n#   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n#\n# GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n# - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n#   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n#   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n#   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Research Loop Manager","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml","text":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n# - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n#   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n#   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n# - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n#   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n#   free-form narrative prose.\n# - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n#   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n#\n# GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n# - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n#   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n#   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n#   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Research Loop Manager\npurpose: Iterative deep research with convergence detection\naction: Run deep-research loop from initialization through synthesis\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: iterative_loop\n  workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n  workflow_execution: autonomous\n  approvals: none\n  tracking: progressive_research_state\n  validation: convergence_detection\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\noperating_principles:\n  core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n  approach: \"Dispatch focused agent, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n  mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nuser_inputs:\n  research_topic: \"[RESEARCH_TOPIC] - Topic to investigate deeply. REQUIRED.\"\n  spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path. REQUIRED.\"\n  max_iterations: \"[MAX_ITERATIONS] - Maximum loop iterations. Default: 10.\"\n  convergence_threshold: \"[CONVERGENCE_THRESHOLD] - Stop threshold. Default: 0.05.\"\n  convergence_mode: \"[default|off|sliding-window|divergent] - Convergence policy modifier. Default: default.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# CONTEXT LOADING\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ncontext_loading:\n  trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n  purpose: \"Load prior research context for the topic and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n  mcp_integration:\n    tool: memory_context\n    note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n    parameters: { input: \"{research_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n  when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n  behavior:\n    if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n    if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# SKILL REFERENCE\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nskill_reference:\n  skill: system-deep-loop\n  skill_md: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md\n  references:\n    loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/loop-protocol.md\n    spec_check_protocol: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/spec-check-protocol.md\n    state_format: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/state/state-format.md\n    convergence: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md\n  templates:\n    config: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-config.json\n    strategy: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-strategy.md\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# AGENT CONFIGURATION\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nagent_config:\n  agent: deep-research\n  agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-research.md\"\n  # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n  model: opus\n  leaf_only: true\n  tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, WebFetch]\n  mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n  tool_call_budget: { target: 8, max: 12 }\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# STATE FILE PATHS\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nstate_paths:\n  # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n  # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep root-local\n  # research/ and child phases keep local research/ packet directories.\n  packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n  config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json\"\n  state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n  status_ledger: \"{artifact_dir}/orchestration-status.log\"\n  strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-strategy.md\"\n  registry: \"{artifact_dir}/findings-registry.json\"\n  dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-dashboard.md\"\n  pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-pause\"\n  run_now_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-run-now\"\n  lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research.lock\"\n  prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n  iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n  iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n  # Per-iteration structured delta stream (one file per iteration) — complement to the\n  # canonical state_log append. The delta file MUST contain at least one record whose\n  # `type === \"iteration\"` so the reducer can rehydrate iteration state after a partial\n  # run. Variants like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer; the\n  # post_dispatch_validate step enforces the canonical type below.\n  delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n  delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n  research_output: \"{artifact_dir}/research.md\"\n  resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n  archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n  synthesis_snapshot_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/synthesis-v{generation}.md\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# WORKFLOW\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nworkflow:\n\n  step_resolve_artifact_root:\n    description: \"Resolve artifact directory — use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n    note: \"Root specs keep research artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/research/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/research/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/research_archive/{packet}/.\"\n    branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n    if_present:\n      bind:\n        artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_subfolder: null\n        artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n    if_absent:\n      command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('./.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'research')));\\\"\"\n      outputs:\n        - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local research owner directory\"\n        - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n        - artifact_dir: \"Resolved research packet directory for this target\"\n        - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local research archive directory for this target\"\n\n  step_fanout_spawn:\n    description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n    skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n    instructions: |\n      Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n      isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n      fanout-run.cjs owns native and CLI lineage execution; native is run through the\n      deep/research command surface with config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir so the LEAF\n      deep-research agent is used only for individual iterations, never as a full-loop\n      sub-agent or pasted phase-running prompt.\n      After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n      phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n      phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n    sub_steps:\n      step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n        description: \"Spawn all native and CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n        skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n            --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n            --loop-type research \\\n            --research-topic \"{research_topic}\" \\\n            --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n            --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir} \\\n            --convergence-threshold {convergence_threshold}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_init:\n    purpose: Create all state files for the research session\n    steps:\n\n      step_preflight_contract:\n        action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n        verify:\n          - required_values_present: [research_topic, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold, convergence_mode]\n          - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n          - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n          - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n        on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n\n      step_create_directories:\n        action: \"Create spec folder and research packet directories if they don't exist\"\n        command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n\n      step_detect_resource_map:\n        action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist the flag and seed Known Context\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n        classify:\n          present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n          absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n        outputs:\n          - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n          - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: summarize the map by section with entry counts across READMEs, Documents, Commands, Agents, Skills, Specs, Scripts, Tests, Config, and Meta, plus a one-line theme summary for each section. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_resolve_canonical_names:\n        action: \"Resolve canonical research packet artifact names before classification\"\n        inspect_legacy:\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/config.json\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/state.jsonl\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/strategy.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dashboard.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/.pause\"\n        migration_policy: \"dual-read / single-write for 4 weeks\"\n        on_legacy_read:\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"migration\",\"legacyPath\":\"{legacy_path}\",\"canonicalPath\":\"{canonical_path}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n      step_acquire_lock:\n        action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n        on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-research run already holds this packet.\"\n        note: \"Uses the promoted runtime/ loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n        # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n        # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n        on_halt:\n          action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n          applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\", \"step_preinit_spec_branch.conflict-detected\"]\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n        on_cancel:\n          action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n        on_workflow_exit:\n          action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n\n      step_classify_session:\n        action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        classify:\n          fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n          resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on topic/spec folder; missing wait-checkpoint fields are read as nextRunAt:null and remainingDelayMs:null\"\n          completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n          invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n        outputs:\n          - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n        on_resume:\n          # T-YML-DPR-01 / R50-001: Resume is a WRITE-PATH. Produces `iteration-NNN.md` + JSONL appends.\n          # Paired with T-DOC-03 Gate 3 trigger addition (resume, save context, save memory, /memory:save).\n          gate3_classification: write-path\n          gate3_rationale: \"resume produces iteration-NNN.md writes and JSONL state-log appends\"\n          log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: phase_loop\n        on_restart:\n          action: \"Archive the current research packet under the root-level research_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n          command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n          set:\n            lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n            parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n            generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: step_create_config\n        note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-research/references/protocol/loop-protocol.md §Lifecycle Branch Contract for the one-session contract.\"\n        on_completed_session:\n          log: \"Prior session already completed. Do not route directly to synthesis; archive the completed research/ tree or start a fresh packet instead.\"\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Completed deep-research packet detected. Archive or replace the existing research/ tree before starting a new session.\"\n        on_invalid_state:\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Existing deep-research state is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid research packet before continuing.\"\n        on_fresh:\n          action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n\n      step_resolve_session_id:\n        action: \"Resolve init session id from caller when supplied, else preserve the auto-generated fallback\"\n        branch_on: \"session_id\"\n        if_present:\n          bind:\n            session_id_init: \"{session_id}\"\n        if_absent:\n          bind:\n            session_id_init: \"{AUTO_SESSION_ID}\"\n\n      step_create_config:\n        action: \"Create deep-research-config.json from template\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-config.json\n        populate:\n          topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n          maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          minIterations: 3\n          # Semantic: newInfoRatio with negative-knowledge emphasis. See SKILL.md §\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n          convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n          antiConvergence.convergenceMode: \"{convergence_mode}\"\n          antiConvergence.divergent: {}\n          stuckThreshold: 3\n          minIdeaObservations: 2\n          maxDurationMinutes: 120\n          specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n          resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n          # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-research.md:73 (default true; false when flag is set).\n          # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n          resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n          createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n          status: \"initialized\"\n          executionMode: \"auto\"\n          lineage.sessionId: \"{session_id_init}\"\n          lineage.parentSessionId: null\n          lineage.lineageMode: \"new\"\n          lineage.generation: 1\n          lineage.continuedFromRun: null\n          nextRunAt: null\n          remainingDelayMs: null\n        output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n\n      step_create_state_log:\n        action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record\"\n        # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n        content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"{research_topic}\",\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"minIterations\":3,\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"antiConvergence\":{\"convergenceMode\":\"{convergence_mode}\",\"divergent\":{}},\"minIdeaObservations\":2,\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\",\"nextRunAt\":null,\"remainingDelayMs\":null}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n\n      step_create_strategy:\n        action: \"Create strategy file from template with initial questions\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-strategy.md\n        populate:\n          topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n          key_questions: \"Derive 3-5 key questions from the research topic\"\n          known_context: \"None\"\n          known_context_summary: \"None\"\n          max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n        output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n      step_create_registry:\n        action: \"Initialize reducer-owned findings registry\"\n        content: '{\"openQuestions\":[],\"resolvedQuestions\":[],\"keyFindings\":[],\"ruledOutDirections\":[],\"metrics\":{\"iterationsCompleted\":0,\"openQuestions\":0,\"resolvedQuestions\":0,\"keyFindings\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0,\"coverageBySources\":{}}}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_context:\n        action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n        condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n        action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_detect_spec_present:\n        action: \"Classify late-INIT spec.md state after the durable research packet exists\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.lock_file}\"\n        classify:\n          no-spec: \"spec.md is absent before any pre-init mutation\"\n          spec-present: \"spec.md exists and approved host anchors are available for bounded mutation\"\n          spec-just-created-by-this-run: \"spec.md already carries this run's DR seed markers and should not be reseeded\"\n          conflict-detected: \"missing host anchor, duplicate markers, or generated-block ambiguity makes mutation unsafe\"\n        outputs:\n          - folder_state: \"no-spec | spec-present | spec-just-created-by-this-run | conflict-detected\"\n          - normalized_topic: \"Trim, lowercase, and collapse whitespace in research_topic before dedupe checks\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_check_result\",\"folder_state\":\"{folder_state}\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"lockPath\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n      step_preinit_spec_branch:\n        action: \"Run the bounded pre-init spec branch required by spec_check_protocol\"\n        protocol_reference: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/spec-check-protocol.md\"\n        branches:\n          no-spec:\n            create: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n            seed_markers:\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n            requirements_host: \"Seed Requirements from the research ask without broadening scope\"\n            scope_host: \"Seed Scope from the research ask without inventing implementation details\"\n            set:\n              folder_state: \"spec-just-created-by-this-run\"\n              validate_spec_doc: true\n            append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_seed_created\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-just-created-by-this-run\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Requirements\",\"Scope\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Seeded Level 1 spec.md from research topic with DR seed markers.\",\"seed_markers\":[\"DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS\",\"DR-SEED:SCOPE\"],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          spec-present:\n            edit: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n            set:\n              validate_spec_doc: true\n            idempotency_check:\n              host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n              normalized_match: \"Normalize the existing anchor text by lowercasing, stripping punctuation, collapsing whitespace, and trimming before comparing with {normalized_topic}.\"\n              if_match:\n                skip_append: true\n                append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_deduped\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Skipped duplicate pre-init topic append because normalized topic already exists in Open Questions.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n              if_no_match:\n                append_only:\n                  - host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n                    content: \"Add the normalized research topic only if it is not already present.\"\n                  - host_anchor: \"Research Context\"\n                    content: \"Add a bounded note that deep-research is active for this topic and that research/research.md remains canonical.\"\n                append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_added\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\",\"Research Context\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Appended bounded pre-init research context for the normalized topic.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          spec-just-created-by-this-run:\n            verify_markers:\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n            set:\n              validate_spec_doc: false\n            note: \"Treat already-seeded spec.md as a no-op guard and continue.\"\n          conflict-detected:\n            append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation_conflict\",\"folder_state\":\"conflict-detected\",\"reason\":\"Pre-init spec.md mutation is ambiguous or unsafe.\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n            halt: true\n\n      step_validate_preinit_spec_doc:\n        action: \"Run targeted strict validation after any deep-research pre-init spec.md mutation\"\n        condition: \"validate_spec_doc\"\n        command: \"SPECKIT_RULES=FRONTMATTER_VALID,LEVEL_DECLARED,TEMPLATE_SOURCE,TEMPLATE_HEADERS,PLACEHOLDER_FILLED,SECTIONS_PRESENT,ANCHORS_VALID,SPEC_DOC_INTEGRITY,TOC_POLICY bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh {spec_folder} --strict\"\n        note: \"This enforces the authored-spec markdown structural contract without applying full-packet required-file or completeness checks to workflow-owned research artifacts. It uses the Node validation orchestrator, whose strict path was measured at about 108ms for a fresh Level 3 packet on the local harness.\"\n\n      step_telemetry_heartbeat_started:\n        action: \"Emit a single-loop started row in the orchestration status ledger\"\n        skip_when: \"config.fanout is present\"\n        canonical_lifecycle_event: \"iteration_start\"\n        command: |\n          node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n          import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n\n          import { appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts';\n          import observabilityEvents from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/observability-events.cjs';\n\n          const { appendObservabilityEvent } = observabilityEvents;\n          const config = JSON.parse(readFileSync('{state_paths.config}', 'utf8'));\n          const timestamp = '{ISO_8601_NOW}';\n          const sessionId = String(config.lineage?.sessionId ?? '{AUTO_SESSION_ID}');\n          const generation = Number(config.lineage?.generation ?? 1);\n          const observabilityPath = '{state_paths.packet_dir}/observability-events.jsonl';\n          const row = {\n            event: 'started',\n            label: 'single',\n            at: timestamp,\n            duration_ms: 0,\n            loop_type: 'research',\n            sessionId,\n            generation,\n            gauges: { iterations: 0, elapsed_ms: 0, score: 0 },\n          };\n\n          const appended = appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic('{state_paths.status_ledger}', row, {\n            diffData: { event: row.event, label: row.label, sessionId, generation, gauges: { iterations: 0, score: 0 } },\n            diffField: 'state_hash',\n          });\n          if (appended) {\n            try {\n              appendObservabilityEvent(observabilityPath, row, {\n                producer: 'deep-research-auto',\n                stream: 'single-loop-telemetry',\n                subject: { label: row.label, sessionId, generation },\n                event: row.event,\n                status: 'running',\n              });\n            } catch {}\n          }\n          EOF\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        outputs:\n          - status_ledger_started: \"A fan-out-shaped status row with label single and event started\"\n\n      step_init_complete:\n        log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, and strategy files created.\"\n        set: { current_iteration: 1, current_segment: 1, stuck_count: 0 }\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_loop:\n    purpose: Dispatch agent iterations until convergence\n    repeat: true\n    max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n    steps:\n\n      step_read_state:\n        action: \"Read current state from JSONL and strategy\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n        extract:\n          - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n          - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n          - current_segment: \"Latest segment_start event segment, else 1\"\n          - last_newInfoRatio: \"Extract newInfoRatio from last iteration record\"\n          - last_focus: \"Extract focus from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - ratio_prev: \"Extract newInfoRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - ratio_latest: \"Extract newInfoRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - next_focus: \"Extract 'Next Focus' section from strategy.md\"\n          - remaining_questions: \"Count unchecked items in 'Key Questions'\"\n          - remaining_questions_list: \"List unchecked key questions from strategy.md\"\n          - carried_forward_open_questions: \"Extract 'Carried-Forward Open Questions' section from strategy.md, else '[None yet]'\"\n          - answered_count: \"Count answered questions from strategy.md\"\n          - total_questions: \"Count total questions tracked in strategy.md\"\n          - resource_map_present: \"Extract boolean from deep-research-config.json, default false\"\n          - resource_map_prompt_line: \"If resource_map_present is true, return 'Resource map: prior-inventoried files are listed in {spec_folder}/resource-map.md; treat them as the exclusion set when hunting for net-new files; flag only missed-from-map candidates as gaps.' Else return 'Resource map: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.'\"\n          - memory_context_prompt_line: \"If a refreshed memory context summary exists from the previous iteration, return 'Memory context refresh: {summary}'. Else use prior_context_summary from startup when available; otherwise return 'Memory context refresh: none loaded yet.'\"\n          - least_explored: \"First unanswered question not covered by the most recent iteration focus, else first unanswered question\"\n          - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: focus (ratio)'\"\n          - latest_status: \"Extract status from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - nextRunAt: \"Extract nullable nextRunAt from deep-research-config.json, default null\"\n          - remainingDelayMs: \"Extract nullable remainingDelayMs from deep-research-config.json, default null\"\n          - min_iterations_present: \"Boolean true when deep-research-config.json has a numeric minIterations field\"\n          - min_iterations_missing_warning: \"Boolean true when minIterations is missing; use no floor and log a warning so older configs keep prior stop behavior\"\n          - min_iterations_raw: \"Extract numeric minIterations from deep-research-config.json when present, default 0\"\n          - effective_min_iterations: \"Clamp min_iterations_raw to the inclusive range 0..max_iterations; if min_iterations_raw exceeds max_iterations, use max_iterations\"\n          - min_iterations_clamped: \"Boolean true when min_iterations_raw > max_iterations\"\n          - min_iterations_guard_already_passed: \"Boolean true when state_log already contains event == 'min_iterations_guard_pass'\"\n          - convergence_mode: \"Extract antiConvergence.convergenceMode when it is one of 'default', 'off', 'sliding-window', or 'divergent'; default to 'default'\"\n          - convergence_mode_warning: \"Boolean true when antiConvergence.convergenceMode is present with an unsupported value; use 'default'\"\n          - rejected_patterns_count: \"Read registry.rejectedPatterns length when registry exists, else 0\"\n          - rejected_candidate_matches: \"Read registry.suppressedCandidates when registry exists, else []\"\n          - rejected_pattern_fuzzy_threshold: \"Read config.rejectedPatternFuzzyThreshold when present, else 0.85\"\n          - min_idea_observations: \"Read config.minIdeaObservations when present, default 2; clamp to 1..10\"\n          - observed_ideas_count: \"Read registry.observedIdeas length when registry exists, else 0\"\n          - promoted_ideas_count: \"Read registry.promotedIdeas length when registry exists, else 0\"\n          - promoted_ideas_list: \"Read registry.promotedIdeas idea text in rank order when registry exists, else []\"\n          - suppressed_ideas_count: \"Read registry.suppressedIdeas length when registry exists, else 0\"\n          - pivot_lineage: \"Summarize registry.divergence.completed and registry.divergence.overrides with pivot ids, source iterations, and selected focus; else 'none yet'\"\n          - saturated_directions: \"List registry.divergence.saturatedDirections; else 'none yet'\"\n\n      step_run_now_check:\n        action: \"Detect and consume a one-shot run-now sentinel before pause/convergence/dispatch\"\n        command: |\n          node <<'EOF'\n          const { appendFileSync, existsSync, renameSync, unlinkSync } = require('node:fs');\n\n          const stateLogPath = \"{state_paths.state_log}\";\n          const sentinelPath = \"{state_paths.run_now_sentinel}\";\n          const pausePath = \"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\";\n          const timestamp = \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\";\n          const sessionId = \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\";\n          const generation = Number(\"{config.lineage.generation}\");\n          const run = Number(\"{current_iteration}\");\n\n          function append(event) {\n            appendFileSync(\n              stateLogPath,\n              `${JSON.stringify({\n                type: \"event\",\n                mode: \"research\",\n                run,\n                timestamp,\n                sessionId,\n                generation,\n                ...event,\n              })}\\n`,\n              \"utf8\",\n            );\n          }\n\n          if (existsSync(sentinelPath)) {\n            append({ event: \"run_now_requested\", sentinelPath });\n            if (existsSync(pausePath)) {\n              append({\n                event: \"run_now_rejected\",\n                reason: \"loop_paused\",\n                sentinelPath,\n                pauseSentinelPath: pausePath,\n              });\n            } else {\n              const claimPath = `${sentinelPath}.consuming.${process.pid}.${Date.now()}`;\n              try {\n                renameSync(sentinelPath, claimPath);\n                unlinkSync(claimPath);\n                append({\n                  event: \"run_now_accepted\",\n                  sentinelPath,\n                  dispatchEvent: \"iteration_start\",\n                });\n              } catch (error) {\n                if (!error || error.code !== \"ENOENT\") {\n                  throw error;\n                }\n              }\n            }\n          }\n          EOF\n        outputs:\n          - run_now_requested: \"Emitted when {state_paths.run_now_sentinel} exists at the loop boundary\"\n          - run_now_accepted: \"Emitted after the sentinel is atomically renamed and deleted before dispatch\"\n          - run_now_rejected: \"Emitted with reason loop_paused when pause takes precedence; sentinel remains present\"\n\n      step_check_pause_sentinel:\n        action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n        check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n        if_exists:\n          log_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          message: \"Research paused. Delete research/.deep-research-pause to resume.\"\n          halt: true\n        if_not_exists:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_validate_convergence_config:\n        action: \"Validate convergence floor settings when loading config\"\n        if_min_iterations_missing:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"config_warning\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"field\":\"minIterations\",\"fallback\":0,\"message\":\"minIterations missing; using no convergence floor for backward compatibility.\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"minIterations missing; using no convergence floor for backward compatibility.\"\n        if_min_iterations_clamped:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"config_warning\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"field\":\"minIterations\",\"configured\":{min_iterations_raw},\"effective\":{effective_min_iterations},\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"message\":\"minIterations exceeds maxIterations; clamping to the hard cap.\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"minIterations exceeds maxIterations; clamping to the hard cap.\"\n        if_convergence_mode_invalid:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"config_warning\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"field\":\"convergenceMode\",\"fallback\":\"default\",\"message\":\"Unsupported convergenceMode; using default convergence behavior.\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"Unsupported convergenceMode; using default convergence behavior.\"\n\n      step_graph_convergence:\n        action: \"Evaluate coverage-graph convergence before the inline 3-signal vote and persist the graph decision snapshot\"\n        bash: 'node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"research\" --session-id \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\" --convergence-mode \"{convergence_mode}\"'\n        note: \"Run before the inline vote. STOP from the inline 3-signal vote is allowed only when the graph decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\"\n        outputs:\n          - graph_decision: \"Tool decision value (CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED), else null when unavailable\"\n          - graph_decision_json: \"JSON-encoded graph decision string, else null\"\n          - graph_signals_json: \"Tool signals object, else {}\"\n          - graph_blockers_json: \"Tool blockers array, else []\"\n          - graph_trace_json: \"Tool trace payload, else []\"\n          - graph_convergence_score: \"signals.blendedScore when present, else the best available graph score, else 0\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"graph_convergence\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"decision\":{graph_decision_json},\"signals\":{graph_signals_json},\"blockers\":{graph_blockers_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n\n      step_check_convergence:\n        action: \"Evaluate stop conditions and combine the inline 3-signal vote with graph convergence\"\n        algorithm: |\n          1. if iteration_count >= max_iterations: STOP (maxIterationsReached). This terminal cap bypasses quality-guard overrides; record failed guards/blockers as synthesis evidence instead of continuing.\n          2. if stuck_count >= config.stuckThreshold: STUCK_RECOVERY\n          3. if convergence_mode == \"off\": skip convergence stop candidates and continue unless a terminal cap, pause sentinel, or recovery halt has already fired.\n          4. if remaining_questions == 0: STOP (all_questions_answered)\n          5. GRAPH-ASSISTED COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE:\n               step_graph_convergence already recorded graph_decision, graph_signals_json, graph_blockers_json, and graph_convergence_score for this run.\n               The existing inline 3-signal vote still computes the inline STOP candidate and is not replaced.\n               signals = []\n               Filter: exclude iterations where status == thought from signal inputs (use only evidence iterations)\n               a) Rolling average (w=0.30, needs 3+ iterations):\n                  avg = mean(last 3 newInfoRatios)\n                  stop if avg < convergence_threshold\n               b) MAD noise floor (w=0.35, needs 4+ iterations):\n                  noiseFloor = MAD(all ratios) * 1.4826\n                  stop if latest ratio <= noiseFloor\n               c) Question entropy (w=0.35):\n                  coverage = answered / total questions\n                  stop if coverage >= 0.85\n               Redistribute weights for unavailable signals.\n               if weighted_stop_score > 0.60: inline_stop_candidate = true\n               Combined stop rule: STOP only if the inline 3-signal vote says STOP AND graph_decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\n               if inline_stop_candidate and graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\":\n                 decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n                 reason = \"blockedStop\"\n                 stop_blocked = true\n                 blocked_by_json = JSON array derived from graph_blockers_json\n                 blocked_by_csv = comma-separated blocker names derived from graph_blockers_json\n                 gate_convergence_pass = false\n                 gate_convergence_score = graph_convergence_score\n                 gate_key_question_coverage_pass = no blocker named questionCoverage\n                 gate_evidence_density_pass = no blocker named sourceDiversity or evidenceDepth\n                 gate_evidence_density_sources = graph_signals_json.sourceDiversity or 0\n                 gate_hotspot_saturation_pass = true\n                 recovery_strategy = first blocker reason/message, else \"Collect deeper graph evidence before stopping.\"\n               else if inline_stop_candidate and (graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\" or graph_decision is absent):\n                 decision = \"STOP\"\n                 reason = \"composite_converged\"\n                 stop_blocked = false\n          6. else: CONTINUE\n          7. if decision == \"STOP\" and reason != \"maxIterationsReached\" and effective_min_iterations > 1 and iteration_count < effective_min_iterations:\n               decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n               reason = \"minIterationsNotReached\"\n               min_iterations_guard_blocked = true\n               min_iterations_guard_pass = false\n          8. if effective_min_iterations > 1 and iteration_count >= effective_min_iterations and min_iterations_guard_already_passed == false:\n               min_iterations_guard_pass = true\n          9. if decision == \"STOP\" and reason != \"maxIterationsReached\":\n               guardResult = checkQualityGuards(state, strategy)\n               if not guardResult.passed:\n                 log: \"Quality guard failed: {guardResult.violations}. Overriding STOP to CONTINUE.\"\n                 decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n          See convergence.md for full pseudocode and signal definitions.\n          Segment-aware convergence is experimental/reference-only; live workflow uses the current session as a single segment.\n        outputs:\n          - decision: \"STOP | BLOCKED | STUCK_RECOVERY | CONTINUE\"\n          - reason: \"Human-readable stop reason\"\n          - stop_blocked: \"Boolean marker set when graph convergence vetoes an inline STOP candidate\"\n          - blocked_by_json: \"JSON array of graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n          - blocked_by_csv: \"Comma-separated graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n          - gate_convergence_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for the graph-assisted convergence gate\"\n          - gate_convergence_score: \"Numeric score recorded from graph convergence\"\n          - gate_key_question_coverage_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker coverage signals\"\n          - gate_evidence_density_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker evidence-depth signals\"\n          - gate_evidence_density_sources: \"Source-diversity count or equivalent evidence-depth proxy\"\n          - gate_hotspot_saturation_pass: \"Research placeholder gate; true unless an explicit blocker sets otherwise\"\n          - recovery_strategy: \"One-line hint describing the next research action when decision == BLOCKED or STUCK_RECOVERY\"\n          - min_iterations_guard_pass: \"Boolean true when the configured convergence floor has cleared for the first time\"\n          - min_iterations_guard_blocked: \"Boolean true when the configured convergence floor overrides a STOP candidate to CONTINUE\"\n\n      step_emit_min_iterations_guard_pass:\n        action: \"Persist a first-class event when the convergence floor clears\"\n        if_pass:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"min_iterations_guard_pass\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"iterationCount\":{iteration_count},\"minIterations\":{effective_min_iterations},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"Minimum iteration floor cleared for convergence stopping.\"\n\n      step_emit_blocked_stop:\n        action: \"Persist a first-class blocked_stop event when the legal-stop decision tree returns blocked\"\n        if_blocked:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergence\":{\"pass\":{gate_convergence_pass},\"score\":{gate_convergence_score}},\"keyQuestionCoverage\":{\"pass\":{gate_key_question_coverage_pass},\"answered\":{answered_count},\"total\":{total_questions}},\"evidenceDensity\":{\"pass\":{gate_evidence_density_pass},\"sources\":{gate_evidence_density_sources}},\"hotspotSaturation\":{\"pass\":{gate_hotspot_saturation_pass}}},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"Graph convergence blocked STOP. Failed blockers: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n          set:\n            decision: \"CONTINUE\"\n            reason: \"blockedStop\"\n            stop_blocked: false\n\n      step_handle_convergence:\n        action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n        if_stop:\n          branch_on: \"convergence_mode == 'divergent' AND reason is in ['composite_converged', 'all_questions_answered']\"\n          if_divergent_eligible:\n            eligibility_contract:\n              required_decision: \"STOP\"\n              eligible_reasons: [composite_converged, all_questions_answered]\n              excluded_reasons: [maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, minIterationsNotReached, error, manualStop, userPaused]\n              fail_closed: \"Any missing or ambiguous reason uses if_existing_terminal_path without preparing a pivot.\"\n            steps:\n              step_prepare_divergent_pivot:\n                action: \"Generate state-grounded research candidates and prepare or resume the pivot transaction\"\n                command: |\n                  node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n                  import {\n                    buildResearchPivotPreparationInput,","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":725,"totalLines":726,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml","time":{"start":1784624002030,"end":1784624002214}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a88b627636cb19a016a5f3381e0c48191aa11ca52fe15b1ba"}},"id":"prt_f83e133b0001IeFOOp9FTkGylA","sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","messageID":"msg_f83e0dfed001PnGWcNgq9WoThY"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1784624002850,"sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","part":{"id":"prt_f83e1371e001sQXgUMvmjbyMRb","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"b1940b77a7b67705ca54e3127e96b4ab903a7d6e","messageID":"msg_f83e0dfed001PnGWcNgq9WoThY","sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":63127,"input":33239,"output":555,"reasoning":149,"cache":{"write":0,"read":29184}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1784624006207,"sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","part":{"id":"prt_f83e1443a001xSmq7F1z6NnfIL","messageID":"msg_f83e13931001Dr7K2ba2C7mC7I","sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","snapshot":"b1940b77a7b67705ca54e3127e96b4ab903a7d6e","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784624008142,"sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ivapcCPeKXKkc11PXTFDcREH","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml","offset":700,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n700:         action: \"Persist a first-class blocked_stop event when the legal-stop decision tree returns blocked\"\n701:         if_blocked:\n702:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergence\":{\"pass\":{gate_convergence_pass},\"score\":{gate_convergence_score}},\"keyQuestionCoverage\":{\"pass\":{gate_key_question_coverage_pass},\"answered\":{answered_count},\"total\":{total_questions}},\"evidenceDensity\":{\"pass\":{gate_evidence_density_pass},\"sources\":{gate_evidence_density_sources}},\"hotspotSaturation\":{\"pass\":{gate_hotspot_saturation_pass}}},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n703:           log: \"Graph convergence blocked STOP. Failed blockers: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n704:           set:\n705:             decision: \"CONTINUE\"\n706:             reason: \"blockedStop\"\n707:             stop_blocked: false\n708: \n709:       step_handle_convergence:\n710:         action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n711:         if_stop:\n712:           branch_on: \"convergence_mode == 'divergent' AND reason is in ['composite_converged', 'all_questions_answered']\"\n713:           if_divergent_eligible:\n714:             eligibility_contract:\n715:               required_decision: \"STOP\"\n716:               eligible_reasons: [composite_converged, all_questions_answered]\n717:               excluded_reasons: [maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, minIterationsNotReached, error, manualStop, userPaused]\n718:               fail_closed: \"Any missing or ambiguous reason uses if_existing_terminal_path without preparing a pivot.\"\n719:             steps:\n720:               step_prepare_divergent_pivot:\n721:                 action: \"Generate state-grounded research candidates and prepare or resume the pivot transaction\"\n722:                 command: |\n723:                   node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n724:                   import {\n725:                     buildResearchPivotPreparationInput,\n726:                     renderResearchPivotSeatPrompt,\n727:                   } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/divergent-research-pivot.ts';\n728:                   import {\n729:                     preparePivotTransaction,\n730:                   } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n731: \n732:                   const input = buildResearchPivotPreparationInput({\n733:                     artifactRoot: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n734:                     configPath: '{state_paths.config}',\n735:                     stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n736:                     strategyPath: '{state_paths.strategy}',\n737:                     registryPath: '{state_paths.registry}',\n738:                     currentIteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n739:                     maxIterations: Number('{max_iterations}'),\n740:                     triggerReason: '{reason}',\n741:                   });\n742:                   const prepared = await preparePivotTransaction(input);\n743:                   const seatPrompts = prepared.status === 'pending'\n744:                     ? Object.fromEntries(prepared.missingSeats.map((seat) => [\n745:                         seat.id,\n746:                         renderResearchPivotSeatPrompt(seat, prepared.dispatchContext),\n747:                       ]))\n748:                     : {};\n749:                   process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify({\n750:                     ...prepared,\n751:                     seatPrompts,\n752:                     boundaryRejections: input.boundaryRejections,\n753:                   })}\\n`);\n754:                   EOF\n755:                 working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n756:                 outputs:\n757:                   - pivot_prepare_json: \"The complete parsed JSON result\"\n758:                   - pivot_prepare_status: \"status from the prepare result\"\n759:                   - pivot_id: \"pivotId from the prepare result\"\n760:                   - pivot_paths_json: \"paths from the prepare result as JSON\"\n761:                   - pivot_resumed: \"resumed from the prepare result\"\n762:                   - pivot_missing_seat_ids: \"missingSeats ids from a pending result\"\n763:                   - pivot_seat_001_json: \"The seat-001 mandate object from missingSeats\"\n764:                   - pivot_seat_002_json: \"The seat-002 mandate object from missingSeats\"\n765:                   - pivot_seat_003_json: \"The seat-003 mandate object from missingSeats\"\n766:                   - pivot_seat_001_prompt: \"seatPrompts['seat-001']\"\n767:                   - pivot_seat_002_prompt: \"seatPrompts['seat-002']\"\n768:                   - pivot_seat_003_prompt: \"seatPrompts['seat-003']\"\n769:                   - pivot_dispatch_context_json: \"dispatchContext from a pending result as JSON\"\n770:                 short_circuit: \"When status is completed or failed, skip all dispatch and record steps and bind this result as pivot_result.\"\n771: \n772:               step_dispatch_pivot_seat_001:\n773:                 action: \"Natively dispatch the analytical research direction-selection seat\"\n774:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-001'\"\n775:                 capture_timing: true\n776:                 if_native:\n777:                   dispatch:\n778:                     agent: deep-research\n779:                     model: opus\n780:                     context_source: \"pivot_seat_001_prompt\"\n781:                   wait_for_completion: true\n782:                 failure_contract: \"A native dispatch failure binds status=rejected, a {name,message} error, and the measured timestamps/duration, then proceeds to step_record_pivot_seat_001.\"\n783:                 outputs:\n784:                   - pivot_seat_001_dispatch_status: \"fulfilled or rejected\"\n785:                   - pivot_seat_001_output_json: \"Raw native return serialized as JSON when fulfilled\"\n786:                   - pivot_seat_001_error_json: \"{name,message} when rejected\"\n787:                   - pivot_seat_001_started_at_iso: \"Dispatch start timestamp\"\n788:                   - pivot_seat_001_completed_at_iso: \"Dispatch completion timestamp\"\n789:                   - pivot_seat_001_duration_ms: \"Dispatch duration in milliseconds\"\n790: \n791:               step_record_pivot_seat_001:\n792:                 action: \"Durably record the seat-001 native dispatch outcome\"\n793:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-001'\"\n794:                 command: |\n795:                   node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n796:                   import { recordPivotSeatResult } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n797:                   const status = '{pivot_seat_001_dispatch_status}';\n798:                   const outcome = status === 'fulfilled'\n799:                     ? { status, output: {pivot_seat_001_output_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_001_duration_ms}') }\n800:                     : { status: 'rejected', error: {pivot_seat_001_error_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_001_duration_ms}') };\n801:                   process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(recordPivotSeatResult({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', seat: {pivot_seat_001_json}, outcome }))}\\n`);\n802:                   EOF\n803:                 working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n804: \n805:               step_dispatch_pivot_seat_002:\n806:                 action: \"Natively dispatch the critical research direction-selection seat\"\n807:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-002'\"\n808:                 capture_timing: true\n809:                 if_native:\n810:                   dispatch:\n811:                     agent: deep-research\n812:                     model: opus\n813:                     context_source: \"pivot_seat_002_prompt\"\n814:                   wait_for_completion: true\n815:                 failure_contract: \"A native dispatch failure binds status=rejected, a {name,message} error, and the measured timestamps/duration, then proceeds to step_record_pivot_seat_002.\"\n816:                 outputs:\n817:                   - pivot_seat_002_dispatch_status: \"fulfilled or rejected\"\n818:                   - pivot_seat_002_output_json: \"Raw native return serialized as JSON when fulfilled\"\n819:                   - pivot_seat_002_error_json: \"{name,message} when rejected\"\n820:                   - pivot_seat_002_started_at_iso: \"Dispatch start timestamp\"\n821:                   - pivot_seat_002_completed_at_iso: \"Dispatch completion timestamp\"\n822:                   - pivot_seat_002_duration_ms: \"Dispatch duration in milliseconds\"\n823: \n824:               step_record_pivot_seat_002:\n825:                 action: \"Durably record the seat-002 native dispatch outcome\"\n826:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-002'\"\n827:                 command: |\n828:                   node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n829:                   import { recordPivotSeatResult } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n830:                   const status = '{pivot_seat_002_dispatch_status}';\n831:                   const outcome = status === 'fulfilled'\n832:                     ? { status, output: {pivot_seat_002_output_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_002_duration_ms}') }\n833:                     : { status: 'rejected', error: {pivot_seat_002_error_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_002_duration_ms}') };\n834:                   process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(recordPivotSeatResult({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', seat: {pivot_seat_002_json}, outcome }))}\\n`);\n835:                   EOF\n836:                 working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n837: \n838:               step_dispatch_pivot_seat_003:\n839:                 action: \"Natively dispatch the pragmatic research direction-selection seat\"\n840:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-003'\"\n841:                 capture_timing: true\n842:                 if_native:\n843:                   dispatch:\n844:                     agent: deep-research\n845:                     model: opus\n846:                     context_source: \"pivot_seat_003_prompt\"\n847:                   wait_for_completion: true\n848:                 failure_contract: \"A native dispatch failure binds status=rejected, a {name,message} error, and the measured timestamps/duration, then proceeds to step_record_pivot_seat_003.\"\n849:                 outputs:\n850:                   - pivot_seat_003_dispatch_status: \"fulfilled or rejected\"\n851:                   - pivot_seat_003_output_json: \"Raw native return serialized as JSON when fulfilled\"\n852:                   - pivot_seat_003_error_json: \"{name,message} when rejected\"\n853:                   - pivot_seat_003_started_at_iso: \"Dispatch start timestamp\"\n854:                   - pivot_seat_003_completed_at_iso: \"Dispatch completion timestamp\"\n855:                   - pivot_seat_003_duration_ms: \"Dispatch duration in milliseconds\"\n856: \n857:               step_record_pivot_seat_003:\n858:                 action: \"Durably record the seat-003 native dispatch outcome\"\n859:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-003'\"\n860:                 command: |\n861:                   node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n862:                   import { recordPivotSeatResult } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n863:                   const status = '{pivot_seat_003_dispatch_status}';\n864:                   const outcome = status === 'fulfilled'\n865:                     ? { status, output: {pivot_seat_003_output_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_003_duration_ms}') }\n866:                     : { status: 'rejected', error: {pivot_seat_003_error_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_003_duration_ms}') };\n867:                   process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(recordPivotSeatResult({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', seat: {pivot_seat_003_json}, outcome }))}\\n`);\n868:                   EOF\n869:                 working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n870: \n871:               step_finalize_divergent_pivot:\n872:                 action: \"Finalize the prepared pivot after all missing native seats are durable\"\n873:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending'\"\n874:                 command: |\n875:                   node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n876:                   import { finalizePivotTransaction } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n877:                   process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(finalizePivotTransaction({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', resumed: {pivot_resumed} }))}\\n`);\n878:                   EOF\n879:                 working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n880:                 outputs:\n881:                   - pivot_finalize_json: \"The complete parsed final result\"\n882: \n883:               step_resolve_divergent_pivot_result:\n884:                 action: \"Use prepare's terminal result on resume/short-circuit, otherwise use finalize's result\"\n885:                 branch_on: \"pivot_prepare_status\"\n886:                 if_pending: { bind: { pivot_result: \"{pivot_finalize_json}\" } }\n887:                 if_completed_or_failed: { bind: { pivot_result: \"{pivot_prepare_json}\" } }\n888: \n889:               step_apply_divergent_pivot_result:\n890:                 action: \"Adopt a successful focus or fail closed to the existing synthesis path\"\n891:                 branch_on: \"pivot_result.status\"\n892:                 if_completed:\n893:                   set:\n894:                     next_focus: \"{pivot_result.restoredFocus}\"\n895:                     pivot_lineage: \"Pivot {pivot_result.pivotId} selected {pivot_result.selectedCandidate.id} from source iteration {current_iteration}.\"\n896:                     saturated_directions: \"{pivot_result.completedEvent.saturatedDirections}\"\n897:                   command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n898:                   log: \"Divergent pivot {pivot_result.pivotId} restored focus to {pivot_result.restoredFocus}; continuing iteration {current_iteration}.\"\n899:                   proceed_to: step_rejected_pattern_cache\n900:                 if_failed:\n901:                   log: \"Divergent pivot {pivot_result.pivotId} failed closed ({pivot_result.failureReason}); proceeding to synthesis.\"\n902:                   skip_to: phase_synthesis\n903:             on_error:\n904:               log: \"Divergent pivot integration error; failing closed to the existing synthesis path.\"\n905:               skip_to: phase_synthesis\n906:           if_existing_terminal_path:\n907:             log: \"Loop stopping. Reason: {reason}\"\n908:             skip_to: phase_synthesis\n909:         if_stuck_recovery:\n910:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"outcome\":\"recovered\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n911:           log: \"Stuck detected ({stuck_count} consecutive no-progress). Entering recovery.\"\n912:           set: { next_focus: \"RECOVERY: Widen scope. Try fundamentally different approach. Least-explored question: {least_explored}\" }\n913:           reset: { stuck_count: 0 }\n914:         if_continue:\n915:           log: \"Iteration {current_iteration}: Continuing. Focus: {next_focus}\"\n916: \n917:       step_rejected_pattern_cache:\n918:         action: \"Apply reducer-derived rejected-pattern suppression before dispatch candidate selection\"\n919:         read:\n920:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n921:           - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n922:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n923:         candidate_sources:\n924:           next_focus:\n925:             category: \"next-focus\"\n926:             values:\n927:               - \"{next_focus}\"\n928:               - \"{remaining_questions_list}\"\n929:               - \"{carried_forward_open_questions}\"\n930:           recovery:\n931:             category: \"recovery\"\n932:             values:\n933:               - \"{recovery_strategy}\"\n934:               - \"{least_explored}\"\n935:           ideas:\n936:             category: \"ideas\"\n937:             values:\n938:               - \"{promoted_ideas_list}\"\n939:             optional_file: \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/research-ideas.md\"\n940:         algorithm: |\n941:           Use registry.rejectedPatternIndex and registry.promotedIdeas from the latest\n942:           reducer pass as the source of truth.\n943:           Compare normalized exact text first. Then compare fuzzy similarity with\n944:           rejected_pattern_fuzzy_threshold, but only when candidate and rejected categories\n945:           are compatible. Remove suppressed candidates from next_focus, recovery, and ideas\n946:           selection before rendering the dispatch prompt. If all candidates are suppressed,\n947:           halt for operator input instead of reusing a rejected idea.\n948:         outputs:\n949:           - accepted_next_focus: \"First unsuppressed next-focus candidate, or null\"\n950:           - accepted_recovery_candidate: \"First unsuppressed recovery candidate, or null\"\n951:           - accepted_idea_candidate: \"First unsuppressed ideas candidate, or null\"\n952:           - rejected_candidate_matches: \"Suppressed candidate diagnostics from registry.suppressedCandidates plus any current-step matches\"\n953:         if_next_focus_suppressed:\n954:           set: { next_focus: \"{accepted_next_focus || accepted_recovery_candidate || accepted_idea_candidate}\" }\n955:           log: \"Rejected-pattern cache suppressed the prior candidate; dispatching the next accepted candidate.\"\n956:         if_all_candidates_suppressed:\n957:           halt: true\n958:           message: \"All next-focus, recovery, and ideas candidates match active rejected patterns. Remove/reset the rejected pattern or provide a new focus.\"\n959: \n960:       step_ideas_backlog_lifecycle:\n961:         action: \"Track reducer-owned observed/promoted/rejected idea lifecycle before dispatch\"\n962:         read:\n963:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n964:           - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n965:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n966:         lifecycle:\n967:           observed_event: \"idea_observed\"\n968:           promoted_event: \"idea_promoted\"\n969:           rejected_event: \"idea_rejected\"\n970:           min_observations: \"{min_idea_observations}\"\n971:           authority: \"Leaf agents emit observations only; reducer emits promotions and owns ranking.\"\n972:         validate:\n973:           - \"If new leaf-authored output includes idea_promoted, fail validation; only reducer output may append idea_promoted.\"\n974:           - \"If promoted_ideas_count > 0 and next_focus is empty or all questions are resolved, prefer the first unsuppressed promoted idea.\"\n975:           - \"If suppressed_ideas_count > 0, do not render those ideas into dispatch context.\"\n976:         outputs:\n977:           - observed_ideas_count: \"Reducer-derived observed ideas count\"\n978:           - promoted_ideas_count: \"Reducer-derived promoted ideas count after minIdeaObservations\"\n979:           - suppressed_ideas_count: \"Reducer-derived rejected/suppressed ideas count\"\n980:           - accepted_idea_candidate: \"First unsuppressed promoted idea, or null\"\n981: \n982:       step_normalize_pause_events:\n983:         action: \"Normalize pause and recovery lifecycle events to the frozen STOP_REASONS enum at emission time\"\n984:         stop_reasons_enum: [converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused]\n985:         rule_pause_sentinel:\n986:           raw_event_forbidden: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"paused\"}'\n987:           canonical_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n988:         rule_stuck_recovery:\n989:           raw_event_forbidden: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuck_recovery\"}'\n990:           canonical_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"outcome\":\"recovered\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n991: \n992:       step_marker_scan:\n993:         action: \"H-2 loop-prevention guard: scan previous iteration's rendered prompt for nested research marker\"\n994:         algorithm: |\n995:           if current_iteration > 1:\n996:             PREV_PROMPT_PATH = \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{previous_iteration}.md\"\n997:             if file_exists(PREV_PROMPT_PATH):\n998:               PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE = head -1 of PREV_PROMPT_PATH\n999:               if PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE matches ^(DEEP-REVIEW|DEEP-RESEARCH|CODE-REVIEW)$:\n1000:                 log \"ERROR: nested research-of-review loop detected (marker found in previous iteration prompt). Aborting.\"\n1001:                 halt with exit code 2\n1002:         note: |\n1003:           False-positive prevention: only matches when the first line is exactly one of the\n1004:           three canonical markers. Markers appearing in comments or body text are ignored.\n1005:           True-positive triggers only when a previous iteration's rendered prompt literally\n1006:           starts with a deep-loop marker, indicating a nested research-of-review dispatch.\n1007: \n1008:       step_dispatch_iteration:\n1009:         action: \"Dispatch one iteration via the selected executor\"\n1010:         resolve_executor:\n1011:           source: \"config.executor\"\n1012:           loader: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n1013:         pre_dispatch:\n1014:           generate_summary: |\n1015:             STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n1016:             Segment: {current_segment} | Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n1017:             Questions: {answered_count}/{total_questions} answered | Last focus: {last_focus}\n1018:             Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n1019:             {resource_map_prompt_line}\n1020:             {memory_context_prompt_line}\n1021:             Next focus: {next_focus}\n1022:           render_prompt_pack:\n1023:             template_path: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/prompt-pack-iteration.md.tmpl\"\n1024:             renderer: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n1025:             output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n1026:             variables:\n1027:               state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"\n1028:               research_topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n1029:               current_iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n1030:               max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n1031:               next_focus: \"{next_focus}\"\n1032:               remaining_questions_list: \"{remaining_questions_list}\"\n1033:               carried_forward_open_questions: \"{carried_forward_open_questions}\"\n1034:               last_3_summaries: \"{last_3_summaries}\"\n1035:               pivot_lineage: \"{pivot_lineage}\"\n1036:               saturated_directions: \"{saturated_directions}\"\n1037:               state_paths_config: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1038:               state_paths_state_log: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1039:               state_paths_strategy: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1040:               state_paths_registry: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n1041:               state_paths_iteration_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1042:               state_paths_delta_pattern: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n1043:         pre_dispatch_audit:\n1044:           skip_when: \"config.executor.type == 'native'\"\n1045:           call: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts#writeFirstRecordExecutor\"\n1046:           args:\n1047:             stateLogPath: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1048:             executor: \"{config.executor}\"\n1049:             iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n1050:         branch_on: \"config.executor.type\"\n1051:         if_native:\n1052:           dispatch:\n1053:             agent: deep-research\n1054:             model: opus\n1055:             context_source: \"rendered_prompt_pack\"\n1056:           wait_for_completion: true\n1057:         if_cli_claude_code:\n1058:           command: |\n1059:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n1060:             import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n1061:             import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n1062: \n1063:             import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n1064:             import { resolveClaudePermissionMode } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n1065: \n1066:             const executor = {\n1067:               kind: 'cli-claude-code',\n1068:               model: '{config.executor.model}',\n1069:               reasoningEffort: '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}',\n1070:               serviceTier: '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}',\n1071:               sandboxMode: '{config.executor.sandboxMode}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.sandboxMode}',\n1072:               timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n1073:             };\n1074:             const args = [\n1075:               '-p',\n1076:               readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n1077:               '--model',\n1078:               executor.model,\n1079:               '--permission-mode',\n1080:               resolveClaudePermissionMode(executor.sandboxMode),\n1081:               '--output-format',\n1082:               'text',\n1083:             ];\n1084:             if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n1085:               args.push('--effort', executor.reasoningEffort);\n1086:             }\n1087: \n1088:             const dispatchFacts = {\n1089:               command: 'deep/research',\n1090:               mode: 'research',\n1091:               specFolder: '{spec_folder}',\n1092:               artifactDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n1093:               iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n1094:               executorKind: '{config.executor.type}',\n1095:               branchId: '{config.executor.type}',\n1096:               sessionId: '{config.lineage.sessionId}',\n1097:               generation: Number('{config.lineage.generation}'),\n1098:             };\n1099:             const dispatchId = 'research-i{current_iteration}-g{config.lineage.generation}';\n1100:             process.exit(\n1101:               runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n1102:                 command: 'claude',\n1103:                 args,\n1104:                 cwd: '{repo_root}',\n1105:                 timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n1106:                 stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n1107:                 executor,\n1108:                 iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n1109:                 receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n1110:                 dispatchId,\n1111:               }),\n1112:             );\n1113:             EOF\n1114:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1115:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n1116:           wait_for_completion: true\n1117:           notes:\n1118:             - \"sandboxMode maps to permission-mode: read-only -> plan, workspace-write -> acceptEdits, danger-full-access -> bypassPermissions\"\n1119:             - \"claude-code has no serviceTier flag\"\n1120:             - \"claude-code supports --effort for reasoning depth\"\n1121:         record_executor_audit:\n1122:           skip_when: \"config.executor.type == 'native'\"\n1123:           target: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1124:           field: \"executor\"\n1125:           value:\n1126:             kind: \"{config.executor.type}\"\n1127:             model: \"{config.executor.model}\"\n1128:             reasoningEffort: \"{config.executor.reasoningEffort}\"\n1129:             serviceTier: \"{config.executor.serviceTier}\"\n1130:         if_cli_opencode:\n1131:           command: |\n1132:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n1133:             import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n1134:             import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n1135: \n1136:             import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n1137: \n1138:             const reasoningEffort = '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}';\n1139:             const executor = {\n1140:               kind: 'cli-opencode',\n1141:               model: '{config.executor.model}',\n1142:               configDir: null,\n1143:               reasoningEffort,\n1144:               serviceTier: null,\n1145:               sandboxMode: null,\n1146:               timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n1147:               governor: null,\n1148:             };\n1149:             const promptBody = readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8');\n1150:             const message = 'Resolved route: mode=research; target_agent=@deep-research; execution=single_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true'\n1151:               + '\\n\\n'\n1152:               + promptBody;\n1153:             const args = [\n1154:               'run',\n1155:               '--model',\n1156:               executor.model,\n1157:               '--format',\n1158:               'json',\n1159:               '--dangerously-skip-permissions',\n1160:               '--pure',\n1161:               '--dir',\n1162:               '{repo_root}',\n1163:             ];\n1164:             if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n1165:               args.push('--variant', executor.reasoningEffort);\n1166:             }\n1167:             args.push(message);\n1168: \n1169:             const dispatchFacts = {\n1170:               command: 'deep/research',\n1171:               mode: 'research',\n1172:               specFolder: '{spec_folder}',\n1173:               artifactDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n1174:               iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n1175:               executorKind: '{config.executor.type}',\n1176:               branchId: '{config.executor.type}',\n1177:               sessionId: '{config.lineage.sessionId}',\n1178:               generation: Number('{config.lineage.generation}'),\n1179:             };\n1180:             const dispatchId = 'research-i{current_iteration}-g{config.lineage.generation}';\n1181:             process.exit(\n1182:               runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n1183:                 command: 'opencode',\n1184:                 args,\n1185:                 cwd: '{repo_root}',\n1186:                 timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n1187:                 stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n1188:                 executor,\n1189:                 iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n1190:                 // opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation;\n1191:                 // an empty input gives EOF stdin, equivalent to </dev/null.\n1192:                 input: '',\n1193:                 receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n1194:                 dispatchId,\n1195:               }),\n1196:             );\n1197:             EOF\n1198:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1199:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n1200:           wait_for_completion: true\n1201:           notes:\n1202:             - \"Routed through runAuditedExecutorCommand so opencode produces INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts; recursion guard + env allowlist enforced via buildExecutorDispatchEnv\"\n1203:             - \"input:'' yields closed stdin (EOF), equivalent to </dev/null — opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup and hangs at 0% CPU after +60s snapshot prune without it (the `cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode` mode's SKILL.md (`.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/SKILL.md`) §4 ALWAYS rule)\"\n1204:             - \"opencode run takes a positional message; prompt is the route-proof preamble + iteration body\"\n1205:             - \"--variant maps reasoningEffort to opencode's provider-specific reasoning lever (e.g., high, medium, minimal)\"\n1206:             - \"--dangerously-skip-permissions enables hands-off automation; sandboxMode='read-only' is not currently honored (no opencode equivalent)\"\n1207:             - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude Code/raw shell). the `cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode` mode's SKILL.md (`.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/SKILL.md`) §SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"\n1208:         if_cli_codex:\n1209:           command: |\n1210:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n1211:             import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n1212:             import { execFileSync } from 'node:child_process';\n1213: \n1214:             import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n1215: \n1216:             // Fail closed: a requested codex executor must dispatch codex or abort,\n1217:             // never silently degrade to another executor. Undetected absence is what\n1218:             // got Codex deprecated before, so the branch exits non-zero when the\n1219:             // binary is missing instead of falling through to a native/other path.\n1220:             let codexAvailable = false;\n1221:             try {\n1222:               execFileSync('/bin/sh', ['-c', 'command -v codex >/dev/null 2>&1'], { stdio: 'ignore' });\n1223:               codexAvailable = true;\n1224:             } catch {}\n1225:             if (!codexAvailable) {\n1226:               console.error('cli-codex executor unavailable: command -v codex failed');\n1227:               process.exit(1);\n1228:             }\n1229: \n1230:             const reasoningEffort = '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}';\n1231:             const serviceTier = '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}';\n1232:             const model = '{config.executor.model}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.model}';\n1233:             const executor = {\n1234:               kind: 'cli-codex',\n1235:               model,\n1236:               configDir: null,\n1237:               reasoningEffort,\n1238:               serviceTier,\n1239:               sandboxMode: 'workspace-write',\n1240:               timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n1241:               governor: null,\n1242:             };\n1243: \n1244:             const promptBody = readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8');\n1245: \n1246:             // codex reads the iteration prompt from stdin via the trailing '-'. A research\n1247:             // iteration must WRITE its own iteration file, delta and state record, so the\n1248:             // sandbox is workspace-write — read-only would block those required writes.\n1249:             // approval_policy=never keeps the run non-interactive.\n1250:             const args = ['exec'];\n1251:             if (model) {\n1252:               args.push('--model', model);\n1253:             }\n1254:             args.push('-c', 'model_reasoning_effort=' + (reasoningEffort || 'medium'));\n1255:             if (serviceTier) {\n1256:               args.push('-c', 'service_tier=' + serviceTier);\n1257:             }\n1258:             args.push('-c', 'approval_policy=never', '--sandbox', executor.sandboxMode, '-');\n1259: \n1260:             const dispatchId = 'research-i{current_iteration}-g{config.lineage.generation}';\n1261:             process.exit(\n1262:               runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n1263:                 command: 'codex',\n1264:                 args,\n1265:                 cwd: '{repo_root}',\n1266:                 timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n1267:                 stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n1268:                 executor,\n1269:                 iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n1270:                 input: promptBody,\n1271:                 receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n1272:                 dispatchId,\n1273:               }),\n1274:             );\n1275:             EOF\n1276:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1277:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n1278:           wait_for_completion: true\n1279:           notes:\n1280:             - \"Routed through runAuditedExecutorCommand so codex produces INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts; recursion guard (CODEX_SESSION_ID) + env allowlist (CODEX_/OPENAI_/AZURE_OPENAI_) enforced via buildExecutorDispatchEnv\"\n1281:             - \"Fails closed when the codex binary is absent (exit 1) — parity with the fan-out cli-codex lineage guard in fanout-run.cjs; codex routing never degrades to native\"\n1282:             - \"codex exec reads the iteration prompt from stdin via the trailing '-' (input: promptBody); '-c model_reasoning_effort=' maps reasoning depth, default medium; '-c service_tier=' forwarded when configured\"\n1283:             - \"--sandbox workspace-write is required so the iteration can write its own iteration file/delta/state record (read-only would fail the post-dispatch artifact gate); -c approval_policy=never keeps it non-interactive; --model omitted when unset so ~/.codex/config.toml default applies\"\n1284:         post_dispatch_validate:\n1285:           validator: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts#validateIterationOutputs\"\n1286:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/verify-iteration.cjs --loop-type research --artifact-dir {artifact_dir} --iteration {current_iteration}\"\n1287:           command_note: \"Mechanical leaf-reliability gate: exit 0 = complete; non-zero prints one machine reason (iteration_file_missing|state_record_missing|route_proof_missing|route_proof_mismatch|delta_file_missing). The script enforces the artifact + route-proof contract instead of trusting the leaf to self-report, and a non-zero exit triggers on_failure.redispatch_once.\"\n1288:           assert_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1289:           assert_appended: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1290:           assert_jsonl_fields: [type, iteration, newInfoRatio, status, focus, mode]\n1291:           route_proof:\n1292:             mode: research\n1293:             target_agent: deep-research\n1294:             agent_definition_loaded: true\n1295:             resolved_route: \"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\"\n1296:           dispatchReceipt:\n1297:             receiptDir: \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts\"\n1298:             dispatchId: \"research-i{current_iteration}-g{config.lineage.generation}\"\n1299:           optional_jsonl_fields:\n1300:             logOffset: \"Byte offset where the seekable log region starts\"\n1301:             logSize: \"Byte length of the seekable log region\"\n1302:             logPath: \"Absolute path to the file containing the seekable log region\"\n1303:             skippedCount: \"Missed fixed-rate slots counted for the completed dispatch; 0 when no slot was missed\"\n1304:             slotDurationMs: \"Monotonic elapsed duration for the completed dispatch slot\"\n1305:           assert_canonical_type: \"iteration\"\n1306:           assert_delta_file_exists: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n1307:           assert_delta_file_has_iteration_record: true\n1308:           on_failure:\n1309:             action: \"emit schema_mismatch canonical conflict event\"\n1310:             redispatch_once: \"On the FIRST failure of the mechanical command check for this iteration, re-run step_dispatch_iteration exactly once for the same iteration number, then re-run the check. If it still fails, record the iteration as error and continue. Never re-dispatch a given iteration more than once.\"\n1311:             escalation: \"After 3 consecutive failures across iterations, trigger stuck_recovery event with diagnostic context\"\n1312:           failure_reasons_reference:\n1313:             - \"iteration_file_missing — iteration narrative markdown not written\"\n1314:             - \"iteration_file_empty — iteration narrative markdown is zero bytes\"\n1315:             - \"jsonl_not_appended — state log file did not grow since pre-dispatch snapshot\"\n1316:             - \"jsonl_missing_fields — last state-log record omits required schema fields\"\n1317:             - \"jsonl_parse_error — last state-log line is not valid JSON\"\n1318:             - \"jsonl_wrong_type — last state-log record uses type!='iteration' (e.g. 'iteration_delta'); reducer will silently drop\"\n1319:             - \"delta_file_missing — per-iteration deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl not written\"\n1320:             - \"delta_file_empty — per-iteration delta file exists but has zero bytes\"\n1321:             - \"delta_file_missing_iteration_record — delta file lacks any record with type='iteration'\"\n1322:             - \"route_proof_missing — state-log or delta iteration record omits route-proof fields\"\n1323:             - \"route_proof_mismatch — state-log or delta iteration record does not match the resolved deep route\"\n1324:             - \"executor_missing — non-native executor did not record provenance\"\n1325:             - \"dispatch_failure_logged — last record is an explicit dispatch_failure event\"\n1326: \n1327:       step_run_now_restore_check:\n1328:         action: \"Record a run-now sentinel recreated during the completed dispatch\"\n1329:         command: |\n1330:           node <<'EOF'\n1331:           const { appendFileSync, existsSync, readFileSync } = require('node:fs');\n1332: \n1333:           const stateLogPath = \"{state_paths.state_log}\";\n1334:           const sentinelPath = \"{state_paths.run_now_sentinel}\";\n1335:           const timestamp = \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\";\n1336:           const sessionId = \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\";\n1337:           const generation = Number(\"{config.lineage.generation}\");\n1338:           const run = Number(\"{current_iteration}\");\n1339: \n1340:           function hasAcceptedCurrentRun() {\n1341:             if (!existsSync(stateLogPath)) return false;\n1342:             const lines = readFileSync(stateLogPath, \"utf8\").trim().split(/\\r?\\n/).filter(Boolean);\n1343:             for (let index = lines.length - 1; index >= 0; index -= 1) {\n1344:               const record = JSON.parse(lines[index]);\n1345:               if (record.run !== run || record.sessionId !== sessionId) continue;\n1346:               if (record.event === \"run_now_accepted\") return true;\n1347:               if (record.event === \"run_now_rejected\") return false;\n1348:             }\n1349:             return false;\n1350:           }\n1351: \n1352:           if (existsSync(sentinelPath) && hasAcceptedCurrentRun()) {\n1353:             appendFileSync(\n1354:               stateLogPath,\n1355:               `${JSON.stringify({\n1356:                 type: \"event\",\n1357:                 event: \"run_now_restored\",\n1358:                 mode: \"research\",\n1359:                 run,\n1360:                 sentinelPath,\n1361:                 timestamp,\n1362:                 sessionId,\n1363:                 generation,\n1364:               })}\\n`,\n1365:               \"utf8\",\n1366:             );\n1367:           }\n1368:           EOF\n1369:         outputs:\n1370:           - run_now_restored: \"Emitted when an operator recreates the sentinel before the accepted dispatch completes\"\n1371: \n1372:       step_reduce_state:\n1373:         action: \"Run the reducer to synchronize registry, dashboard, and strategy\"\n1374:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n1375:         inputs:\n1376:           latestJSONLDelta: \"Latest JSONL records written since the previous iteration\"\n1377:           newIterationFile: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1378:           priorReducedState: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n1379:         outputs:\n1380:           - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n1381:           - \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n1382:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1383:           - \"{state_paths.state_log} question_conflict events when inbox text disagrees with registry-owned question text\"\n1384:           - \"{state_paths.state_log} idempotent idea_promoted events when observed ideas reach minIdeaObservations\"\n1385:           - \"{state_paths.registry} observedIdeas, promotedIdeas, suppressedIdeas, rejectedPatterns, and suppressedCandidates from idea lifecycle events\"\n1386:         failure_modes:\n1387:           malformed_delta: \"skip + warn\"\n1388:           missing_iteration_file: \"no-op + error\"\n1389:           schema_mismatch: \"reject + conflict event\"\n1390:           question_conflict: \"keep registry value + append question_conflict event with inboxValue, registryValue, and operatorDecision\"\n1391:         guarantee: \"Idempotent for identical inputs\"\n1392: \n1393:       step_graph_upsert:\n1394:         action: \"Persist the latest iteration graph delta after the reducer refresh and after the iteration file exists\"\n1395:         read:\n1396:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1397:         extract:\n1398:           - latest_graph_events: \"Read graphEvents from the latest iteration record, else []\"\n1399:           - graph_upsert_nodes_json: \"Map latest_graph_events where type == 'node' to node payloads with label -> name and preserve remaining node fields\"\n1400:           - graph_upsert_edges_json: \"Map latest_graph_events where type == 'edge' to edge payloads with source -> sourceId, target -> targetId, relation -> uppercase(relation), and preserve remaining edge fields\"\n1401:           - graph_upsert_event_count: \"Count mapped node and edge events\"\n1402:         if_graph_events_present:\n1403:           bash: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"research\\\" --session-id \\\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\\\" --nodes '{graph_upsert_nodes_json}' --edges '{graph_upsert_edges_json}'\"\n1404:           note: \"Skip silently when graphEvents is missing or empty.\"\n1405:         if_graph_events_missing:\n1406:           proceed: true\n1407: \n1408:       step_memory_upsert_iteration:\n1409:         action: \"Upsert the canonical iteration evidence into Spec Kit Memory after reducer and graph persistence\"\n1410:         mcp_tool: memory_save\n1411:         invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\" })'\n1412:         timeout_seconds: 5\n1413:         idempotency: \"Re-running the same iteration file is safe because the memory backend upserts by path/content.\"\n1414:         failure_policy:\n1415:           mcp_error: \"non-fatal; log advisory warning and continue\"\n1416:           timeout: \"non-fatal after timeout_seconds; log advisory warning and continue\"\n1417:         outputs:\n1418:           - memory_upsert_iteration_file: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1419:           - memory_upsert_status: \"upserted | advisory_error\"\n1420: \n1421:       step_refresh_memory_context:\n1422:         action: \"Refresh focused Spec Kit Memory context before the next prompt render\"\n1423:         mcp_tool: memory_context\n1424:         invocation: 'memory_context({ input: \"{research_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true })'\n1425:         timeout_seconds: 5\n1426:         use_response:\n1427:           - \"Update memory_context_prompt_line with a concise summary for the next step_dispatch_iteration.pre_dispatch.generate_summary.\"\n1428:         failure_policy:\n1429:           mcp_error: \"non-fatal; log advisory warning and continue with the previous memory_context_prompt_line\"\n1430:           timeout: \"non-fatal after timeout_seconds; log advisory warning and continue with the previous memory_context_prompt_line\"\n1431:         outputs:\n1432:           - memory_context_prompt_line: \"Fresh focused context summary for the next iteration prompt\"\n1433:           - memory_context_refresh_status: \"refreshed | advisory_error\"\n1434: \n1435:       step_evaluate_results:\n1436:         action: \"Verify iteration outputs and extract metrics\"\n1437:         verify:\n1438:           - file_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1439:           - jsonl_appended: \"New iteration record in state.jsonl\"\n1440:           - strategy_updated: \"Reducer refreshed strategy machine-owned sections\"\n1441:           - registry_updated: \"Reducer refreshed findings-registry.json\"\n1442:         extract:\n1443:           - newInfoRatio: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1444:           - findings_count: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1445:           - status: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1446:           - latest_focus: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1447:         on_missing_outputs:\n1448:           action: \"Mark iteration as 'error', continue to next\"\n1449:           # Canonical iteration record: include mode, sessionId, generation, durationMs, keyQuestions, answeredQuestions\n1450:           # so the reducer can persist the failure without dropping the iteration. Schema source: state-format.md §Iteration Records.\n1451:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"error\",\"focus\":\"{next_focus}\",\"findingsCount\":0,\"newInfoRatio\":0.0,\"keyQuestions\":[],\"answeredQuestions\":[],\"durationMs\":0,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n1452: \n1453:       step_telemetry_heartbeat_progress:\n1454:         action: \"Emit a single-loop progress row when iteration state changes\"\n1455:         skip_when: \"config.fanout is present\"\n1456:         command: |\n1457:           node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n1458:           import { existsSync, readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n1459: \n1460:           import { appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts';\n1461:           import observabilityEvents from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/observability-events.cjs';\n1462: \n1463:           const { appendObservabilityEvent } = observabilityEvents;\n1464:           const stateLogPath = '{state_paths.state_log}';\n1465:           const timestamp = '{ISO_8601_NOW}';\n1466:           const sessionId = '{config.lineage.sessionId}';\n1467:           const generation = Number('{config.lineage.generation}');\n1468:           const observabilityPath = '{state_paths.packet_dir}/observability-events.jsonl';\n1469: \n1470:           function readRecords(path) {\n1471:             if (!existsSync(path)) return [];\n1472:             return readFileSync(path, 'utf8')\n1473:               .split(/\\r?\\n/)\n1474:               .map((line) => line.trim())\n1475:               .filter(Boolean)\n1476:               .map((line) => JSON.parse(line));\n1477:           }\n1478: \n1479:           function elapsedSince(value) {\n1480:             const startedAtMs = Date.parse(String(value ?? ''));\n1481:             const nowMs = Date.parse(timestamp);\n1482:             if (!Number.isFinite(startedAtMs) || !Number.isFinite(nowMs)) return 0;\n1483:             return Math.max(0, nowMs - startedAtMs);\n1484:           }\n1485: \n1486:           const records = readRecords(stateLogPath);\n1487:           const iterations = records.filter((record) => record.type === 'iteration');\n1488:           const latest = iterations.at(-1) ?? {};\n1489:           const startedAt = records.find((record) => typeof record.createdAt === 'string')?.createdAt\n1490:             ?? records.find((record) => typeof record.timestamp === 'string')?.timestamp\n1491:             ?? timestamp;\n1492:           const elapsedMs = elapsedSince(startedAt);\n1493:           const score = Number.isFinite(Number(latest.newInfoRatio)) ? Number(latest.newInfoRatio) : 0;\n1494:           const run = Number.isFinite(Number(latest.run)) ? Number(latest.run) : Number('{current_iteration}');\n1495:           const status = typeof latest.status === 'string' ? latest.status : 'unknown';\n1496:           const row = {\n1497:             event: 'progress',\n1498:             label: 'single',\n1499:             at: timestamp,\n1500:             duration_ms: elapsedMs,\n1501:             loop_type: 'research',\n1502:             sessionId,\n1503:             generation,\n1504:             run,\n1505:             status,\n1506:             gauges: { iterations: iterations.length, elapsed_ms: elapsedMs, score },\n1507:           };\n1508: \n1509:           const appended = appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic('{state_paths.status_ledger}', row, {\n1510:             diffData: { event: row.event, label: row.label, sessionId, generation, run, status, gauges: { iterations: iterations.length, score } },\n1511:             diffField: 'state_hash',\n1512:           });\n1513:           if (appended) {\n1514:             try {\n1515:               appendObservabilityEvent(observabilityPath, row, {\n1516:                 producer: 'deep-research-auto',\n1517:                 stream: 'single-loop-telemetry',\n1518:                 subject: { label: row.label, sessionId, generation, run },\n1519:                 event: row.event,\n1520:                 status,\n1521:               });\n1522:             } catch {}\n1523:           }\n1524:           EOF\n1525:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1526:         outputs:\n1527:           - status_ledger_progress: \"A fan-out-shaped status row with label single and event progress\"\n1528: \n1529:       step_generate_dashboard:\n1530:         action: \"Generate or refresh the human-readable dashboard\"\n1531:         read:\n1532:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1533:           - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n1534:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 700-1534. Use offset=1535 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"        action: \"Persist a first-class blocked_stop event when the legal-stop decision tree returns blocked\"\n        if_blocked:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergence\":{\"pass\":{gate_convergence_pass},\"score\":{gate_convergence_score}},\"keyQuestionCoverage\":{\"pass\":{gate_key_question_coverage_pass},\"answered\":{answered_count},\"total\":{total_questions}},\"evidenceDensity\":{\"pass\":{gate_evidence_density_pass},\"sources\":{gate_evidence_density_sources}},\"hotspotSaturation\":{\"pass\":{gate_hotspot_saturation_pass}}},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"Graph convergence blocked STOP. Failed blockers: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n          set:\n            decision: \"CONTINUE\"\n            reason: \"blockedStop\"\n            stop_blocked: false\n\n      step_handle_convergence:\n        action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n        if_stop:\n          branch_on: \"convergence_mode == 'divergent' AND reason is in ['composite_converged', 'all_questions_answered']\"\n          if_divergent_eligible:\n            eligibility_contract:\n              required_decision: \"STOP\"\n              eligible_reasons: [composite_converged, all_questions_answered]\n              excluded_reasons: [maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, minIterationsNotReached, error, manualStop, userPaused]\n              fail_closed: \"Any missing or ambiguous reason uses if_existing_terminal_path without preparing a pivot.\"\n            steps:","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml","text":"        action: \"Persist a first-class blocked_stop event when the legal-stop decision tree returns blocked\"\n        if_blocked:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergence\":{\"pass\":{gate_convergence_pass},\"score\":{gate_convergence_score}},\"keyQuestionCoverage\":{\"pass\":{gate_key_question_coverage_pass},\"answered\":{answered_count},\"total\":{total_questions}},\"evidenceDensity\":{\"pass\":{gate_evidence_density_pass},\"sources\":{gate_evidence_density_sources}},\"hotspotSaturation\":{\"pass\":{gate_hotspot_saturation_pass}}},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"Graph convergence blocked STOP. Failed blockers: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n          set:\n            decision: \"CONTINUE\"\n            reason: \"blockedStop\"\n            stop_blocked: false\n\n      step_handle_convergence:\n        action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n        if_stop:\n          branch_on: \"convergence_mode == 'divergent' AND reason is in ['composite_converged', 'all_questions_answered']\"\n          if_divergent_eligible:\n            eligibility_contract:\n              required_decision: \"STOP\"\n              eligible_reasons: [composite_converged, all_questions_answered]\n              excluded_reasons: [maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, minIterationsNotReached, error, manualStop, userPaused]\n              fail_closed: \"Any missing or ambiguous reason uses if_existing_terminal_path without preparing a pivot.\"\n            steps:\n              step_prepare_divergent_pivot:\n                action: \"Generate state-grounded research candidates and prepare or resume the pivot transaction\"\n                command: |\n                  node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n                  import {\n                    buildResearchPivotPreparationInput,\n                    renderResearchPivotSeatPrompt,\n                  } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/divergent-research-pivot.ts';\n                  import {\n                    preparePivotTransaction,\n                  } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n\n                  const input = buildResearchPivotPreparationInput({\n                    artifactRoot: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n                    configPath: '{state_paths.config}',\n                    stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                    strategyPath: '{state_paths.strategy}',\n                    registryPath: '{state_paths.registry}',\n                    currentIteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n                    maxIterations: Number('{max_iterations}'),\n                    triggerReason: '{reason}',\n                  });\n                  const prepared = await preparePivotTransaction(input);\n                  const seatPrompts = prepared.status === 'pending'\n                    ? Object.fromEntries(prepared.missingSeats.map((seat) => [\n                        seat.id,\n                        renderResearchPivotSeatPrompt(seat, prepared.dispatchContext),\n                      ]))\n                    : {};\n                  process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify({\n                    ...prepared,\n                    seatPrompts,\n                    boundaryRejections: input.boundaryRejections,\n                  })}\\n`);\n                  EOF\n                working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n                outputs:\n                  - pivot_prepare_json: \"The complete parsed JSON result\"\n                  - pivot_prepare_status: \"status from the prepare result\"\n                  - pivot_id: \"pivotId from the prepare result\"\n                  - pivot_paths_json: \"paths from the prepare result as JSON\"\n                  - pivot_resumed: \"resumed from the prepare result\"\n                  - pivot_missing_seat_ids: \"missingSeats ids from a pending result\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_json: \"The seat-001 mandate object from missingSeats\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_json: \"The seat-002 mandate object from missingSeats\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_json: \"The seat-003 mandate object from missingSeats\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_prompt: \"seatPrompts['seat-001']\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_prompt: \"seatPrompts['seat-002']\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_prompt: \"seatPrompts['seat-003']\"\n                  - pivot_dispatch_context_json: \"dispatchContext from a pending result as JSON\"\n                short_circuit: \"When status is completed or failed, skip all dispatch and record steps and bind this result as pivot_result.\"\n\n              step_dispatch_pivot_seat_001:\n                action: \"Natively dispatch the analytical research direction-selection seat\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-001'\"\n                capture_timing: true\n                if_native:\n                  dispatch:\n                    agent: deep-research\n                    model: opus\n                    context_source: \"pivot_seat_001_prompt\"\n                  wait_for_completion: true\n                failure_contract: \"A native dispatch failure binds status=rejected, a {name,message} error, and the measured timestamps/duration, then proceeds to step_record_pivot_seat_001.\"\n                outputs:\n                  - pivot_seat_001_dispatch_status: \"fulfilled or rejected\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_output_json: \"Raw native return serialized as JSON when fulfilled\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_error_json: \"{name,message} when rejected\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_started_at_iso: \"Dispatch start timestamp\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_completed_at_iso: \"Dispatch completion timestamp\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_duration_ms: \"Dispatch duration in milliseconds\"\n\n              step_record_pivot_seat_001:\n                action: \"Durably record the seat-001 native dispatch outcome\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-001'\"\n                command: |\n                  node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n                  import { recordPivotSeatResult } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n                  const status = '{pivot_seat_001_dispatch_status}';\n                  const outcome = status === 'fulfilled'\n                    ? { status, output: {pivot_seat_001_output_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_001_duration_ms}') }\n                    : { status: 'rejected', error: {pivot_seat_001_error_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_001_duration_ms}') };\n                  process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(recordPivotSeatResult({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', seat: {pivot_seat_001_json}, outcome }))}\\n`);\n                  EOF\n                working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n\n              step_dispatch_pivot_seat_002:\n                action: \"Natively dispatch the critical research direction-selection seat\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-002'\"\n                capture_timing: true\n                if_native:\n                  dispatch:\n                    agent: deep-research\n                    model: opus\n                    context_source: \"pivot_seat_002_prompt\"\n                  wait_for_completion: true\n                failure_contract: \"A native dispatch failure binds status=rejected, a {name,message} error, and the measured timestamps/duration, then proceeds to step_record_pivot_seat_002.\"\n                outputs:\n                  - pivot_seat_002_dispatch_status: \"fulfilled or rejected\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_output_json: \"Raw native return serialized as JSON when fulfilled\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_error_json: \"{name,message} when rejected\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_started_at_iso: \"Dispatch start timestamp\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_completed_at_iso: \"Dispatch completion timestamp\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_duration_ms: \"Dispatch duration in milliseconds\"\n\n              step_record_pivot_seat_002:\n                action: \"Durably record the seat-002 native dispatch outcome\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-002'\"\n                command: |\n                  node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n                  import { recordPivotSeatResult } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n                  const status = '{pivot_seat_002_dispatch_status}';\n                  const outcome = status === 'fulfilled'\n                    ? { status, output: {pivot_seat_002_output_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_002_duration_ms}') }\n                    : { status: 'rejected', error: {pivot_seat_002_error_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_002_duration_ms}') };\n                  process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(recordPivotSeatResult({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', seat: {pivot_seat_002_json}, outcome }))}\\n`);\n                  EOF\n                working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n\n              step_dispatch_pivot_seat_003:\n                action: \"Natively dispatch the pragmatic research direction-selection seat\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-003'\"\n                capture_timing: true\n                if_native:\n                  dispatch:\n                    agent: deep-research\n                    model: opus\n                    context_source: \"pivot_seat_003_prompt\"\n                  wait_for_completion: true\n                failure_contract: \"A native dispatch failure binds status=rejected, a {name,message} error, and the measured timestamps/duration, then proceeds to step_record_pivot_seat_003.\"\n                outputs:\n                  - pivot_seat_003_dispatch_status: \"fulfilled or rejected\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_output_json: \"Raw native return serialized as JSON when fulfilled\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_error_json: \"{name,message} when rejected\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_started_at_iso: \"Dispatch start timestamp\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_completed_at_iso: \"Dispatch completion timestamp\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_duration_ms: \"Dispatch duration in milliseconds\"\n\n              step_record_pivot_seat_003:\n                action: \"Durably record the seat-003 native dispatch outcome\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-003'\"\n                command: |\n                  node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n                  import { recordPivotSeatResult } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n                  const status = '{pivot_seat_003_dispatch_status}';\n                  const outcome = status === 'fulfilled'\n                    ? { status, output: {pivot_seat_003_output_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_003_duration_ms}') }\n                    : { status: 'rejected', error: {pivot_seat_003_error_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_003_duration_ms}') };\n                  process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(recordPivotSeatResult({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', seat: {pivot_seat_003_json}, outcome }))}\\n`);\n                  EOF\n                working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n\n              step_finalize_divergent_pivot:\n                action: \"Finalize the prepared pivot after all missing native seats are durable\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending'\"\n                command: |\n                  node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n                  import { finalizePivotTransaction } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n                  process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(finalizePivotTransaction({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', resumed: {pivot_resumed} }))}\\n`);\n                  EOF\n                working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n                outputs:\n                  - pivot_finalize_json: \"The complete parsed final result\"\n\n              step_resolve_divergent_pivot_result:\n                action: \"Use prepare's terminal result on resume/short-circuit, otherwise use finalize's result\"\n                branch_on: \"pivot_prepare_status\"\n                if_pending: { bind: { pivot_result: \"{pivot_finalize_json}\" } }\n                if_completed_or_failed: { bind: { pivot_result: \"{pivot_prepare_json}\" } }\n\n              step_apply_divergent_pivot_result:\n                action: \"Adopt a successful focus or fail closed to the existing synthesis path\"\n                branch_on: \"pivot_result.status\"\n                if_completed:\n                  set:\n                    next_focus: \"{pivot_result.restoredFocus}\"\n                    pivot_lineage: \"Pivot {pivot_result.pivotId} selected {pivot_result.selectedCandidate.id} from source iteration {current_iteration}.\"\n                    saturated_directions: \"{pivot_result.completedEvent.saturatedDirections}\"\n                  command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n                  log: \"Divergent pivot {pivot_result.pivotId} restored focus to {pivot_result.restoredFocus}; continuing iteration {current_iteration}.\"\n                  proceed_to: step_rejected_pattern_cache\n                if_failed:\n                  log: \"Divergent pivot {pivot_result.pivotId} failed closed ({pivot_result.failureReason}); proceeding to synthesis.\"\n                  skip_to: phase_synthesis\n            on_error:\n              log: \"Divergent pivot integration error; failing closed to the existing synthesis path.\"\n              skip_to: phase_synthesis\n          if_existing_terminal_path:\n            log: \"Loop stopping. Reason: {reason}\"\n            skip_to: phase_synthesis\n        if_stuck_recovery:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"outcome\":\"recovered\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"Stuck detected ({stuck_count} consecutive no-progress). Entering recovery.\"\n          set: { next_focus: \"RECOVERY: Widen scope. Try fundamentally different approach. Least-explored question: {least_explored}\" }\n          reset: { stuck_count: 0 }\n        if_continue:\n          log: \"Iteration {current_iteration}: Continuing. Focus: {next_focus}\"\n\n      step_rejected_pattern_cache:\n        action: \"Apply reducer-derived rejected-pattern suppression before dispatch candidate selection\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        candidate_sources:\n          next_focus:\n            category: \"next-focus\"\n            values:\n              - \"{next_focus}\"\n              - \"{remaining_questions_list}\"\n              - \"{carried_forward_open_questions}\"\n          recovery:\n            category: \"recovery\"\n            values:\n              - \"{recovery_strategy}\"\n              - \"{least_explored}\"\n          ideas:\n            category: \"ideas\"\n            values:\n              - \"{promoted_ideas_list}\"\n            optional_file: \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/research-ideas.md\"\n        algorithm: |\n          Use registry.rejectedPatternIndex and registry.promotedIdeas from the latest\n          reducer pass as the source of truth.\n          Compare normalized exact text first. Then compare fuzzy similarity with\n          rejected_pattern_fuzzy_threshold, but only when candidate and rejected categories\n          are compatible. Remove suppressed candidates from next_focus, recovery, and ideas\n          selection before rendering the dispatch prompt. If all candidates are suppressed,\n          halt for operator input instead of reusing a rejected idea.\n        outputs:\n          - accepted_next_focus: \"First unsuppressed next-focus candidate, or null\"\n          - accepted_recovery_candidate: \"First unsuppressed recovery candidate, or null\"\n          - accepted_idea_candidate: \"First unsuppressed ideas candidate, or null\"\n          - rejected_candidate_matches: \"Suppressed candidate diagnostics from registry.suppressedCandidates plus any current-step matches\"\n        if_next_focus_suppressed:\n          set: { next_focus: \"{accepted_next_focus || accepted_recovery_candidate || accepted_idea_candidate}\" }\n          log: \"Rejected-pattern cache suppressed the prior candidate; dispatching the next accepted candidate.\"\n        if_all_candidates_suppressed:\n          halt: true\n          message: \"All next-focus, recovery, and ideas candidates match active rejected patterns. Remove/reset the rejected pattern or provide a new focus.\"\n\n      step_ideas_backlog_lifecycle:\n        action: \"Track reducer-owned observed/promoted/rejected idea lifecycle before dispatch\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n        lifecycle:\n          observed_event: \"idea_observed\"\n          promoted_event: \"idea_promoted\"\n          rejected_event: \"idea_rejected\"\n          min_observations: \"{min_idea_observations}\"\n          authority: \"Leaf agents emit observations only; reducer emits promotions and owns ranking.\"\n        validate:\n          - \"If new leaf-authored output includes idea_promoted, fail validation; only reducer output may append idea_promoted.\"\n          - \"If promoted_ideas_count > 0 and next_focus is empty or all questions are resolved, prefer the first unsuppressed promoted idea.\"\n          - \"If suppressed_ideas_count > 0, do not render those ideas into dispatch context.\"\n        outputs:\n          - observed_ideas_count: \"Reducer-derived observed ideas count\"\n          - promoted_ideas_count: \"Reducer-derived promoted ideas count after minIdeaObservations\"\n          - suppressed_ideas_count: \"Reducer-derived rejected/suppressed ideas count\"\n          - accepted_idea_candidate: \"First unsuppressed promoted idea, or null\"\n\n      step_normalize_pause_events:\n        action: \"Normalize pause and recovery lifecycle events to the frozen STOP_REASONS enum at emission time\"\n        stop_reasons_enum: [converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused]\n        rule_pause_sentinel:\n          raw_event_forbidden: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"paused\"}'\n          canonical_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n        rule_stuck_recovery:\n          raw_event_forbidden: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuck_recovery\"}'\n          canonical_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"outcome\":\"recovered\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n\n      step_marker_scan:\n        action: \"H-2 loop-prevention guard: scan previous iteration's rendered prompt for nested research marker\"\n        algorithm: |\n          if current_iteration > 1:\n            PREV_PROMPT_PATH = \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{previous_iteration}.md\"\n            if file_exists(PREV_PROMPT_PATH):\n              PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE = head -1 of PREV_PROMPT_PATH\n              if PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE matches ^(DEEP-REVIEW|DEEP-RESEARCH|CODE-REVIEW)$:\n                log \"ERROR: nested research-of-review loop detected (marker found in previous iteration prompt). Aborting.\"\n                halt with exit code 2\n        note: |\n          False-positive prevention: only matches when the first line is exactly one of the\n          three canonical markers. Markers appearing in comments or body text are ignored.\n          True-positive triggers only when a previous iteration's rendered prompt literally\n          starts with a deep-loop marker, indicating a nested research-of-review dispatch.\n\n      step_dispatch_iteration:\n        action: \"Dispatch one iteration via the selected executor\"\n        resolve_executor:\n          source: \"config.executor\"\n          loader: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n        pre_dispatch:\n          generate_summary: |\n            STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n            Segment: {current_segment} | Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n            Questions: {answered_count}/{total_questions} answered | Last focus: {last_focus}\n            Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n            {resource_map_prompt_line}\n            {memory_context_prompt_line}\n            Next focus: {next_focus}\n          render_prompt_pack:\n            template_path: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/prompt-pack-iteration.md.tmpl\"\n            renderer: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n            output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n            variables:\n              state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"\n              research_topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n              current_iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n              max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n              next_focus: \"{next_focus}\"\n              remaining_questions_list: \"{remaining_questions_list}\"\n              carried_forward_open_questions: \"{carried_forward_open_questions}\"\n              last_3_summaries: \"{last_3_summaries}\"\n              pivot_lineage: \"{pivot_lineage}\"\n              saturated_directions: \"{saturated_directions}\"\n              state_paths_config: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n              state_paths_state_log: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n              state_paths_strategy: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n              state_paths_registry: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n              state_paths_iteration_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n              state_paths_delta_pattern: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n        pre_dispatch_audit:\n          skip_when: \"config.executor.type == 'native'\"\n          call: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts#writeFirstRecordExecutor\"\n          args:\n            stateLogPath: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n            executor: \"{config.executor}\"\n            iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n        branch_on: \"config.executor.type\"\n        if_native:\n          dispatch:\n            agent: deep-research\n            model: opus\n            context_source: \"rendered_prompt_pack\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n        if_cli_claude_code:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n            import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n\n            import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n            import { resolveClaudePermissionMode } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n\n            const executor = {\n              kind: 'cli-claude-code',\n              model: '{config.executor.model}',\n              reasoningEffort: '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}',\n              serviceTier: '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}',\n              sandboxMode: '{config.executor.sandboxMode}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.sandboxMode}',\n              timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n            };\n            const args = [\n              '-p',\n              readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n              '--model',\n              executor.model,\n              '--permission-mode',\n              resolveClaudePermissionMode(executor.sandboxMode),\n              '--output-format',\n              'text',\n            ];\n            if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n              args.push('--effort', executor.reasoningEffort);\n            }\n\n            const dispatchFacts = {\n              command: 'deep/research',\n              mode: 'research',\n              specFolder: '{spec_folder}',\n              artifactDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n              iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n              executorKind: '{config.executor.type}',\n              branchId: '{config.executor.type}',\n              sessionId: '{config.lineage.sessionId}',\n              generation: Number('{config.lineage.generation}'),\n            };\n            const dispatchId = 'research-i{current_iteration}-g{config.lineage.generation}';\n            process.exit(\n              runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n                command: 'claude',\n                args,\n                cwd: '{repo_root}',\n                timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n                stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                executor,\n                iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n                receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n                dispatchId,\n              }),\n            );\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          notes:\n            - \"sandboxMode maps to permission-mode: read-only -> plan, workspace-write -> acceptEdits, danger-full-access -> bypassPermissions\"\n            - \"claude-code has no serviceTier flag\"\n            - \"claude-code supports --effort for reasoning depth\"\n        record_executor_audit:\n          skip_when: \"config.executor.type == 'native'\"\n          target: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          field: \"executor\"\n          value:\n            kind: \"{config.executor.type}\"\n            model: \"{config.executor.model}\"\n            reasoningEffort: \"{config.executor.reasoningEffort}\"\n            serviceTier: \"{config.executor.serviceTier}\"\n        if_cli_opencode:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n            import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n\n            import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n\n            const reasoningEffort = '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}';\n            const executor = {\n              kind: 'cli-opencode',\n              model: '{config.executor.model}',\n              configDir: null,\n              reasoningEffort,\n              serviceTier: null,\n              sandboxMode: null,\n              timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n              governor: null,\n            };\n            const promptBody = readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8');\n            const message = 'Resolved route: mode=research; target_agent=@deep-research; execution=single_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true'\n              + '\\n\\n'\n              + promptBody;\n            const args = [\n              'run',\n              '--model',\n              executor.model,\n              '--format',\n              'json',\n              '--dangerously-skip-permissions',\n              '--pure',\n              '--dir',\n              '{repo_root}',\n            ];\n            if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n              args.push('--variant', executor.reasoningEffort);\n            }\n            args.push(message);\n\n            const dispatchFacts = {\n              command: 'deep/research',\n              mode: 'research',\n              specFolder: '{spec_folder}',\n              artifactDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n              iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n              executorKind: '{config.executor.type}',\n              branchId: '{config.executor.type}',\n              sessionId: '{config.lineage.sessionId}',\n              generation: Number('{config.lineage.generation}'),\n            };\n            const dispatchId = 'research-i{current_iteration}-g{config.lineage.generation}';\n            process.exit(\n              runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n                command: 'opencode',\n                args,\n                cwd: '{repo_root}',\n                timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n                stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                executor,\n                iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n                // opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation;\n                // an empty input gives EOF stdin, equivalent to </dev/null.\n                input: '',\n                receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n                dispatchId,\n              }),\n            );\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          notes:\n            - \"Routed through runAuditedExecutorCommand so opencode produces INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts; recursion guard + env allowlist enforced via buildExecutorDispatchEnv\"\n            - \"input:'' yields closed stdin (EOF), equivalent to </dev/null — opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup and hangs at 0% CPU after +60s snapshot prune without it (the `cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode` mode's SKILL.md (`.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/SKILL.md`) §4 ALWAYS rule)\"\n            - \"opencode run takes a positional message; prompt is the route-proof preamble + iteration body\"\n            - \"--variant maps reasoningEffort to opencode's provider-specific reasoning lever (e.g., high, medium, minimal)\"\n            - \"--dangerously-skip-permissions enables hands-off automation; sandboxMode='read-only' is not currently honored (no opencode equivalent)\"\n            - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude Code/raw shell). the `cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode` mode's SKILL.md (`.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/SKILL.md`) §SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"\n        if_cli_codex:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n            import { execFileSync } from 'node:child_process';\n\n            import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n\n            // Fail closed: a requested codex executor must dispatch codex or abort,\n            // never silently degrade to another executor. Undetected absence is what\n            // got Codex deprecated before, so the branch exits non-zero when the\n            // binary is missing instead of falling through to a native/other path.\n            let codexAvailable = false;\n            try {\n              execFileSync('/bin/sh', ['-c', 'command -v codex >/dev/null 2>&1'], { stdio: 'ignore' });\n              codexAvailable = true;\n            } catch {}\n            if (!codexAvailable) {\n              console.error('cli-codex executor unavailable: command -v codex failed');\n              process.exit(1);\n            }\n\n            const reasoningEffort = '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}';\n            const serviceTier = '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}';\n            const model = '{config.executor.model}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.model}';\n            const executor = {\n              kind: 'cli-codex',\n              model,\n              configDir: null,\n              reasoningEffort,\n              serviceTier,\n              sandboxMode: 'workspace-write',\n              timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n              governor: null,\n            };\n\n            const promptBody = readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8');\n\n            // codex reads the iteration prompt from stdin via the trailing '-'. A research\n            // iteration must WRITE its own iteration file, delta and state record, so the\n            // sandbox is workspace-write — read-only would block those required writes.\n            // approval_policy=never keeps the run non-interactive.\n            const args = ['exec'];\n            if (model) {\n              args.push('--model', model);\n            }\n            args.push('-c', 'model_reasoning_effort=' + (reasoningEffort || 'medium'));\n            if (serviceTier) {\n              args.push('-c', 'service_tier=' + serviceTier);\n            }\n            args.push('-c', 'approval_policy=never', '--sandbox', executor.sandboxMode, '-');\n\n            const dispatchId = 'research-i{current_iteration}-g{config.lineage.generation}';\n            process.exit(\n              runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n                command: 'codex',\n                args,\n                cwd: '{repo_root}',\n                timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n                stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                executor,\n                iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n                input: promptBody,\n                receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n                dispatchId,\n              }),\n            );\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          notes:\n            - \"Routed through runAuditedExecutorCommand so codex produces INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts; recursion guard (CODEX_SESSION_ID) + env allowlist (CODEX_/OPENAI_/AZURE_OPENAI_) enforced via buildExecutorDispatchEnv\"\n            - \"Fails closed when the codex binary is absent (exit 1) — parity with the fan-out cli-codex lineage guard in fanout-run.cjs; codex routing never degrades to native\"\n            - \"codex exec reads the iteration prompt from stdin via the trailing '-' (input: promptBody); '-c model_reasoning_effort=' maps reasoning depth, default medium; '-c service_tier=' forwarded when configured\"\n            - \"--sandbox workspace-write is required so the iteration can write its own iteration file/delta/state record (read-only would fail the post-dispatch artifact gate); -c approval_policy=never keeps it non-interactive; --model omitted when unset so ~/.codex/config.toml default applies\"\n        post_dispatch_validate:\n          validator: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts#validateIterationOutputs\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/verify-iteration.cjs --loop-type research --artifact-dir {artifact_dir} --iteration {current_iteration}\"\n          command_note: \"Mechanical leaf-reliability gate: exit 0 = complete; non-zero prints one machine reason (iteration_file_missing|state_record_missing|route_proof_missing|route_proof_mismatch|delta_file_missing). The script enforces the artifact + route-proof contract instead of trusting the leaf to self-report, and a non-zero exit triggers on_failure.redispatch_once.\"\n          assert_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          assert_appended: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          assert_jsonl_fields: [type, iteration, newInfoRatio, status, focus, mode]\n          route_proof:\n            mode: research\n            target_agent: deep-research\n            agent_definition_loaded: true\n            resolved_route: \"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\"\n          dispatchReceipt:\n            receiptDir: \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts\"\n            dispatchId: \"research-i{current_iteration}-g{config.lineage.generation}\"\n          optional_jsonl_fields:\n            logOffset: \"Byte offset where the seekable log region starts\"\n            logSize: \"Byte length of the seekable log region\"\n            logPath: \"Absolute path to the file containing the seekable log region\"\n            skippedCount: \"Missed fixed-rate slots counted for the completed dispatch; 0 when no slot was missed\"\n            slotDurationMs: \"Monotonic elapsed duration for the completed dispatch slot\"\n          assert_canonical_type: \"iteration\"\n          assert_delta_file_exists: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n          assert_delta_file_has_iteration_record: true\n          on_failure:\n            action: \"emit schema_mismatch canonical conflict event\"\n            redispatch_once: \"On the FIRST failure of the mechanical command check for this iteration, re-run step_dispatch_iteration exactly once for the same iteration number, then re-run the check. If it still fails, record the iteration as error and continue. Never re-dispatch a given iteration more than once.\"\n            escalation: \"After 3 consecutive failures across iterations, trigger stuck_recovery event with diagnostic context\"\n          failure_reasons_reference:\n            - \"iteration_file_missing — iteration narrative markdown not written\"\n            - \"iteration_file_empty — iteration narrative markdown is zero bytes\"\n            - \"jsonl_not_appended — state log file did not grow since pre-dispatch snapshot\"\n            - \"jsonl_missing_fields — last state-log record omits required schema fields\"\n            - \"jsonl_parse_error — last state-log line is not valid JSON\"\n            - \"jsonl_wrong_type — last state-log record uses type!='iteration' (e.g. 'iteration_delta'); reducer will silently drop\"\n            - \"delta_file_missing — per-iteration deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl not written\"\n            - \"delta_file_empty — per-iteration delta file exists but has zero bytes\"\n            - \"delta_file_missing_iteration_record — delta file lacks any record with type='iteration'\"\n            - \"route_proof_missing — state-log or delta iteration record omits route-proof fields\"\n            - \"route_proof_mismatch — state-log or delta iteration record does not match the resolved deep route\"\n            - \"executor_missing — non-native executor did not record provenance\"\n            - \"dispatch_failure_logged — last record is an explicit dispatch_failure event\"\n\n      step_run_now_restore_check:\n        action: \"Record a run-now sentinel recreated during the completed dispatch\"\n        command: |\n          node <<'EOF'\n          const { appendFileSync, existsSync, readFileSync } = require('node:fs');\n\n          const stateLogPath = \"{state_paths.state_log}\";\n          const sentinelPath = \"{state_paths.run_now_sentinel}\";\n          const timestamp = \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\";\n          const sessionId = \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\";\n          const generation = Number(\"{config.lineage.generation}\");\n          const run = Number(\"{current_iteration}\");\n\n          function hasAcceptedCurrentRun() {\n            if (!existsSync(stateLogPath)) return false;\n            const lines = readFileSync(stateLogPath, \"utf8\").trim().split(/\\r?\\n/).filter(Boolean);\n            for (let index = lines.length - 1; index >= 0; index -= 1) {\n              const record = JSON.parse(lines[index]);\n              if (record.run !== run || record.sessionId !== sessionId) continue;\n              if (record.event === \"run_now_accepted\") return true;\n              if (record.event === \"run_now_rejected\") return false;\n            }\n            return false;\n          }\n\n          if (existsSync(sentinelPath) && hasAcceptedCurrentRun()) {\n            appendFileSync(\n              stateLogPath,\n              `${JSON.stringify({\n                type: \"event\",\n                event: \"run_now_restored\",\n                mode: \"research\",\n                run,\n                sentinelPath,\n                timestamp,\n                sessionId,\n                generation,\n              })}\\n`,\n              \"utf8\",\n            );\n          }\n          EOF\n        outputs:\n          - run_now_restored: \"Emitted when an operator recreates the sentinel before the accepted dispatch completes\"\n\n      step_reduce_state:\n        action: \"Run the reducer to synchronize registry, dashboard, and strategy\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n        inputs:\n          latestJSONLDelta: \"Latest JSONL records written since the previous iteration\"\n          newIterationFile: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          priorReducedState: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n        outputs:\n          - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log} question_conflict events when inbox text disagrees with registry-owned question text\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log} idempotent idea_promoted events when observed ideas reach minIdeaObservations\"\n          - \"{state_paths.registry} observedIdeas, promotedIdeas, suppressedIdeas, rejectedPatterns, and suppressedCandidates from idea lifecycle events\"\n        failure_modes:\n          malformed_delta: \"skip + warn\"\n          missing_iteration_file: \"no-op + error\"\n          schema_mismatch: \"reject + conflict event\"\n          question_conflict: \"keep registry value + append question_conflict event with inboxValue, registryValue, and operatorDecision\"\n        guarantee: \"Idempotent for identical inputs\"\n\n      step_graph_upsert:\n        action: \"Persist the latest iteration graph delta after the reducer refresh and after the iteration file exists\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n        extract:\n          - latest_graph_events: \"Read graphEvents from the latest iteration record, else []\"\n          - graph_upsert_nodes_json: \"Map latest_graph_events where type == 'node' to node payloads with label -> name and preserve remaining node fields\"\n          - graph_upsert_edges_json: \"Map latest_graph_events where type == 'edge' to edge payloads with source -> sourceId, target -> targetId, relation -> uppercase(relation), and preserve remaining edge fields\"\n          - graph_upsert_event_count: \"Count mapped node and edge events\"\n        if_graph_events_present:\n          bash: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"research\\\" --session-id \\\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\\\" --nodes '{graph_upsert_nodes_json}' --edges '{graph_upsert_edges_json}'\"\n          note: \"Skip silently when graphEvents is missing or empty.\"\n        if_graph_events_missing:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_memory_upsert_iteration:\n        action: \"Upsert the canonical iteration evidence into Spec Kit Memory after reducer and graph persistence\"\n        mcp_tool: memory_save\n        invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\" })'\n        timeout_seconds: 5\n        idempotency: \"Re-running the same iteration file is safe because the memory backend upserts by path/content.\"\n        failure_policy:\n          mcp_error: \"non-fatal; log advisory warning and continue\"\n          timeout: \"non-fatal after timeout_seconds; log advisory warning and continue\"\n        outputs:\n          - memory_upsert_iteration_file: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          - memory_upsert_status: \"upserted | advisory_error\"\n\n      step_refresh_memory_context:\n        action: \"Refresh focused Spec Kit Memory context before the next prompt render\"\n        mcp_tool: memory_context\n        invocation: 'memory_context({ input: \"{research_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true })'\n        timeout_seconds: 5\n        use_response:\n          - \"Update memory_context_prompt_line with a concise summary for the next step_dispatch_iteration.pre_dispatch.generate_summary.\"\n        failure_policy:\n          mcp_error: \"non-fatal; log advisory warning and continue with the previous memory_context_prompt_line\"\n          timeout: \"non-fatal after timeout_seconds; log advisory warning and continue with the previous memory_context_prompt_line\"\n        outputs:\n          - memory_context_prompt_line: \"Fresh focused context summary for the next iteration prompt\"\n          - memory_context_refresh_status: \"refreshed | advisory_error\"\n\n      step_evaluate_results:\n        action: \"Verify iteration outputs and extract metrics\"\n        verify:\n          - file_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          - jsonl_appended: \"New iteration record in state.jsonl\"\n          - strategy_updated: \"Reducer refreshed strategy machine-owned sections\"\n          - registry_updated: \"Reducer refreshed findings-registry.json\"\n        extract:\n          - newInfoRatio: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - findings_count: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - status: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - latest_focus: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n        on_missing_outputs:\n          action: \"Mark iteration as 'error', continue to next\"\n          # Canonical iteration record: include mode, sessionId, generation, durationMs, keyQuestions, answeredQuestions\n          # so the reducer can persist the failure without dropping the iteration. Schema source: state-format.md §Iteration Records.\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"error\",\"focus\":\"{next_focus}\",\"findingsCount\":0,\"newInfoRatio\":0.0,\"keyQuestions\":[],\"answeredQuestions\":[],\"durationMs\":0,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n\n      step_telemetry_heartbeat_progress:\n        action: \"Emit a single-loop progress row when iteration state changes\"\n        skip_when: \"config.fanout is present\"\n        command: |\n          node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n          import { existsSync, readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n\n          import { appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts';\n          import observabilityEvents from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/observability-events.cjs';\n\n          const { appendObservabilityEvent } = observabilityEvents;\n          const stateLogPath = '{state_paths.state_log}';\n          const timestamp = '{ISO_8601_NOW}';\n          const sessionId = '{config.lineage.sessionId}';\n          const generation = Number('{config.lineage.generation}');\n          const observabilityPath = '{state_paths.packet_dir}/observability-events.jsonl';\n\n          function readRecords(path) {\n            if (!existsSync(path)) return [];\n            return readFileSync(path, 'utf8')\n              .split(/\\r?\\n/)\n              .map((line) => line.trim())\n              .filter(Boolean)\n              .map((line) => JSON.parse(line));\n          }\n\n          function elapsedSince(value) {\n            const startedAtMs = Date.parse(String(value ?? ''));\n            const nowMs = Date.parse(timestamp);\n            if (!Number.isFinite(startedAtMs) || !Number.isFinite(nowMs)) return 0;\n            return Math.max(0, nowMs - startedAtMs);\n          }\n\n          const records = readRecords(stateLogPath);\n          const iterations = records.filter((record) => record.type === 'iteration');\n          const latest = iterations.at(-1) ?? {};\n          const startedAt = records.find((record) => typeof record.createdAt === 'string')?.createdAt\n            ?? records.find((record) => typeof record.timestamp === 'string')?.timestamp\n            ?? timestamp;\n          const elapsedMs = elapsedSince(startedAt);\n          const score = Number.isFinite(Number(latest.newInfoRatio)) ? Number(latest.newInfoRatio) : 0;\n          const run = Number.isFinite(Number(latest.run)) ? Number(latest.run) : Number('{current_iteration}');\n          const status = typeof latest.status === 'string' ? latest.status : 'unknown';\n          const row = {\n            event: 'progress',\n            label: 'single',\n            at: timestamp,\n            duration_ms: elapsedMs,\n            loop_type: 'research',\n            sessionId,\n            generation,\n            run,\n            status,\n            gauges: { iterations: iterations.length, elapsed_ms: elapsedMs, score },\n          };\n\n          const appended = appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic('{state_paths.status_ledger}', row, {\n            diffData: { event: row.event, label: row.label, sessionId, generation, run, status, gauges: { iterations: iterations.length, score } },\n            diffField: 'state_hash',\n          });\n          if (appended) {\n            try {\n              appendObservabilityEvent(observabilityPath, row, {\n                producer: 'deep-research-auto',\n                stream: 'single-loop-telemetry',\n                subject: { label: row.label, sessionId, generation, run },\n                event: row.event,\n                status,\n              });\n            } catch {}\n          }\n          EOF\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        outputs:\n          - status_ledger_progress: \"A fan-out-shaped status row with label single and event progress\"\n\n      step_generate_dashboard:\n        action: \"Generate or refresh the human-readable dashboard\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"","lineStart":700,"lineEnd":1534,"totalLines":1535,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml","time":{"start":1784624008130,"end":1784624008137}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0021727ff6bc4ba6016a5f33877ff481918c4a0da82b753c5c"}},"id":"prt_f83e149c70016wEnU3QjpR8jYP","sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","messageID":"msg_f83e13931001Dr7K2ba2C7mC7I"}}
