Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/spec.md\",\"lockPath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/.deep-research.lock\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-21T08:55:18Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-high-fast-1784623934648-kt3qkt\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_synthesis_deferred\",\"reason\":\"detached-lineage scope permits writes only inside the lineage artifact directory\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-21T08:55:18Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-high-fast-1784623934648-kt3qkt\",\"generation\":1}\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,91 @@\n+# Deep Research Strategy: Literal Interface Command Prompts\n+\n+## 1. Research Topic\n+\n+Rewrite the five `/interface:*` commands as literal, self-contained design prompts while preserving the split where commands own intake and lifecycle, `sk-design` modes own taste and judgment, transports own realization, and `sk-code` owns application-code mutation.\n+\n+## 2. Non-Goals\n+\n+- Do not modify commands, presentation assets, skills, workflows, tests, or packet docs.\n+- Do not write anywhere outside this detached `sol-high-fast` lineage.\n+- Do not reopen the settled five-command namespace or stable workflow-mode mapping without contradictory evidence.\n+- Do not duplicate palettes, typography prescriptions, style menus, reference inventories, or mode-owned taste doctrine into commands.\n+- Do not settle unrelated styles-library structure or database-fate work.\n+\n+## 3. Stop Conditions\n+\n+- Complete exactly five iterations because `stopPolicy=max-iterations`.\n+- Produce concrete, substantially self-contained command-body proposals for all five `/interface:*` commands.\n+- Resolve the runtime-supported include/shared-fragment mechanism with direct repository evidence.\n+- Provide a durable authority/anti-duplication rule and a testable implementation plan.\n+\n+<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n+## 4. Key Questions (Remaining)\n+\n+- [ ] What exactly do the shipped command routers, presentation assets, and shared creation contract contain, and which literal-prompt qualities are absent?\n+- [ ] What complete literal body should each of the five commands contain so an agent receives an evocative, actionable creation brief rather than a thin route?\n+- [ ] What include, template injection, renderer, or generated-fragment mechanism does the current command runtime actually support?\n+- [ ] Which content must stay literal in each command, which content may be shared, and which doctrine must remain mode-owned to prevent drift?\n+- [ ] What exact file/change/test sequence can ship the rewrite without breaking route, intake, proof, handoff, or compatibility contracts?\n+<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n+\n+<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n+## 5. Answered Questions\n+\n+None yet.\n+<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n+\n+<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n+<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n+## 6. What Worked\n+\n+None yet.\n+<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n+\n+<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n+## 7. What Failed\n+\n+None yet.\n+<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n+\n+<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n+## 8. Exhausted Approaches\n+\n+- Replacing mode judgment with command-owned taste: already rejected by the authority split established in prior research.\n+- Treating the current shared contract alone as the requested literal-prompt deliverable: contradicted by the verified gap analysis.\n+<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n+\n+<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n+## 9. Ruled-Out Directions\n+\n+None yet.\n+<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n+\n+<!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n+## 10. Carried-Forward Open Questions\n+\n+None yet.\n+<!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n+\n+<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n+## 11. Next Focus\n+\n+Baseline the five shipped commands, their presentation assets, and `shared/creation-contract.md`; identify the precise delta between working routing architecture and the missing literal-prompt experience.\n+<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n+<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n+\n+## 12. Known Context\n+\n+- The parent gap analysis confirms that the 002 research produced literal templates but the build shipped thin routers plus a shared lifecycle contract. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/gap-analysis.md:109-147]\n+- The 002 synthesis defines five stable command-to-mode mappings, a nine-stage shared lifecycle, concrete short templates, and an unresolved include/shared-fragment question. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/002-research-design-commands/research/research.md:67-178] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/002-research-design-commands/research/research.md:291-300]\n+- The target packet explicitly requires research and recommendations only; command files remain read-only. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/spec.md:50-75]\n+- `resource-map.md` is not present in the target spec folder; skipping the input coverage gate.\n+\n+## 13. Research Boundaries\n+\n+- Maximum iterations: 5\n+- Stop policy: max-iterations\n+- Convergence threshold: 0.05, telemetry only before iteration 5\n+- Allowed write root: this detached `sol-high-fast` lineage only\n+- Per-iteration write set: one prompt, one narrative, one delta, and one append-only state record\n+- Workflow-owned outputs: reducer projections, resource map, and final synthesis within the lineage\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json\n@@ -0,0 +1,14 @@\n+{\n+  \"openQuestions\": [],\n+  \"resolvedQuestions\": [],\n+  \"keyFindings\": [],\n+  \"ruledOutDirections\": [],\n+  \"metrics\": {\n+    \"iterationsCompleted\": 0,\n+    \"openQuestions\": 5,\n+    \"resolvedQuestions\": 0,\n+    \"keyFindings\": 0,\n+    \"convergenc