{"type":"text","timestamp":1784624610480,"sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","part":{"id":"prt_f83ea6131001ysTnddtLL7HBKD","messageID":"msg_f83ea2cac001R9J2v7ZOrlvuRu","sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","type":"text","text":"Iteration 1 passed the mechanical route-proof, narrative, and delta gate. It confirmed the gap is experiential rather than architectural and narrowed the next pass to command-runtime include and rendering capabilities, so I’m reducing that evidence into the lineage state before the second fresh-context dispatch.","time":{"start":1784624603441,"end":1784624610478},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0a75be7de4a45514016a5f35da95e08191ad9a99520da2982e","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784624610800,"sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_3s7xJv3x9TmgFQrGZkfdpzBG","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Research Strategy: Literal Interface Command Prompts\n2: \n3: ## 1. Research Topic\n4: \n5: Rewrite the five `/interface:*` commands as literal, self-contained design prompts while preserving the split where commands own intake and lifecycle, `sk-design` modes own taste and judgment, transports own realization, and `sk-code` owns application-code mutation.\n6: \n7: ## 2. Non-Goals\n8: \n9: - Do not modify commands, presentation assets, skills, workflows, tests, or packet docs.\n10: - Do not write anywhere outside this detached `sol-high-fast` lineage.\n11: - Do not reopen the settled five-command namespace or stable workflow-mode mapping without contradictory evidence.\n12: - Do not duplicate palettes, typography prescriptions, style menus, reference inventories, or mode-owned taste doctrine into commands.\n13: - Do not settle unrelated styles-library structure or database-fate work.\n14: \n15: ## 3. Stop Conditions\n16: \n17: - Complete exactly five iterations because `stopPolicy=max-iterations`.\n18: - Produce concrete, substantially self-contained command-body proposals for all five `/interface:*` commands.\n19: - Resolve the runtime-supported include/shared-fragment mechanism with direct repository evidence.\n20: - Provide a durable authority/anti-duplication rule and a testable implementation plan.\n21: \n22: <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n23: ## 4. Key Questions (Remaining)\n24: \n25: - [ ] What exactly do the shipped command routers, presentation assets, and shared creation contract contain, and which literal-prompt qualities are absent?\n26: - [ ] What complete literal body should each of the five commands contain so an agent receives an evocative, actionable creation brief rather than a thin route?\n27: - [ ] What include, template injection, renderer, or generated-fragment mechanism does the current command runtime actually support?\n28: - [ ] Which content must stay literal in each command, which content may be shared, and which doctrine must remain mode-owned to prevent drift?\n29: - [ ] What exact file/change/test sequence can ship the rewrite without breaking route, intake, proof, handoff, or compatibility contracts?\n30: <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n31: \n32: <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n33: ## 5. Answered Questions\n34: \n35: None yet.\n36: <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n37: \n38: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n39: <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n40: ## 6. What Worked\n41: \n42: None yet.\n43: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n44: \n45: <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n46: ## 7. What Failed\n47: \n48: None yet.\n49: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n50: \n51: <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n52: ## 8. Exhausted Approaches\n53: \n54: - Replacing mode judgment with command-owned taste: already rejected by the authority split established in prior research.\n55: - Treating the current shared contract alone as the requested literal-prompt deliverable: contradicted by the verified gap analysis.\n56: <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n57: \n58: <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n59: ## 9. Ruled-Out Directions\n60: \n61: None yet.\n62: <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n63: \n64: <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n65: ## 10. Carried-Forward Open Questions\n66: \n67: None yet.\n68: <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n69: \n70: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n71: ## 11. Next Focus\n72: \n73: Baseline the five shipped commands, their presentation assets, and `shared/creation-contract.md`; identify the precise delta between working routing architecture and the missing literal-prompt experience.\n74: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n75: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n76: \n77: ## 12. Known Context\n78: \n79: - The parent gap analysis confirms that the 002 research produced literal templates but the build shipped thin routers plus a shared lifecycle contract. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/gap-analysis.md:109-147]\n80: - The 002 synthesis defines five stable command-to-mode mappings, a nine-stage shared lifecycle, concrete short templates, and an unresolved include/shared-fragment question. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/002-research-design-commands/research/research.md:67-178] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/002-research-design-commands/research/research.md:291-300]\n81: - The target packet explicitly requires research and recommendations only; command files remain read-only. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/spec.md:50-75]\n82: - `resource-map.md` is not present in the target spec folder; skipping the input coverage gate.\n83: \n84: ## 13. Research Boundaries\n85: \n86: - Maximum iterations: 5\n87: - Stop policy: max-iterations\n88: - Convergence threshold: 0.05, telemetry only before iteration 5\n89: - Allowed write root: this detached `sol-high-fast` lineage only\n90: - Per-iteration write set: one prompt, one narrative, one delta, and one append-only state record\n91: - Workflow-owned outputs: reducer projections, resource map, and final synthesis within the lineage\n\n(End of file - total 91 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Research Strategy: Literal Interface Command Prompts\n\n## 1. Research Topic\n\nRewrite the five `/interface:*` commands as literal, self-contained design prompts while preserving the split where commands own intake and lifecycle, `sk-design` modes own taste and judgment, transports own realization, and `sk-code` owns application-code mutation.\n\n## 2. Non-Goals\n\n- Do not modify commands, presentation assets, skills, workflows, tests, or packet docs.\n- Do not write anywhere outside this detached `sol-high-fast` lineage.\n- Do not reopen the settled five-command namespace or stable workflow-mode mapping without contradictory evidence.\n- Do not duplicate palettes, typography prescriptions, style menus, reference inventories, or mode-owned taste doctrine into commands.\n- Do not settle unrelated styles-library structure or database-fate work.\n\n## 3. Stop Conditions\n\n- Complete exactly five iterations because `stopPolicy=max-iterations`.\n- Produce concrete, substantially self-contained command-body proposals for all five `/interface:*` commands.\n- Resolve the runtime-supported include/shared-fragment mechanism with direct repository evidence.\n- Provide a durable authority/anti-duplication rule and a testable implementation plan.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"# Deep Research Strategy: Literal Interface Command Prompts\n\n## 1. Research Topic\n\nRewrite the five `/interface:*` commands as literal, self-contained design prompts while preserving the split where commands own intake and lifecycle, `sk-design` modes own taste and judgment, transports own realization, and `sk-code` owns application-code mutation.\n\n## 2. Non-Goals\n\n- Do not modify commands, presentation assets, skills, workflows, tests, or packet docs.\n- Do not write anywhere outside this detached `sol-high-fast` lineage.\n- Do not reopen the settled five-command namespace or stable workflow-mode mapping without contradictory evidence.\n- Do not duplicate palettes, typography prescriptions, style menus, reference inventories, or mode-owned taste doctrine into commands.\n- Do not settle unrelated styles-library structure or database-fate work.\n\n## 3. Stop Conditions\n\n- Complete exactly five iterations because `stopPolicy=max-iterations`.\n- Produce concrete, substantially self-contained command-body proposals for all five `/interface:*` commands.\n- Resolve the runtime-supported include/shared-fragment mechanism with direct repository evidence.\n- Provide a durable authority/anti-duplication rule and a testable implementation plan.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 4. Key Questions (Remaining)\n\n- [ ] What exactly do the shipped command routers, presentation assets, and shared creation contract contain, and which literal-prompt qualities are absent?\n- [ ] What complete literal body should each of the five commands contain so an agent receives an evocative, actionable creation brief rather than a thin route?\n- [ ] What include, template injection, renderer, or generated-fragment mechanism does the current command runtime actually support?\n- [ ] Which content must stay literal in each command, which content may be shared, and which doctrine must remain mode-owned to prevent drift?\n- [ ] What exact file/change/test sequence can ship the rewrite without breaking route, intake, proof, handoff, or compatibility contracts?\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n## 5. Answered Questions\n\nNone yet.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n## 6. What Worked\n\nNone yet.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n## 7. What Failed\n\nNone yet.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n## 8. Exhausted Approaches\n\n- Replacing mode judgment with command-owned taste: already rejected by the authority split established in prior research.\n- Treating the current shared contract alone as the requested literal-prompt deliverable: contradicted by the verified gap analysis.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n## 9. Ruled-Out Directions\n\nNone yet.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n## 10. Carried-Forward Open Questions\n\nNone yet.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. Next Focus\n\nBaseline the five shipped commands, their presentation assets, and `shared/creation-contract.md`; identify the precise delta between working routing architecture and the missing literal-prompt experience.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## 12. Known Context\n\n- The parent gap analysis confirms that the 002 research produced literal templates but the build shipped thin routers plus a shared lifecycle contract. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/gap-analysis.md:109-147]\n- The 002 synthesis defines five stable command-to-mode mappings, a nine-stage shared lifecycle, concrete short templates, and an unresolved include/shared-fragment question. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/002-research-design-commands/research/research.md:67-178] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/002-research-design-commands/research/research.md:291-300]\n- The target packet explicitly requires research and recommendations only; command files remain read-only. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/spec.md:50-75]\n- `resource-map.md` is not present in the target spec folder; skipping the input coverage gate.\n\n## 13. Research Boundaries\n\n- Maximum iterations: 5\n- Stop policy: max-iterations\n- Convergence threshold: 0.05, telemetry only before iteration 5\n- Allowed write root: this detached `sol-high-fast` lineage only\n- Per-iteration write set: one prompt, one narrative, one delta, and one append-only state record\n- Workflow-owned outputs: reducer projections, resource map, and final synthesis within the lineage","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":91,"totalLines":91,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1784624610790,"end":1784624610798}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a75be7de4a45514016a5f35e06da48191bc7c83d56087e3e8"}},"id":"prt_f83ea7cee0016xzzwSTQyb30GR","sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","messageID":"msg_f83ea2cac001R9J2v7ZOrlvuRu"}}
