{"type":"text","timestamp":1784624953241,"sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","part":{"id":"prt_f83efa284001ygT1Z2nAhniP4G","messageID":"msg_f83ef7bdb001CqUvY2lYpm6DjP","sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","type":"text","text":"Iteration 2 passed and resolved the central runtime fork: use a literal mode-specific brief in each command plus one `@./path` expansion for the shared normative contract; generation is only needed if source-byte self-containment is mandatory. The third pass now moves from mechanism to deliverable and will draft all five concrete command bodies with a literal/shared/mode-owned content matrix.","time":{"start":1784624947844,"end":1784624953235},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0dee18f3a7149f21016a5f3733bc6c81919b143b5724db2f8b","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784624953400,"sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_KIYhJ1Y81jOBVJ1qOBE3vweZ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-dashboard.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-dashboard.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Research Dashboard\n2: \n3: ## Iteration Table\n4: \n5: | run | focus | newInfoRatio | findings | status |\n6: |---:|---|---:|---:|---|\n7: | 1 | Shipped command anatomy and literal-prompt gap | 0.90 | 5 | complete |\n8: \n9: ## Question Status\n10: \n11: - Answered: 1 / 5\n12: - Remaining: include mechanics; five literal bodies; authority split; implementation and verification sequence.\n13: \n14: ## Convergence Trend\n15: \n16: - Ratios: 0.90\n17: - Stop policy: `max-iterations`; convergence is telemetry only until iteration 5.\n18: - Stuck count: 0\n19: \n20: ## Dead Ends\n21: \n22: - Broad repository searches over generic include/template terms are too noisy.\n23: - Wholesale router replacement and command-owned taste doctrine are eliminated.\n24: \n25: ## Next Focus\n26: \n27: Verify the command runtime's actual include, renderer, and template-injection capabilities.\n28: \n29: ## Active Risks\n30: \n31: - A runtime mechanism must be proven rather than invented.\n32: - Literal richness must not fork mode-owned taste doctrine.\n\n(End of file - total 32 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Research Dashboard\n\n## Iteration Table\n\n| run | focus | newInfoRatio | findings | status |\n|---:|---|---:|---:|---|\n| 1 | Shipped command anatomy and literal-prompt gap | 0.90 | 5 | complete |\n\n## Question Status\n\n- Answered: 1 / 5\n- Remaining: include mechanics; five literal bodies; authority split; implementation and verification sequence.\n\n## Convergence Trend\n\n- Ratios: 0.90\n- Stop policy: `max-iterations`; convergence is telemetry only until iteration 5.\n- Stuck count: 0\n\n## Dead Ends","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-dashboard.md","text":"# Deep Research Dashboard\n\n## Iteration Table\n\n| run | focus | newInfoRatio | findings | status |\n|---:|---|---:|---:|---|\n| 1 | Shipped command anatomy and literal-prompt gap | 0.90 | 5 | complete |\n\n## Question Status\n\n- Answered: 1 / 5\n- Remaining: include mechanics; five literal bodies; authority split; implementation and verification sequence.\n\n## Convergence Trend\n\n- Ratios: 0.90\n- Stop policy: `max-iterations`; convergence is telemetry only until iteration 5.\n- Stuck count: 0\n\n## Dead Ends\n\n- Broad repository searches over generic include/template terms are too noisy.\n- Wholesale router replacement and command-owned taste doctrine are eliminated.\n\n## Next Focus\n\nVerify the command runtime's actual include, renderer, and template-injection capabilities.\n\n## Active Risks\n\n- A runtime mechanism must be proven rather than invented.\n- Literal richness must not fork mode-owned taste doctrine.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":32,"totalLines":32,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-dashboard.md","time":{"start":1784624953373,"end":1784624953392}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0dee18f3a7149f21016a5f373932d0819188936405c0a92ecb"}},"id":"prt_f83efb7970015pMn27wODMPJCg","sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","messageID":"msg_f83ef7bdb001CqUvY2lYpm6DjP"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784624953400,"sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_c3PgYIYMPfmzAJu5CzwQSHMA","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"openQuestions\": [\n3:     \"What complete literal body should each of the five commands contain?\",\n4:     \"What include/shared-fragment mechanism does the runtime support?\",\n5:     \"Which content stays literal, shared, or mode-owned?\",\n6:     \"What file/change/test sequence can ship the rewrite safely?\"\n7:   ],\n8:   \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n9:     \"What exactly do the shipped command routers, presentation assets, and shared creation contract contain, and which literal-prompt qualities are absent?\"\n10:   ],\n11:   \"keyFindings\": [\n12:     {\"id\":\"I001-F1\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"The five shipped bodies are substantial mode routers, not self-contained creation prompts.\"},\n13:     {\"id\":\"I001-F2\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"Command-specific intake, sibling discrimination, stable mappings, and typed products are working architecture worth preserving.\"},\n14:     {\"id\":\"I001-F3\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"Presentation assets implement progressive intake and visible lifecycle blocks but fragment prompt wording away from command bodies.\"},\n15:     {\"id\":\"I001-F4\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"The skill-local creation contract centralizes choreography and authority while intentionally excluding design taste.\"},\n16:     {\"id\":\"I001-F5\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"The remaining gap is an evocative, actionable, command-visible creation brief, not missing routing architecture.\"}\n17:   ],\n18:   \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n19:     \"Replace the working routers wholesale\",\n20:     \"Copy mode-owned taste doctrine into commands\",\n21:     \"Treat presentation assets or the shared contract alone as the literal-prompt deliverable\"\n22:   ],\n23:   \"metrics\": {\n24:     \"iterationsCompleted\": 1,\n25:     \"openQuestions\": 4,\n26:     \"resolvedQuestions\": 1,\n27:     \"keyFindings\": 5,\n28:     \"convergenceScore\": 0.1,\n29:     \"coverageBySources\": {\"commands\":5,\"presentations\":5,\"shared-contract\":1,\"prior-research\":2}\n30:   },\n31:   \"status\": \"iterating\",\n32:   \"sessionId\": \"fanout-sol-high-fast-1784623934648-kt3qkt\",\n33:   \"generation\": 1,\n34:   \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-07-21T08:59:21Z\"\n35: }\n\n(End of file - total 35 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"openQuestions\": [\n    \"What complete literal body should each of the five commands contain?\",\n    \"What include/shared-fragment mechanism does the runtime support?\",\n    \"Which content stays literal, shared, or mode-owned?\",\n    \"What file/change/test sequence can ship the rewrite safely?\"\n  ],\n  \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n    \"What exactly do the shipped command routers, presentation assets, and shared creation contract contain, and which literal-prompt qualities are absent?\"\n  ],\n  \"keyFindings\": [\n    {\"id\":\"I001-F1\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"The five shipped bodies are substantial mode routers, not self-contained creation prompts.\"},\n    {\"id\":\"I001-F2\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"Command-specific intake, sibling discrimination, stable mappings, and typed products are working architecture worth preserving.\"},\n    {\"id\":\"I001-F3\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"Presentation assets implement progressive intake and visible lifecycle blocks but fragment prompt wording away from command bodies.\"},\n    {\"id\":\"I001-F4\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"The skill-local creation contract centralizes choreography and authority while intentionally excluding design taste.\"},\n    {\"id\":\"I001-F5\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"The remaining gap is an evocative, actionable, command-visible creation brief, not missing routing architecture.\"}\n  ],\n  \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n    \"Replace the working routers wholesale\",\n    \"Copy mode-owned taste doctrine into commands\",","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json","text":"{\n  \"openQuestions\": [\n    \"What complete literal body should each of the five commands contain?\",\n    \"What include/shared-fragment mechanism does the runtime support?\",\n    \"Which content stays literal, shared, or mode-owned?\",\n    \"What file/change/test sequence can ship the rewrite safely?\"\n  ],\n  \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n    \"What exactly do the shipped command routers, presentation assets, and shared creation contract contain, and which literal-prompt qualities are absent?\"\n  ],\n  \"keyFindings\": [\n    {\"id\":\"I001-F1\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"The five shipped bodies are substantial mode routers, not self-contained creation prompts.\"},\n    {\"id\":\"I001-F2\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"Command-specific intake, sibling discrimination, stable mappings, and typed products are working architecture worth preserving.\"},\n    {\"id\":\"I001-F3\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"Presentation assets implement progressive intake and visible lifecycle blocks but fragment prompt wording away from command bodies.\"},\n    {\"id\":\"I001-F4\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"The skill-local creation contract centralizes choreography and authority while intentionally excluding design taste.\"},\n    {\"id\":\"I001-F5\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"The remaining gap is an evocative, actionable, command-visible creation brief, not missing routing architecture.\"}\n  ],\n  \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n    \"Replace the working routers wholesale\",\n    \"Copy mode-owned taste doctrine into commands\",\n    \"Treat presentation assets or the shared contract alone as the literal-prompt deliverable\"\n  ],\n  \"metrics\": {\n    \"iterationsCompleted\": 1,\n    \"openQuestions\": 4,\n    \"resolvedQuestions\": 1,\n    \"keyFindings\": 5,\n    \"convergenceScore\": 0.1,\n    \"coverageBySources\": {\"commands\":5,\"presentations\":5,\"shared-contract\":1,\"prior-research\":2}\n  },\n  \"status\": \"iterating\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"fanout-sol-high-fast-1784623934648-kt3qkt\",\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-07-21T08:59:21Z\"\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":35,"totalLines":35,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json","time":{"start":1784624953376,"end":1784624953394}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0dee18f3a7149f21016a5f373932ec8191ae3e126ef26fdf21"}},"id":"prt_f83efb81e001krlyXqbjShecTo","sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","messageID":"msg_f83ef7bdb001CqUvY2lYpm6DjP"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784624953401,"sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_gzyL3dUJ0uC2uWngl3yytadS","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md","offset":20,"limit":60},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n20: - Provide a durable authority/anti-duplication rule and a testable implementation plan.\n21: \n22: <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n23: ## 4. Key Questions (Remaining)\n24: \n25: - [x] What exactly do the shipped command routers, presentation assets, and shared creation contract contain, and which literal-prompt qualities are absent?\n26: - [ ] What complete literal body should each of the five commands contain so an agent receives an evocative, actionable creation brief rather than a thin route?\n27: - [ ] What include, template injection, renderer, or generated-fragment mechanism does the current command runtime actually support?\n28: - [ ] Which content must stay literal in each command, which content may be shared, and which doctrine must remain mode-owned to prevent drift?\n29: - [ ] What exact file/change/test sequence can ship the rewrite without breaking route, intake, proof, handoff, or compatibility contracts?\n30: <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n31: \n32: <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n33: ## 5. Answered Questions\n34: \n35: - The shipped bodies preserve valuable command-specific intake, sibling discrimination, route proof, stable mode mappings, typed outputs, and mutation boundaries, but outsource the creation experience across presentations and the shared contract. The missing layer is a command-visible, evocative, actionable brief with experiential stakes, anti-generic constraints, real context/content, and a mode-specific quality bar. (iteration 1)\n36: <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n37: \n38: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n39: <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n40: ## 6. What Worked\n41: \n42: - Exact cross-command anchor comparison separated the shared routing skeleton from meaningful domain-specific intake and exposed the missing prompt layer without discarding working architecture. (iteration 1)\n43: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n44: \n45: <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n46: ## 7. What Failed\n47: \n48: - Broad repository search for generic include/template terms was noisy; exact command-runtime and renderer symbols are required for the next pass. (iteration 1)\n49: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n50: \n51: <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n52: ## 8. Exhausted Approaches\n53: \n54: - Replacing mode judgment with command-owned taste: already rejected by the authority split established in prior research.\n55: - Treating the current shared contract alone as the requested literal-prompt deliverable: contradicted by the verified gap analysis.\n56: - Wholesale router replacement: exhausted because current prerequisites, route mappings, proof outputs, and handoff boundaries are useful and should be retained. (iteration 1)\n57: - Presentation-only enrichment: exhausted because it leaves the literal command body dependent on external fragments and preserves the experiential gap. (iteration 1)\n58: <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n59: \n60: <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n61: ## 9. Ruled-Out Directions\n62: \n63: - Command-owned palettes, typography recipes, style menus, or fixed visual doctrine: ruled out because modes own taste and design judgment. (iteration 1)\n64: <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n65: \n66: <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n67: ## 10. Carried-Forward Open Questions\n68: \n69: None yet.\n70: <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n71: \n72: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n73: ## 11. Next Focus\n74: \n75: Determine the runtime-supported include/shared-fragment mechanism with direct command-loader, renderer, `$ARGUMENTS`, and template-injection evidence; decide whether source commands can remain literally rich while sharing lifecycle text at execution time.\n76: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n77: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n78: \n79: ## 12. Known Context\n\n(Showing lines 20-79 of 93. Use offset=80 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"- Provide a durable authority/anti-duplication rule and a testable implementation plan.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 4. Key Questions (Remaining)\n\n- [x] What exactly do the shipped command routers, presentation assets, and shared creation contract contain, and which literal-prompt qualities are absent?\n- [ ] What complete literal body should each of the five commands contain so an agent receives an evocative, actionable creation brief rather than a thin route?\n- [ ] What include, template injection, renderer, or generated-fragment mechanism does the current command runtime actually support?\n- [ ] Which content must stay literal in each command, which content may be shared, and which doctrine must remain mode-owned to prevent drift?\n- [ ] What exact file/change/test sequence can ship the rewrite without breaking route, intake, proof, handoff, or compatibility contracts?\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n## 5. Answered Questions\n\n- The shipped bodies preserve valuable command-specific intake, sibling discrimination, route proof, stable mode mappings, typed outputs, and mutation boundaries, but outsource the creation experience across presentations and the shared contract. The missing layer is a command-visible, evocative, actionable brief with experiential stakes, anti-generic constraints, real context/content, and a mode-specific quality bar. (iteration 1)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"- Provide a durable authority/anti-duplication rule and a testable implementation plan.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 4. Key Questions (Remaining)\n\n- [x] What exactly do the shipped command routers, presentation assets, and shared creation contract contain, and which literal-prompt qualities are absent?\n- [ ] What complete literal body should each of the five commands contain so an agent receives an evocative, actionable creation brief rather than a thin route?\n- [ ] What include, template injection, renderer, or generated-fragment mechanism does the current command runtime actually support?\n- [ ] Which content must stay literal in each command, which content may be shared, and which doctrine must remain mode-owned to prevent drift?\n- [ ] What exact file/change/test sequence can ship the rewrite without breaking route, intake, proof, handoff, or compatibility contracts?\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n## 5. Answered Questions\n\n- The shipped bodies preserve valuable command-specific intake, sibling discrimination, route proof, stable mode mappings, typed outputs, and mutation boundaries, but outsource the creation experience across presentations and the shared contract. The missing layer is a command-visible, evocative, actionable brief with experiential stakes, anti-generic constraints, real context/content, and a mode-specific quality bar. (iteration 1)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n## 6. What Worked\n\n- Exact cross-command anchor comparison separated the shared routing skeleton from meaningful domain-specific intake and exposed the missing prompt layer without discarding working architecture. (iteration 1)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n## 7. What Failed\n\n- Broad repository search for generic include/template terms was noisy; exact command-runtime and renderer symbols are required for the next pass. (iteration 1)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n## 8. Exhausted Approaches\n\n- Replacing mode judgment with command-owned taste: already rejected by the authority split established in prior research.\n- Treating the current shared contract alone as the requested literal-prompt deliverable: contradicted by the verified gap analysis.\n- Wholesale router replacement: exhausted because current prerequisites, route mappings, proof outputs, and handoff boundaries are useful and should be retained. (iteration 1)\n- Presentation-only enrichment: exhausted because it leaves the literal command body dependent on external fragments and preserves the experiential gap. (iteration 1)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n## 9. Ruled-Out Directions\n\n- Command-owned palettes, typography recipes, style menus, or fixed visual doctrine: ruled out because modes own taste and design judgment. (iteration 1)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n## 10. Carried-Forward Open Questions\n\nNone yet.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. Next Focus\n\nDetermine the runtime-supported include/shared-fragment mechanism with direct command-loader, renderer, `$ARGUMENTS`, and template-injection evidence; decide whether source commands can remain literally rich while sharing lifecycle text at execution time.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## 12. Known Context","lineStart":20,"lineEnd":79,"totalLines":93,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1784624953380,"end":1784624953396}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0dee18f3a7149f21016a5f373932f881918ba40fa9e273c749"}},"id":"prt_f83efb821001Sjk17Tq6IRUXfy","sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","messageID":"msg_f83ef7bdb001CqUvY2lYpm6DjP"}}
