| 0.90 | 5 | complete |\n+| 2 | Runtime include/shared-fragment mechanism | 1.00 | 5 | complete |\n \n ## Question Status\n \n-- Answered: 1 / 5\n-- Remaining: include mechanics; five literal bodies; authority split; implementation and verification sequence.\n+- Answered: 2 / 5\n+- Remaining: five literal bodies; authority split; implementation and verification sequence.\n \n ## Convergence Trend\n \n-- Ratios: 0.90\n+- Ratios: 0.90 -> 1.00\n - Stop policy: `max-iterations`; convergence is telemetry only until iteration 5.\n - Stuck count: 0\n \n ## Dead Ends\n \n - Broad repository searches over generic include/template terms are too noisy.\n - Wholesale router replacement and command-owned taste doctrine are eliminated.\n+- Markdown/read references are not loader includes; shell rendering and full hand duplication are unnecessary.\n \n ## Next Focus\n \n-Verify the command runtime's actual include, renderer, and template-injection capabilities.\n+Draft all five literal command bodies using the literal/shared/mode-owned content matrix.\n \n ## Active Risks\n \n-- A runtime mechanism must be proven rather than invented.\n+- `@./path` runtime expansion still needs a representative live command-dispatch fixture during implementation.\n - Literal richness must not fork mode-owned taste doctrine.\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md","relativePath":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interf