c to source-faithful extraction\",\"Replacing useful route, suffix, sibling, and typed-status architecture\"],\"focusTrack\":\"literal-command-bodies\",\"edgeCase\":\"partial-success\",\"toolsUsed\":[\"Read\",\"Grep\",\"Glob\",\"apply_patch\"],\"sourcesQueried\":[\".opencode/commands/interface/*.md\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/SKILL.md\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/SKILL.md\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/SKILL.md\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/SKILL.md\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/002-research-design-commands/research/research.md:60-319\",\"deep-research-config.json\",\"deep-research-state.jsonl\",\"deep-research-strategy.md\",\"findings-registry.json\"],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-21T09:15:00Z\",\"durationMs\":480000,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-high-fast-1784623934648-kt3qkt\",\"generation\":1,\"executor\":{\"kind\":\"cli-opencode\",\"model\":\"openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast\"},\"graphEvents\":[]}\n+{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"min_iterations_guard_pass\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":4,\"iterationCount\":3,\"minIterations\":3,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-21T09:15:01Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-high-fast-1784623934648-kt3qkt\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"dashboard_generated\",\"iteration\":3,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-21T09:15:01Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-high-fast-1784623934648-kt3qkt\",\"generation\":1}\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/orchestration-status.log\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/orchestration-status.log\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/orchestration-status.log\n@@ -1,3 +1,4 @@\n {\"event\":\"started\",\"label\":\"single\",\"at\":\"2026-07-21T08:55:18Z\",\"duration_ms\":0,\"loop_type\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-high-fast-1784623934648-kt3qkt\",\"generation\":1,\"gauges\":{\"iterations\":0,\"elapsed_ms\":0,\"score\":0}}\n {\"event\":\"progress\",\"label\":\"single\",\"at\":\"2026-07-21T08:59:21Z\",\"duration_ms\":243000,\"loop_type\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-high-fast-1784623934648-kt3qkt\",\"generation\":1,\"run\":1,\"status\":\"complete\",\"gauges\":{\"iterations\":1,\"elapsed_ms\":243000,\"score\":0.9}}\n {\"event\":\"progress\",\"label\":\"single\",\"at\":\"2026-07-21T09:06:37Z\",\"duration_ms\":679000,\"loop_type\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-high-fast-1784623934648-kt3qkt\",\"generation\":1,\"run\":2,\"status\":\"complete\",\"gauges\":{\"iterations\":2,\"elapsed_ms\":679000,\"score\":1.0}}\n+{\"event\":\"progress\",\"label\":\"single\",\"at\":\"2026-07-21T09:15:01Z\",\"duration_ms\":1183000,\"loop_type\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-high-fast-1784623934648-kt3qkt\",\"generation\":1,\"run\":3,\"status\":\"complete\",\"gauges\":{\"iterations\":3,\"elapsed_ms\":1183000,\"score\":0.9}}\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-dashboard.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-dashboard.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-dashboard.md\n@@ -5,30 +5,34 @@\n | run | focus | newInfoRatio | findings | status |\n |---:|---|---:|---:|---|\n | 1 | Shipped command anatomy and literal-prompt gap | 0.90 | 5 | complete |\n | 2 | Runtime include/shared-fragment mechanism | 1.00 | 5 | complete |\n+| 3 | Five literal body cores and content ownership | 0.90 | 5 | complete |\n \n ## Question Status\n \n-- Answered: 2 / 5\n-- Remaining: five literal bodies; authority split; implementation and verification sequence.\n+- Answered: 4 / 5\n+- Remaining: implementation and verification sequence.\n \n ## Convergence Trend\n \n-- Ratios: 0.90 -> 1.00\n+- Ratios: 0.90 -> 1.00 -> 0.90\n+- Minimum-iteration guard: passed after iteration 3.\n - Stop policy: `max-iterations`; convergence is telemetry only until iteration 5.\n - Stuck count: 0\n \n ## Dead Ends\n \n - Broad repository searches over generic include/template terms are too noisy.\n - Wholesale router replacement and command-owned taste doctrine are eliminated.\n - Markdown/read references are not loader includes; shell rendering and full hand duplication are unnecessary.\n+- Design-reference must not inherit originality rhetoric; reference inventories and transport mechanics stay mode-owned.\n \n ## Next Focus\n \n-Draft all five literal command bodies using the literal/shared/mode-owned content matrix.\n+Adversarially review phrase-level authority, proof, mutation, routing, and typed-status behavior.\n \n ## Active Risks\n \n - `@./path` runtime expansion still needs a representative live command-dispatch fixture during implementation.\n - Literal richness must not fork mode-owned taste doctrine.\n+- The five drafts need exact-router comparison before their implementation sequence can be trusted.\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md","relativePath":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -22,34 +22,37 @@\n <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n ## 4. Key Questions (Remaining)\n \n - [x] What exactly do the shipped command routers, presentation assets, and shared creation contract contain, and which literal-prompt qualities are absent?\n-- [ ] What complete literal body should each of the five commands contain so an agent receives an evocative, actionable creation brief rather than a thin route?\n+- [x] What complete literal body should each of the five commands contain so an agent receives an evocative, actionable creation brief rather than a thin route?\n - [x] What include, template injection, renderer, or generated-fragment mechanism does the current command runtime actually support?\n-- [ ] Which content must stay literal in each command, which content may be shared, and which doctrine must remain mode-owned to prevent drift?\n+- [x] Which content must stay literal in each command, which content may be shared, and which doctrine must remain mode-owned to prevent drift?\n - [ ] What exact file/change/test sequence can ship the rewrite without breaking route, intake, proof, handoff, or compatibility contracts?\n <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n ## 5. Answered Questions\n \n - The shipped bodies preserve valuable command-specific intake, sibling discrimination, route proof, stable mode mappings, typed outputs, and mutation boundaries, but outsource the creation experience across presentations and the shared contract. The missing layer is a command-visible, evocative, actionable brief with experiential stakes, anti-generic constraints, real context/content, and a mode-specific quality bar. (iteration 1)\n - OpenCode command templates support direct `@./path` file-content expansion. The recommended mechanism is literal, mode-specific creation prose in each command plus one `@./.opencode/skills/sk-design/shared/creation-contract.md` expansion for shared normative lifecycle and authority content. This yields runtime-expanded self-containment; checked-in source-byte duplication would require generation and is unnecessary. (iteration 2)\n+- Five concrete body cores now define the command-visible mission, intake, grounding, stable route, ordered work, targeted revision, proof ceiling, typed output, and handoff for design, foundations, motion, audit, and design-reference. Public orchestration stays literal, universal schemas arrive through the shared `@` contract, and values/judgment remain mode-owned. (iteration 3)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n \n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n ## 6. What Worked\n \n - Exact cross-command anchor comparison separated the shared routing skeleton from meaningful domain-specific intake and exposed the missing prompt layer without discarding working architecture. (iteration 1)\n - Exact command-authoring and renderer-symbol tracing distinguished native `@` expansion, `$ARGUMENTS` substitution, shell rendering, and generated-router patterns. (iteration 2)\n+- A common mission-to-handoff grammar plus one decisive mode-specific quality rule produced five concrete prompts without flattening their distinct jobs. (iteration 3)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n ## 7. What Failed\n \n - Broad repository search for generic include/template terms was noisy; exact command-runtime and renderer symbols are required for the next pass. (iteration 1)\n - Historical compiled-stub descriptions were insufficient; direct live-command reads were required to establish the current runtime contract. (iteration 2)\n+- A broad all-command read truncated before all five routers; exact current anchors plus the prior synthesis covered the missing comparisons, but iteration 4 must narrowly verify authority-bearing phrases against each exact router. (iteration 3)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n ## 8. Exhausted Approaches\n@@ -59,15 +62,17 @@\n - Wholesale router replacement: exhausted because current prerequisites, route mappings, proof outputs, and handoff boundaries are useful and should be retained. (iteration 1)\n - Presentation-only enrichment: exhausted because it leaves the literal command body dependent on external fragments and preserves the experiential gap. (iteration 1)\n - Shell-output compilation for this rewrite: exhausted as disproportionate registry, drift, security, and manifest machinery when native `@` expansion exists. (iteration 2)\n - Hand-duplicating the full lifecycle in five commands: exhausted because it creates normative drift without improving runtime self-containment. (iteration 2)\n+- Applying anti-generic creative rhetoric to `design-reference`: exhausted because extraction quality is source fidelity and provenance, not originality. (iteration 3)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n ## 9. Ruled-Out Directions\n \n - Command-owned palettes, typography recipes, style menus, or fixed visual doctrine: ruled out because modes own taste and design judgment. (iteration 1)\n - Markdown links/read imperatives and presentation/YAML assets as loader includes: ruled out because they do not provide native file-content expansion. (iteration 2)\n+- Copying reference inventories, transport mechanics, exact palettes/fonts, token recipes, or validation procedures into command bodies: ruled out as mode/transport-owned doctrine. (iteration 3)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n ## 10. Carried-Forward Open Questions\n@@ -77,9 +82,9 @@\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n ## 11. Next Focus\n \n-Draft complete literal creation briefs for all five commands. Label every paragraph as command-owned literal, shared normative contract, or mode-owned judgment; preserve existing route/intake/proof architecture while making the command-visible experience concrete and evocative.\n+Adversarially review the five proposed bodies against each exact current router, mode authority, mutation boundary, evidence ceiling, suffix/cannot-run/sibling routing, and typed statuses. Produce phrase-level keep/move/delete corrections and identify the implementation/test sequence constraints.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n ## 12. Known Context\n","additions":8,"deletions":3},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json","relativePath":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json\n@@ -1,13 +1,13 @@\n {\n   \"openQuestions\": [\n-    \"What complete literal body should each of the five commands contain?\",\n-    \"Which content stays literal, shared, or mode-owned?\",\n     \"What file/change/test sequence can ship the rewrite safely?\"\n   ],\n   \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n     \"What exactly do the shipped command routers, presentation assets, and shared creation contract contain, and which literal-prompt qualities are absent?\",\n-    \"What include/shared-fragment mechanism does the runtime support?\"\n+    \"What include/shared-fragment mechanism does the runtime support?\",\n+    \"What complete literal body should each of the five commands contain?\",\n+    \"Which content stays literal, shared, or mode-owned?\"\n   ],\n   \"keyFindings\": [\n     {\"id\":\"I001-F1\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"The five shipped bodies are substantial mode routers, not self-contained creation prompts.\"},\n     {\"id\":\"I001-F2\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"Command-specific intake, sibling discrimination, stable mappings, and typed products are working architecture worth preserving.\"},\n@@ -17,27 +17,34 @@\n     {\"id\":\"I002-F1\",\"iteration\":2,\"summary\":\"@./path is the smallest direct runtime file-content expansion mechanism; it makes the rendered prompt, not the checked-in command bytes, self-contained.\"},\n     {\"id\":\"I002-F2\",\"iteration\":2,\"summary\":\"$ARGUMENTS preserves invocation intake but is not a shared-fragment mechanism.\"},\n     {\"id\":\"I002-F3\",\"iteration\":2,\"summary\":\"Shell-output rendering is feasible but introduces disproportionate registry, drift, rollout, security, and manifest machinery.\"},\n     {\"id\":\"I002-F4\",\"iteration\":2,\"summary\":\"Generation is required only if every checked-in command must contain all canonical shared bytes.\"},\n-    {\"id\":\"I002-F5\",\"iteration\":2,\"summary\":\"Use a literal mode-specific creation brief plus one @ reference to the shared normative creation contract.\"}\n+    {\"id\":\"I002-F5\",\"iteration\":2,\"summary\":\"Use a literal mode-specific creation brief plus one @ reference to the shared normative creation contract.\"},\n+    {\"id\":\"I003-F1\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"Literal command bodies should own the mode-specific mission, progressive intake, ordered work, critique rule, evidence ceiling, and typed product while delegating taste.\"},\n+    {\"id\":\"I003-F2\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"One canonical @ expansion carries shared lifecycle and schemas without five-copy drift.\"},\n+    {\"id\":\"I003-F3\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"A three-way placement rule separates literal public orchestration, shared normative schemas, and mode-owned judgment.\"},\n+    {\"id\":\"I003-F4\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"All five bodies can share one structural grammar while retaining distinct decisive quality rules.\"},\n+    {\"id\":\"I003-F5\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"Design-reference substitutes source fidelity and provenance for anti-generic creative originality.\"}\n   ],\n   \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n     \"Replace the working routers wholesale\",\n     \"Copy mode-owned taste doctrine into commands\",\n     \"Treat presentation assets or the shared contract alone as the literal-prompt deliverable\",\n     \"Use Markdown links or read imperatives as loader includes\",\n     \"Use a shell-command renderer as the smallest mechanism\",\n-    \"Hand-duplicate the complete shared lifecycle\"\n+    \"Hand-duplicate the complete shared lifecycle\",\n+    \"Copy mode-owned reference inventories or transport mechanics into commands\",\n+    \"Apply anti-generic creation rhetoric to source-faithful extraction\"\n   ],\n   \"metrics\": {\n-    \"iterationsCompleted\": 2,\n-    \"openQuestions\": 3,\n-    \"resolvedQuestions\": 2,\n-    \"keyFindings\": 10,\n-    \"convergenceScore\": 0.2,\n-    \"coverageBySources\": {\"commands\":7,\"presentations\":5,\"shared-contract\":1,\"prior-research\":2,\"runtime-docs\":3,\"runtime-code\":2,\"runtime-tests\":1,\"external-docs\":1}\n+    \"iterationsCompleted\": 3,\n+    \"openQuestions\": 1,\n+    \"resolvedQuestions\": 4,\n+    \"keyFindings\": 15,\n+    \"convergenceScore\": 0.8,\n+    \"coverageBySources\": {\"commands\":7,\"presentations\":5,\"shared-contract\":1,\"prior-research\":2,\"runtime-docs\":3,\"runtime-code\":2,\"runtime-tests\":1,\"external-docs\":1,\"mode-contracts\":5}\n   },\n   \"status\": \"iterating\",\n   \"sessionId\": \"fanout-sol-high-fast-1784623934648-kt3qkt\",\n   