ngsCount\": 5,\n  \"newInfoRatio\": 1.0,\n  \"noveltyJustification\": \"4 of 5 findings were fully new and 1 partially new (0.90), plus a 0.10 simplicity bonus for reducing the corrections to one testable placement model.\",\n  \"keyQuestions\": [\n    \"What exact file/change/test sequence can ship the rewrite without breaking route, intake, proof, handoff, or compatibility contracts?\"\n  ],\n  \"answeredQuestions\": [\n    \"What exact file/change/test sequence can ship the rewrite without breaking route, intake, proof, handoff, or compatibility contracts?\"\n  ],\n  \"ruledOut\": [\n    \"Dropping STATUS=ASK from the literal bodies\",\n    \"Keeping presentation assets as a competing normative prompt authority\",\n    \"Allowing audit to apply fixes\",\n    \"Allowing brief-provided values into design-reference token tables\",\n    \"Claiming exact @./ rooting without a live fixture\"\n  ],\n  \"focusTrack\": \"adversarial-conformance\",\n  \"edgeCase\": \"contradictory-evidence\",\n  \"toolsUsed\": [\n    \"Read\",\n    \"Glob\",\n    \"Grep\",\n    \"WebFetch\",\n    \"Bash\",\n    \"apply_patch\"\n  ],\n  \"sourcesQueried\": [\n    \"iterations/iteration-003.md\",\n    \".opencode/commands/interface/*.md\",\n    \".opencode/commands/interface/assets/interface-*-presentation.txt\",\n    \".opencode/commands/interface/assets/interface-*-auto.yaml\",\n    \".opencode/commands/interface/assets/interface-*-confirm.yaml\",\n    \".opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md\",\n    \".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/SKILL.md\",\n    \".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/SKILL.md\",\n    \".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/SKILL.md\",\n    \".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/SKILL.md\",\n    \".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/SKILL.md\",\n    \".opencode/skills/sk-design/shared/creation-contract.md\",\n    \".opencode/skills/sk-design/mode-registry.json\",\n    \".opencode/skills/sk-design/command-metadata.json\",\n    \".opencode/skills/sk-design/shared/scripts/interface-command-contract.test.mjs\",\n    \".opencode/skills/sk-design/shared/scripts/design-command-surface-check.test.mjs\",\n    \"https://opencode.ai/docs/commands/\",\n    \"node --test command output\"\n  ],\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-07-21T09:22:01Z\",\n  \"durationMs\": 420000,\n  \"sessionId\": \"fanout-sol-high-fast-1784623934648-kt3qkt\",\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"executor\": {\n    \"kind\": \"cli-opencode\",\n    \"model\": \"openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast\"\n  },\n  \"graphEvents\": []\n}\n","exit":0,"truncated":false},"title":"jq -s '.[-1]' \"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-state.jsonl\"","time":{"start":1784626045140,"end":1784626045143}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_029cba594a2c4814016a5f3b7cffa88191bb286dee6e484b7e"}},"id":"prt_f84006083001jeUR6ZF7FdSewL","sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","messageID":"msg_f840012fd0016529edbzet2gZk"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784626045207,"sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Rfk1My8dmuM68ZUuYpWsMHRK","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md","offset":20,"limit":60},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n20: - Provide a durable authority/anti-duplication rule and a testable implementation plan.\n21: \n22: <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n23: ## 4. Key Questions (Remaining)\n24: \n25: - [x] What exactly do the shipped command routers, presentation assets, and shared creation contract contain, and which literal-prompt qualities are absent?\n26: - [x] What complete literal body should each of the five commands contain so an agent receives an evocative, actionable creation brief rather than a thin route?\n27: - [x] What include, template injection, renderer, or generated-fragment mechanism does the current command runtime actually support?\n28: - [x] Which content must stay literal in each command, which content may be shared, and which doctrine must remain mode-owned to prevent drift?\n29: - [ ] What exact file/change/test sequence can ship the rewrite without breaking route, intake, proof, handoff, or compatibility contracts?\n30: <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n31: \n32: <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n33: ## 5. Answered Questions\n34: \n35: - The shipped bodies preserve valuable command-specific intake, sibling discrimination, route proof, stable mode mappings, typed outputs, and mutation boundaries, but outsource the creation experience across presentations and the shared contract. The missing layer is a command-visible, evocative, actionable brief with experiential stakes, anti-generic constraints, real context/content, and a mode-specific quality bar. (iteration 1)\n36: - OpenCode command templates support direct `@./path` file-content expansion. The recommended mechanism is literal, mode-specific creation prose in each command plus one `@./.opencode/skills/sk-design/shared/creation-contract.md` expansion for shared normative lifecycle and authority content. This yields runtime-expanded self-containment; checked-in source-byte duplication would require generation and is unnecessary. (iteration 2)\n37: - Five concrete body cores now define the command-visible mission, intake, grounding, stable route, ordered work, targeted revision, proof ceiling, typed output, and handoff for design, foundations, motion, audit, and design-reference. Public orchestration stays literal, universal schemas arrive through the shared `@` contract, and values/judgment remain mode-owned. (iteration 3)\n38: <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n39: \n40: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n41: <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n42: ## 6. What Worked\n43: \n44: - Exact cross-command anchor comparison separated the shared routing skeleton from meaningful domain-specific intake and exposed the missing prompt layer without discarding working architecture. (iteration 1)\n45: - Exact command-authoring and renderer-symbol tracing distinguished native `@` expansion, `$ARGUMENTS` substitution, shell rendering, and generated-router patterns. (iteration 2)\n46: - A common mission-to-handoff grammar plus one decisive mode-specific quality rule produced five concrete prompts without flattening their distinct jobs. (iteration 3)\n47: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n48: \n49: <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n50: ## 7. What Failed\n51: \n52: - Broad repository search for generic include/template terms was noisy; exact command-runtime and renderer symbols are required for the next pass. (iteration 1)\n53: - Historical compiled-stub descriptions were insufficient; direct live-command reads were required to establish the current runtime contract. (iteration 2)\n54: - A broad all-command read truncated before all five routers; exact current anchors plus the prior synthesis covered the missing comparisons, but iteration 4 must narrowly verify authority-bearing phrases against each exact router. (iteration 3)\n55: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n56: \n57: <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n58: ## 8. Exhausted Approaches\n59: \n60: - Replacing mode judgment with command-owned taste: already rejected by the authority split established in prior research.\n61: - Treating the current shared contract alone as the requested literal-prompt deliverable: contradicted by the verified gap analysis.\n62: - Wholesale router replacement: exhausted because current prerequisites, route mappings, proof outputs, and handoff boundaries are useful and should be retained. (iteration 1)\n63: - Presentation-only enrichment: exhausted because it leaves the literal command body dependent on external fragments and preserves the experiential gap. (iteration 1)\n64: - Shell-output compilation for this rewrite: exhausted as disproportionate registry, drift, security, and manifest machinery when native `@` expansion exists. (iteration 2)\n65: - Hand-duplicating the full lifecycle in five commands: exhausted because it creates normative drift without improving runtime self-containment. (iteration 2)\n66: - Applying anti-generic creative rhetoric to `design-reference`: exhausted because extraction quality is source fidelity and provenance, not originality. (iteration 3)\n67: <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n68: \n69: <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n70: ## 9. Ruled-Out Directions\n71: \n72: - Command-owned palettes, typography recipes, style menus, or fixed visual doctrine: ruled out because modes own taste and design judgment. (iteration 1)\n73: - Markdown links/read imperatives and presentation/YAML assets as loader includes: ruled out because they do not provide native file-content expansion. (iteration 2)\n74: - Copying reference inventories, transport mechanics, exact palettes/fonts, token recipes, or validation procedures into command bodies: ruled out as mode/transport-owned doctrine. (iteration 3)\n75: <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n76: \n77: <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n78: ## 10. Carried-Forward Open Questions\n79: \n\n(Showing lines 20-79 of 104. Use offset=80 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"- Provide a durable authority/anti-duplication rule and a testable implementation plan.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 4. Key Questions (Remaining)\n\n- [x] What exactly do the shipped command routers, presentation assets, and shared creation contract contain, and which literal-prompt qualities are absent?\n- [x] What complete literal body should each of the five commands contain so an agent receives an evocative, actionable creation brief rather than a thin route?\n- [x] What include, template injection, renderer, or generated-fragment mechanism does the current command runtime actually support?\n- [x] Which content must stay literal in each command, which content may be shared, and which doctrine must remain mode-owned to prevent drift?\n- [ ] What exact file/change/test sequence can ship the rewrite without breaking route, intake, proof, handoff, or compatibility contracts?\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n## 5. Answered Questions\n\n- The shipped bodies preserve valuable command-specific intake, sibling discrimination, route proof, stable mode mappings, typed outputs, and mutation boundaries, but outsource the creation experience across presentations and the shared contract. The missing layer is a command-visible, evocative, actionable brief with experiential stakes, anti-generic constraints, real context/content, and a mode-specific quality bar. (iteration 1)\n- OpenCode command templates support direct `@./path` file-content expansion. The recommended mechanism is literal, mode-specific creation prose in each command plus one `@./.opencode/skills/sk-design/shared/creation-contract.md` expansion for shared normative lifecycle and authority content. This yields runtime-expanded self-containment; checked-in source-byte duplication would require generation and is unnecessary. (iteration 2)\n- Five concrete body cores now define the command-visible mission, intake, grounding, stable route, ordered work, targeted revision, proof ceiling, typed output, and handoff for design, foundations, motion, audit, and design-reference. Public orchestration stays literal, universal schemas arrive through the shared `@` contract, and values/judgment remain mode-owned. (iteration 3)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"- Provide a durable authority/anti-duplication rule and a testable implementation plan.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 4. Key Questions (Remaining)\n\n- [x] What exactly do the shipped command routers, presentation assets, and shared creation contract contain, and which literal-prompt qualities are absent?\n- [x] What complete literal body should each of the five commands contain so an agent receives an evocative, actionable creation brief rather than a thin route?\n- [x] What include, template injection, renderer, or generated-fragment mechanism does the current command runtime actually support?\n- [x] Which content must stay literal in each command, which content may be shared, and which doctrine must remain mode-owned to prevent drift?\n- [ ] What exact file/change/test sequence can ship the rewrite without breaking route, intake, proof, handoff, or compatibility contracts?\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n## 5. Answered Questions\n\n- The shipped bodies preserve valuable command-specific intake, sibling discrimination, route proof, stable mode mappings, typed outputs, and mutation boundaries, but outsource the creation experience across presentations and the shared contract. The missing layer is a command-visible, evocative, actionable brief with experiential stakes, anti-generic constraints, real context/content, and a mode-specific quality bar. (iteration 1)\n- OpenCode command templates support direct `@./path` file-content expansion. The recommended mechanism is literal, mode-specific creation prose in each command plus one `@./.opencode/skills/sk-design/shared/creation-contract.md` expansion for shared normative lifecycle and authority content. This yields runtime-expanded self-containment; checked-in source-byte duplication would require generation and is unnecessary. (iteration 2)\n- Five concrete body cores now define the command-visible mission, intake, grounding, stable route, ordered work, targeted revision, proof ceiling, typed output, and handoff for design, foundations, motion, audit, and design-reference. Public orchestration stays literal, universal schemas arrive through the shared `@` contract, and values/judgment remain mode-owned. (iteration 3)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n## 6. What Worked\n\n- Exact cross-command anchor comparison separated the shared routing skeleton from meaningful domain-specific intake and exposed the missing prompt layer without discarding working architecture. (iteration 1)\n- Exact command-authoring and renderer-symbol tracing distinguished native `@` expansion, `$ARGUMENTS` substitution, shell rendering, and generated-router patterns. (iteration 2)\n- A common mission-to-handoff grammar plus one decisive mode-specific quality rule produced five concrete prompts without flattening their distinct jobs. (iteration 3)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n## 7. What Failed\n\n- Broad repository search for generic include/template terms was noisy; exact command-runtime and renderer symbols are required for the next pass. (iteration 1)\n- Historical compiled-stub descriptions were insufficient; direct live-command reads were required to establish the current runtime contract. (iteration 2)\n- A broad all-command read truncated before all five routers; exact current anchors plus the prior synthesis covered the missing comparisons, but iteration 4 must narrowly verify authority-bearing phrases against each exact router. (iteration 3)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n## 8. Exhausted Approaches\n\n- Replacing mode judgment with command-owned taste: already rejected by the authority split established in prior research.\n- Treating the current shared contract alone as the requested literal-prompt deliverable: contradicted by the verified gap analysis.\n- Wholesale router replacement: exhausted because current prerequisites, route mappings, proof outputs, and handoff boundaries are useful and should be retained. (iteration 1)\n- Presentation-only enrichment: exhausted because it leaves the literal command body dependent on external fragments and preserves the experiential gap. (iteration 1)\n- Shell-output compilation for this rewrite: exhausted as disproportionate registry, drift, security, and manifest machinery when native `@` expansion exists. (iteration 2)\n- Hand-duplicating the full lifecycle in five commands: exhausted because it creates normative drift without improving runtime self-containment. (iteration 2)\n- Applying anti-generic creative rhetoric to `design-reference`: exhausted because extraction quality is source fidelity and provenance, not originality. (iteration 3)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n## 9. Ruled-Out Directions\n\n- Command-owned palettes, typography recipes, style menus, or fixed visual doctrine: ruled out because modes own taste and design judgment. (iteration 1)\n- Markdown links/read imperatives and presentation/YAML assets as loader includes: ruled out because they do not provide native file-content expansion. (iteration 2)\n- Copying reference inventories, transport mechanics, exact palettes/fonts, token recipes, or validation procedures into command bodies: ruled out as mode/transport-owned doctrine. (iteration 3)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n## 10. Carried-Forward Open Questions\n","lineStart":20,"lineEnd":79,"totalLines":104,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1784626045190,"end":1784626045206}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_029cba594a2c4814016a5f3b7cffbc8191957667480356b710"}},"id":"prt_f840061020014tLSP2SpYU6TXZ","sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","messageID":"msg_f840012fd0016529edbzet2gZk"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784626045252,"sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_1VTINGHKew2ePSAcdoSLP1TH","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json","offset":1,"limit":100},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"openQuestions\": [\n3:     \"What file/change/test sequence can ship the rewrite safely?\"\n4:   ],\n5:   \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n6:     \"What exactly do the shipped command routers, presentation assets, and shared creation contract contain, and which literal-prompt qualities are absent?\",\n7:     \"What include/shared-fragment mechanism does the runtime support?\",\n8:     \"What complete literal body should each of the five commands contain?\",\n9:     \"Which content stays literal, shared, or mode-owned?\"\n10:   ],\n11:   \"keyFindings\": [\n12:     {\"id\":\"I001-F1\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"The five shipped bodies are substantial mode routers, not self-contained creation prompts.\"},\n13:     {\"id\":\"I001-F2\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"Command-specific intake, sibling discrimination, stable mappings, and typed products are working architecture worth preserving.\"},\n14:     {\"id\":\"I001-F3\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"Presentation assets implement progressive intake and visible lifecycle blocks but fragment prompt wording away from command bodies.\"},\n15:     {\"id\":\"I001-F4\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"The skill-local creation contract centralizes choreography and authority while intentionally excluding design taste.\"},\n16:     {\"id\":\"I001-F5\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"The remaining gap is an evocative, actionable, command-visible creation brief, not missing routing architecture.\"},\n17:     {\"id\":\"I002-F1\",\"iteration\":2,\"summary\":\"@./path is the smallest direct runtime file-content expansion mechanism; it makes the rendered prompt, not the checked-in command bytes, self-contained.\"},\n18:     {\"id\":\"I002-F2\",\"iteration\":2,\"summary\":\"$ARGUMENTS preserves invocation intake but is not a shared-fragment mechanism.\"},\n19:     {\"id\":\"I002-F3\",\"iteration\":2,\"summary\":\"Shell-output rendering is feasible but introduces disproportionate registry, drift, rollout, security, and manifest machinery.\"},\n20:     {\"id\":\"I002-F4\",\"iteration\":2,\"summary\":\"Generation is required only if every checked-in command must contain all canonical shared bytes.\"},\n21:     {\"id\":\"I002-F5\",\"iteration\":2,\"summary\":\"Use a literal mode-specific creation brief plus one @ reference to the shared normative creation contract.\"},\n22:     {\"id\":\"I003-F1\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"Literal command bodies should own the mode-specific mission, progressive intake, ordered work, critique rule, evidence ceiling, and typed product while delegating taste.\"},\n23:     {\"id\":\"I003-F2\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"One canonical @ expansion carries shared lifecycle and schemas without five-copy drift.\"},\n24:     {\"id\":\"I003-F3\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"A three-way placement rule separates literal public orchestration, shared normative schemas, and mode-owned judgment.\"},\n25:     {\"id\":\"I003-F4\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"All five bodies can share one structural grammar while retaining distinct decisive quality rules.\"},\n26:     {\"id\":\"I003-F5\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"Design-reference substitutes source fidelity and provenance for anti-generic creative originality.\"}\n27:   ],\n28:   \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n29:     \"Replace the working routers wholesale\",\n30:     \"Copy mode-owned taste doctrine into commands\",\n31:     \"Treat presentation assets or the shared contract alone as the literal-prompt deliverable\",\n32:     \"Use Markdown links or read imperatives as loader includes\",\n33:     \"Use a shell-command renderer as the smallest mechanism\",\n34:     \"Hand-duplicate the complete shared lifecycle\",\n35:     \"Copy mode-owned reference inventories or transport mechanics into commands\",\n36:     \"Apply anti-generic creation rhetoric to source-faithful extraction\"\n37:   ],\n38:   \"metrics\": {\n39:     \"iterationsCompleted\": 3,\n40:     \"openQuestions\": 1,\n41:     \"resolvedQuestions\": 4,\n42:     \"keyFindings\": 15,\n43:     \"convergenceScore\": 0.8,\n44:     \"coverageBySources\": {\"commands\":7,\"presentations\":5,\"shared-contract\":1,\"prior-research\":2,\"runtime-docs\":3,\"runtime-code\":2,\"runtime-tests\":1,\"external-docs\":1,\"mode-contracts\":5}\n45:   },\n46:   \"status\": \"iterating\",\n47:   \"sessionId\": \"fanout-sol-high-fast-1784623934648-kt3qkt\",\n48:   \"generation\": 1,\n49:   \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-07-21T09:15:01Z\"\n50: }\n\n(End of file - total 50 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"openQuestions\": [\n    \"What file/change/test sequence can ship the rewrite safely?\"\n  ],\n  \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n    \"What exactly do the shipped command routers, presentation assets, and shared creation contract contain, and which literal-prompt qualities are absent?\",\n    \"What include/shared-fragment mechanism does the runtime support?\",\n    \"What complete literal body should each of the five commands contain?\",\n    \"Which content stays literal, shared, or mode-owned?\"\n  ],\n  \"keyFindings\": [\n    {\"id\":\"I001-F1\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"The five shipped bodies are substantial mode routers, not self-contained creation prompts.\"},\n    {\"id\":\"I001-F2\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"Command-specific intake, sibling discrimination, stable mappings, and typed products are working architecture worth preserving.\"},\n    {\"id\":\"I001-F3\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"Presentation assets implement progressive intake and visible lifecycle blocks but fragment prompt wording away from command bodies.\"},\n    {\"id\":\"I001-F4\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"The skill-local creation contract centralizes choreography and authority while intentionally excluding design taste.\"},\n    {\"id\":\"I001-F5\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"The remaining gap is an evocative, actionable, command-visible creation brief, not missing routing architecture.\"},\n    {\"id\":\"I002-F1\",\"iteration\":2,\"summary\":\"@./path is the smallest direct runtime file-content expansion mechanism; it makes the rendered prompt, not the checked-in command bytes, self-contained.\"},\n    {\"id\":\"I002-F2\",\"iteration\":2,\"summary\":\"$ARGUMENTS preserves invocation intake but is not a shared-fragment mechanism.\"},\n    {\"id\":\"I002-F3\",\"iteration\":2,\"summary\":\"Shell-output rendering is feasible but introduces disproportionate registry, drift, rollout, security, and manifest machinery.\"},\n    {\"id\":\"I002-F4\",\"iteration\":2,\"summary\":\"Generation is required only if every checked-in command must contain all canonical shared bytes.\"},","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json","text":"{\n  \"openQuestions\": [\n    \"What file/change/test sequence can ship the rewrite safely?\"\n  ],\n  \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n    \"What exactly do the shipped command routers, presentation assets, and shared creation contract contain, and which literal-prompt qualities are absent?\",\n    \"What include/shared-fragment mechanism does the runtime support?\",\n    \"What complete literal body should each of the five commands contain?\",\n    \"Which content stays literal, shared, or mode-owned?\"\n  ],\n  \"keyFindings\": [\n    {\"id\":\"I001-F1\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"The five shipped bodies are substantial mode routers, not self-contained creation prompts.\"},\n    {\"id\":\"I001-F2\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"Command-specific intake, sibling discrimination, stable mappings, and typed products are working architecture worth preserving.\"},\n    {\"id\":\"I001-F3\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"Presentation assets implement progressive intake and visible lifecycle blocks but fragment prompt wording away from command bodies.\"},\n    {\"id\":\"I001-F4\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"The skill-local creation contract centralizes choreography and authority while intentionally excluding design taste.\"},\n    {\"id\":\"I001-F5\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"The remaining gap is an evocative, actionable, command-visible creation brief, not missing routing architecture.\"},\n    {\"id\":\"I002-F1\",\"iteration\":2,\"summary\":\"@./path is the smallest direct runtime file-content expansion mechanism; it makes the rendered prompt, not the checked-in command bytes, self-contained.\"},\n    {\"id\":\"I002-F2\",\"iteration\":2,\"summary\":\"$ARGUMENTS preserves invocation intake but is not a shared-fragment mechanism.\"},\n    {\"id\":\"I002-F3\",\"iteration\":2,\"summary\":\"Shell-output rendering is feasible but introduces disproportionate registry, drift, rollout, security, and manifest machinery.\"},\n    {\"id\":\"I002-F4\",\"iteration\":2,\"summary\":\"Generation is required only if every checked-in command must contain all canonical shared bytes.\"},\n    {\"id\":\"I002-F5\",\"iteration\":2,\"summary\":\"Use a literal mode-specific creation brief plus one @ reference to the shared normative creation contract.\"},\n    {\"id\":\"I003-F1\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"Literal command bodies should own the mode-specific mission, progressive intake, ordered work, critique rule, evidence ceiling, and typed product while delegating taste.\"},\n    {\"id\":\"I003-F2\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"One canonical @ expansion carries shared lifecycle and schemas without five-copy drift.\"},\n    {\"id\":\"I003-F3\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"A three-way placement rule separates literal public orchestration, shared normative schemas, and mode-owned judgment.\"},\n    {\"id\":\"I003-F4\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"All five bodies can share one structural grammar while retaining distinct decisive quality rules.\"},\n    {\"id\":\"I003-F5\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"Design-reference substitutes source fidelity and provenance for anti-generic creative originality.\"}\n  ],\n  \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n    \"Replace the working routers wholesale\",\n    \"Copy mode-owned taste doctrine into commands\",\n    \"Treat presentation assets or the shared contract alone as the literal-prompt deliverable\",\n    \"Use Markdown links or read imperatives as loader includes\",\n    \"Use a shell-command renderer as the smallest mechanism\",\n    \"Hand-duplicate the complete shared lifecycle\",\n    \"Copy mode-owned reference inventories or transport mechanics into commands\",\n    \"Apply anti-generic creation rhetoric to source-faithful extraction\"\n  ],\n  \"metrics\": {\n    \"iterationsCompleted\": 3,\n    \"openQuestions\": 1,\n    \"resolvedQuestions\": 4,\n    \"keyFindings\": 15,\n    \"convergenceScore\": 0.8,\n    \"coverageBySources\": {\"commands\":7,\"presentations\":5,\"shared-contract\":1,\"prior-research\":2,\"runtime-docs\":3,\"runtime-code\":2,\"runtime-tests\":1,\"external-docs\":1,\"mode-contracts\":5}\n  },\n  \"status\": \"iterating\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"fanout-sol-high-fas