{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784626045315,"sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_7XeN949kSlZu5pBCqtonAFjM","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-dashboard.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-dashboard.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Research Dashboard\n2: \n3: ## Iteration Table\n4: \n5: | run | focus | newInfoRatio | findings | status |\n6: |---:|---|---:|---:|---|\n7: | 1 | Shipped command anatomy and literal-prompt gap | 0.90 | 5 | complete |\n8: | 2 | Runtime include/shared-fragment mechanism | 1.00 | 5 | complete |\n9: | 3 | Five literal body cores and content ownership | 0.90 | 5 | complete |\n10: \n11: ## Question Status\n12: \n13: - Answered: 4 / 5\n14: - Remaining: implementation and verification sequence.\n15: \n16: ## Convergence Trend\n17: \n18: - Ratios: 0.90 -> 1.00 -> 0.90\n19: - Minimum-iteration guard: passed after iteration 3.\n20: - Stop policy: `max-iterations`; convergence is telemetry only until iteration 5.\n21: - Stuck count: 0\n22: \n23: ## Dead Ends\n24: \n25: - Broad repository searches over generic include/template terms are too noisy.\n26: - Wholesale router replacement and command-owned taste doctrine are eliminated.\n27: - Markdown/read references are not loader includes; shell rendering and full hand duplication are unnecessary.\n28: - Design-reference must not inherit originality rhetoric; reference inventories and transport mechanics stay mode-owned.\n29: \n30: ## Next Focus\n31: \n32: Adversarially review phrase-level authority, proof, mutation, routing, and typed-status behavior.\n33: \n34: ## Active Risks\n35: \n36: - `@./path` runtime expansion still needs a representative live command-dispatch fixture during implementation.\n37: - Literal richness must not fork mode-owned taste doctrine.\n38: - The five drafts need exact-router comparison before their implementation sequence can be trusted.\n\n(End of file - total 38 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Research Dashboard\n\n## Iteration Table\n\n| run | focus | newInfoRatio | findings | status |\n|---:|---|---:|---:|---|\n| 1 | Shipped command anatomy and literal-prompt gap | 0.90 | 5 | complete |\n| 2 | Runtime include/shared-fragment mechanism | 1.00 | 5 | complete |\n| 3 | Five literal body cores and content ownership | 0.90 | 5 | complete |\n\n## Question Status\n\n- Answered: 4 / 5\n- Remaining: implementation and verification sequence.\n\n## Convergence Trend\n\n- Ratios: 0.90 -> 1.00 -> 0.90\n- Minimum-iteration guard: passed after iteration 3.\n- Stop policy: `max-iterations`; convergence is telemetry only until iteration 5.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-dashboard.md","text":"# Deep Research Dashboard\n\n## Iteration Table\n\n| run | focus | newInfoRatio | findings | status |\n|---:|---|---:|---:|---|\n| 1 | Shipped command anatomy and literal-prompt gap | 0.90 | 5 | complete |\n| 2 | Runtime include/shared-fragment mechanism | 1.00 | 5 | complete |\n| 3 | Five literal body cores and content ownership | 0.90 | 5 | complete |\n\n## Question Status\n\n- Answered: 4 / 5\n- Remaining: implementation and verification sequence.\n\n## Convergence Trend\n\n- Ratios: 0.90 -> 1.00 -> 0.90\n- Minimum-iteration guard: passed after iteration 3.\n- Stop policy: `max-iterations`; convergence is telemetry only until iteration 5.\n- Stuck count: 0\n\n## Dead Ends\n\n- Broad repository searches over generic include/template terms are too noisy.\n- Wholesale router replacement and command-owned taste doctrine are eliminated.\n- Markdown/read references are not loader includes; shell rendering and full hand duplication are unnecessary.\n- Design-reference must not inherit originality rhetoric; reference inventories and transport mechanics stay mode-owned.\n\n## Next Focus\n\nAdversarially review phrase-level authority, proof, mutation, routing, and typed-status behavior.\n\n## Active Risks\n\n- `@./path` runtime expansion still needs a representative live command-dispatch fixture during implementation.\n- Literal richness must not fork mode-owned taste doctrine.\n- The five drafts need exact-router comparison before their implementation sequence can be trusted.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":38,"totalLines":38,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-dashboard.md","time":{"start":1784626045305,"end":1784626045312}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_029cba594a2c4814016a5f3b7cffd08191b4c976021d1c9884"}},"id":"prt_f84006168001zQXHHKqTqASWrm","sessionID":"ses_07c1fcf6effe2YUDoq6jbB4HYf","messageID":"msg_f840012fd0016529edbzet2gZk"}}
