 or compatibility contracts?\n <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n ## 5. Answered Questions\n \n - The shipped bodies preserve valuable command-specific intake, sibling discrimination, route proof, stable mode mappings, typed outputs, and mutation boundaries, but outsource the creation experience across presentations and the shared contract. The missing layer is a command-visible, evocative, actionable brief with experiential stakes, anti-generic constraints, real context/content, and a mode-specific quality bar. (iteration 1)\n - OpenCode command templates support direct `@./path` file-content expansion. The recommended mechanism is literal, mode-specific creation prose in each command plus one `@./.opencode/skills/sk-design/shared/creation-contract.md` expansion for shared normative lifecycle and authority content. This yields runtime-expanded self-containment; checked-in source-byte duplication would require generation and is unnecessary. (iteration 2)\n - Five concrete body cores now define the command-visible mission, intake, grounding, stable route, ordered work, targeted revision, proof ceiling, typed output, and handoff for design, foundations, motion, audit, and design-reference. Public orchestration stays literal, universal schemas arrive through the shared `@` contract, and values/judgment remain mode-owned. (iteration 3)\n+- Adversarial review preserved the missions and mode-specific quality rules but moved universal intake schemas, common blocks, targeted revision, evidence labels, and handoff continuity back to the shared contract. It restored `ASK`, required literal suffix control, made audit review-only, and restricted design-reference token tables to measured values. The safe shipment is test-first and atomic across wrappers, presentation/YAML ownership declarations, and metadata projections. (iteration 4)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n \n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n@@ -43,16 +44,18 @@\n \n - Exact cross-command anchor comparison separated the shared routing skeleton from meaningful domain-specific intake and exposed the missing prompt layer without discarding working architecture. (iteration 1)\n - Exact command-authoring and renderer-symbol tracing distinguished native `@` expansion, `$ARGUMENTS` substitution, shell rendering, and generated-router patterns. (iteration 2)\n - A common mission-to-handoff grammar plus one decisive mode-specific quality rule produced five concrete prompts without flattening their distinct jobs. (iteration 3)\n+- Phrase-level contract comparison and the 15-test baseline exposed regressions that thematic prompt review missed. (iteration 4)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n ## 7. What Failed\n \n - Broad repository search for generic include/template terms was noisy; exact command-runtime and renderer symbols are required for the next pass. (iteration 1)\n - Historical compiled-stub descriptions were insufficient; direct live-command reads were required to establish the current runtime contract. (iteration 2)\n - A broad all-command read truncated before all five routers; exact current anchors plus the prior synthesis covered the missing comparisons, but iteration 4 must narrowly verify authority-bearing phrases against each exact router. (iteration 3)\n+- Official documentation proves `@` content expansion but does not explicitly define the base of the exact `@./.opencode/...` spelling; the lineage-only boundary prohibits creating a scratch command outside this packet. (iteration 4)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n ## 8. Exhausted Approaches\n@@ -63,28 +66,30 @@\n - Presentation-only enrichment: exhausted because it leaves the literal command body dependent on external fragments and preserves the experiential gap. (iteration 1)\n - Shell-output compilation for this rewrite: exhausted as disproportionate registry, drift, security, and manifest machinery when native `@` expansion exists. (iteration 2)\n - Hand-duplicating the full lifecycle in five commands: exhausted because it creates normative drift without improving runtime self-containment. (iteration 2)\n - Applying anti-generic creative rhetoric to `design-reference`: exhausted because extraction quality is source fidelity and provenance, not originality. (iteration 3)\n+- Wrapper-only literal enrichment while retaining presentations as normative prompt authority: exhausted because it creates competing command-package sources of truth. (iteration 4)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n ## 9. Ruled-Out Directions\n \n - Command-owned palettes, typography recipes, style menus, or fixed visual doctrine: ruled out because modes own taste and design judgment. (iteration 1)\n - Markdown links/read imperatives and presentation/YAML assets as loader includes: ruled out because they do not provide native file-content expansion. (iteration 2)\n - Copying reference inventories, transport mechanics, exact palettes/fonts, token recipes, or validation procedures into command bodies: ruled out as mode/transport-owned doctrine. (iteration 3)\n+- Dropping `STATUS=ASK`, letting audit apply fixes, or allowing brief-provided values into design-reference token tables: ruled out by shared and mode contracts. (iteration 4)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n ## 10. Carried-Forward Open Questions\n \n-None yet.\n+- Verify the exact project-root include token in an isolated implementation fixture before merging; documentation supports `@path` inclusion but the proposed `@./.opencode/...` base remains unproven. (iteration 4)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n ## 11. Next Focus\n \n-Adversarially review the five proposed bodies against each exact current router, mode authority, mutation boundary, evidence ceiling, suffix/cannot-run/sibling routing, and typed statuses. Produce phrase-level keep/move/delete corrections and identify the implementation/test sequence constraints.\n+Resolve the include token from the strongest available runtime/source evidence without violating the lineage-only write boundary, then consolidate the corrected body grammar, acceptance matrix, rollout order, risks, and residual fixture requirement for final synthesis.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n ## 12. Known Context\n","additions":8,"deletions":3},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json","relativePath":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json\n@@ -1,13 +1,12 @@\n {\n-  \"openQuestions\": [\n-    \"What file/change/test sequence can ship the rewrite safely?\"\n-  ],\n+  \"openQuestions\": [\"What exact project-root spelling should the isolated live include fixture promote?\"],\n   \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n     \"What exactly do the shipped command routers, presentation assets, and shared creation contract contain, and which literal-prompt qualities are absent?\",\n     \"What include/shared-fragment mechanism does the runtime support?\",\n     \"What complete literal body should each of the five commands contain?\",\n-    \"Which content stays literal, shared, or mode-owned?\"\n+    \"Which content stays literal, shared, or mode-owned?\",\n+    \"What file/change/test sequence can ship the rewrite safely?\"\n   ],\n   \"keyFindings\": [\n     {\"id\":\"I001-F1\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"The five shipped bodies are substantial mode routers, not self-contained creation prompts.\"},\n     {\"id\":\"I001-F2\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"Command-specific intake, sibling discrimination, stable mappings, and typed products are working architecture worth preserving.\"},\n@@ -22,9 +21,14 @@\n     {\"id\":\"I003-F1\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"Literal command bodies should own the mode-specific mission, progressive intake, ordered work, critique rule, evidence ceiling, and typed product while delegating taste.\"},\n     {\"id\":\"I003-F2\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"One canonical @ expansion carries shared lifecycle and schemas without five-copy drift.\"},\n     {\"id\":\"I003-F3\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"A three-way placement rule separates literal public orchestration, shared normative schemas, and mode-owned judgment.\"},\n     {\"id\":\"I003-F4\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"All five bodies can share one structural grammar while retaining distinct decisive quality rules.\"},\n-    {\"id\":\"I003-F5\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"Design-reference substitutes source fidelity and provenance for anti-generic creative originality.\"}\n+    {\"id\":\"I003-F5\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"Design-reference substitutes source fidelity and provenance for anti-generic creative originality.\"},\n+    {\"id\":\"I004-F1\",\"iteration\":4,\"summary\":\"Keep mode-specific missions and local fields, but move universal lifecycle, intake schemas, output blocks, proof labels, and handoff continuity to the shared contract.\"},\n+    {\"id\":\"I004-F2\",\"iteration\":4,\"summary\":\"The proposed OK|DEFER|FAIL shorthand regresses the required STATUS=ASK path.\"},\n+    {\"id\":\"I004-F3\",\"iteration\":4,\"summary\":\"Suffix behavior and prompt ownership must be changed atomically because literal wrapper prompts conflict with current presentation-owned wording.\"},\n+    {\"id\":\"I004-F4\",\"iteration\":4,\"summary\":\"Audit remains review-only; md-generator alone may write artifacts and only measured values may enter token tables.\"},\n+    {\"id\":\"I004-F5\",\"iteration\":4,\"summary\":\"Safe shipment requires an include-root fixture, test-first body invariants, atomic package ownership edits, and suffix/status/mutation negative cases.\"}\n   ],\n   \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n     \"Replace the working routers wholesale\",\n     \"Copy mode-owned taste doctrine into commands\",\n@@ -32,19 +36,24 @@\n     \"Use Markdown links or read imperatives as loader includes\",\n     \"Use a shell-command renderer as the smallest mechanism\",\n     \"Hand-duplicate the complete shared lifecycle\",\n     \"Copy mode-owned reference inventories or transport mechanics into commands\",\n-    \"Apply anti-generic creation rhetoric to source-faithful extraction\"\n+    \"Apply anti-generic creation rhetoric to source-faithful extraction\",\n+    \"Drop STATUS=ASK from literal bodies\",\n+    \"Keep presentations as a competing normative prompt authority\",\n+    \"Allow audit to apply fixes\",\n+    \"Allow brief-provided values into design-reference token tables\",\n+    \"Claim exact @./ rooting without a live fixture\"\n   ],\n   \"metrics\": {\n-    \"iterationsCompleted\": 3,\n+    \"iterationsCompleted\": 4,\n     \"openQuestions\": 1,\n-    \"resolvedQuestions\": 4,\n-    \"keyFindings\": 15,\n-    \"convergenceScore\": 0.8,\n-    \"coverageBySources\": {\"commands\":7,\"presentations\":5,\"shared-contract\":1,\"prior-research\":2,\"runtime-docs\":3,\"runtime-code\":2,\"runtime-tests\":1,\"external-docs\":1,\"mode-contracts\":5}\n+    \"resolvedQuestions\": 5,\n+    \"keyFindings\": 20,\n+    \"convergenceScore\": 0.9,\n+    \"coverageBySources\": {\"commands\":7,\"presentations\":5,\"shared-contract\":1,\"prior-research\":2,\"runtime-docs\":3,\"runtime-code\":2,\"runtime-tests\":3,\"external-docs\":1,\"mode-contracts\":5,\"metadata\":2}\n   },\n   \"status\": \"iterating\",\n   \"sessionId\": \"fanout-sol-high-fast-1784623934648-kt3qkt\",\n   \"generation\": 1,\n-  \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-07-21T09:15:01Z\"\n+  \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-07-21T09:22:02Z\"\n }\n","additions":21,"deletions":12},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/orchestration-status.log","relativePath":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/orchestration-status.log","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/004-commands/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/orchestration-status.log\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-datab